v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

137// Base class for shell ArrayBuffer allocators. It forwards all operations to
138// the default v8 allocator.
139class ArrayBufferAllocatorBase : public v8::ArrayBuffer::Allocator {
140 public:
141 void* Allocate(size_t length) override {
142 return allocator_->Allocate(length);
143 }
144
145 void* AllocateUninitialized(size_t length) override {
146 return allocator_->AllocateUninitialized(length);
147 }
148
149 void Free(void* data, size_t length) override {
150 allocator_->Free(data, length);
151 }
152
153 private:
154 std::unique_ptr<Allocator> allocator_ =
155 std::unique_ptr<Allocator>(NewDefaultAllocator());
156};
157
158// ArrayBuffer allocator that can use virtual memory to improve performance.
159class ShellArrayBufferAllocator : public ArrayBufferAllocatorBase {
160 public:
161 void* Allocate(size_t length) override {
162 if (length >= kVMThreshold) return AllocateVM(length);
163 return ArrayBufferAllocatorBase::Allocate(length);
164 }
165
166 void* AllocateUninitialized(size_t length) override {
167 if (length >= kVMThreshold) return AllocateVM(length);
168 return ArrayBufferAllocatorBase::AllocateUninitialized(length);
169 }
170
171 void Free(void* data, size_t length) override {
172 if (length >= kVMThreshold) {
173 FreeVM(data, length);
174 } else {
175 ArrayBufferAllocatorBase::Free(data, length);
176 }
177 }
178
179 private:
180 static constexpr size_t kVMThreshold = 65536;
181
182 void* AllocateVM(size_t length) {
183 DCHECK_LE(kVMThreshold, length);
184 v8::PageAllocator* page_allocator = i::GetArrayBufferPageAllocator();
185 size_t page_size = page_allocator->AllocatePageSize();
186 size_t allocated = RoundUp(length, page_size);
187 return i::AllocatePages(page_allocator, nullptr, allocated, page_size,
188 PageAllocator::kReadWrite);
189 }
190
191 void FreeVM(void* data, size_t length) {
192 v8::PageAllocator* page_allocator = i::GetArrayBufferPageAllocator();
193 size_t page_size = page_allocator->AllocatePageSize();
194 size_t allocated = RoundUp(length, page_size);
195 i::FreePages(page_allocator, data, allocated);
196 }
197};
198
199// ArrayBuffer allocator that never allocates over 10MB.
200class MockArrayBufferAllocator : public ArrayBufferAllocatorBase {
201 protected:
202 void* Allocate(size_t length) override {
203 return ArrayBufferAllocatorBase::Allocate(Adjust(length));
204 }
205
206 void* AllocateUninitialized(size_t length) override {
207 return ArrayBufferAllocatorBase::AllocateUninitialized(Adjust(length));
208 }
209
210 void Free(void* data, size_t length) override {
211 return ArrayBufferAllocatorBase::Free(data, Adjust(length));
212 }
213
214 private:
215 size_t Adjust(size_t length) {
216 const size_t kAllocationLimit = 10 * i::MB;
217 return length > kAllocationLimit ? i::AllocatePageSize() : length;
218 }
219};
220
221// ArrayBuffer allocator that can be equipped with a limit to simulate system
222// OOM.
223class MockArrayBufferAllocatiorWithLimit : public MockArrayBufferAllocator {
224 public:
225 explicit MockArrayBufferAllocatiorWithLimit(size_t allocation_limit)
226 : space_left_(allocation_limit) {}
227
228 protected:
229 void* Allocate(size_t length) override {
230 if (length > space_left_) {
231 return nullptr;
232 }
233 space_left_ -= length;
234 return MockArrayBufferAllocator::Allocate(length);
235 }
236
237 void* AllocateUninitialized(size_t length) override {
238 if (length > space_left_) {
239 return nullptr;
240 }
241 space_left_ -= length;
242 return MockArrayBufferAllocator::AllocateUninitialized(length);
243 }
244
245 void Free(void* data, size_t length) override {
246 space_left_ += length;
247 return MockArrayBufferAllocator::Free(data, length);
248 }
249
250 private:
251 std::atomic<size_t> space_left_;
252};

254#ifdef V8_OS_LINUX

256// This is a mock allocator variant that provides a huge virtual allocation
257// backed by a small real allocation that is repeatedly mapped. If you create an
258// array on memory allocated by this allocator, you will observe that elements
259// will alias each other as if their indices were modulo-divided by the real
260// allocation length.
261// The purpose is to allow stability-testing of huge (typed) arrays without
262// actually consuming huge amounts of physical memory.
263// This is currently only available on Linux because it relies on {mremap}.
264class MultiMappedAllocator : public ArrayBufferAllocatorBase {
265 protected:
266 void* Allocate(size_t length) override {
267 if (length < kChunkSize) {
268 return ArrayBufferAllocatorBase::Allocate(length);
269 }
270 // We use mmap, which initializes pages to zero anyway.
271 return AllocateUninitialized(length);
272 }
273
274 void* AllocateUninitialized(size_t length) override {
275 if (length < kChunkSize) {
276 return ArrayBufferAllocatorBase::AllocateUninitialized(length);
277 }
278 size_t rounded_length = RoundUp(length, kChunkSize);
279 int prot = PROT_READ | PROT_WRITE;
280 // We have to specify MAP_SHARED to make {mremap} below do what we want.
281 int flags = MAP_SHARED | MAP_ANONYMOUS;
282 void* real_alloc = mmap(nullptr, kChunkSize, prot, flags, -1, 0);
283 if (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(real_alloc) == -1) {
284 // If we ran into some limit (physical or virtual memory, or number
285 // of mappings, etc), return {nullptr}, which callers can handle.
286 if (errno == ENOMEM) {
287 return nullptr;
288 }
289 // Other errors may be bugs which we want to learn about.
290 FATAL("mmap (real) failed with error %d: %s", errno, strerror(errno));
291 }
292#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
293 // The backing memory must be allocated inside the sandbox as it will be
294 // used for array buffer contents.
295 // Here we go into somewhat less-well-defined territory by using the
296 // sandbox's virtual address space to essentially just reserve a number of
297 // OS pages inside the sandbox, but then using mremap to replace these
298 // pages directly afterwards. In practice, this works fine however.
299 VirtualAddressSpace* vas = i::Sandbox::current()->address_space();
300 i::Address in_sandbox_page_reservation = vas->AllocatePages(
301 VirtualAddressSpace::kNoHint, rounded_length,
302 vas->allocation_granularity(), PagePermissions::kNoAccess);
303 void* virtual_alloc =
304 in_sandbox_page_reservation != 0
305 ? reinterpret_cast<void*>(in_sandbox_page_reservation)
306 : reinterpret_cast<void*>(-1);
307#else
308 void* virtual_alloc =
309 mmap(nullptr, rounded_length, prot, flags | MAP_NORESERVE, -1, 0);
310#endif
311 if (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(virtual_alloc) == -1) {
312 if (errno == ENOMEM) {
313 // Undo earlier, successful mappings.
314 munmap(real_alloc, kChunkSize);
315 return nullptr;
316 }
317 FATAL("mmap (virtual) failed with error %d: %s", errno, strerror(errno));
318 }
319 i::Address virtual_base = reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(virtual_alloc);
320 i::Address virtual_end = virtual_base + rounded_length;
321 for (i::Address to_map = virtual_base; to_map < virtual_end;
322 to_map += kChunkSize) {
323 // Specifying 0 as the "old size" causes the existing map entry to not
324 // get deleted, which is important so that we can remap it again in the
325 // next iteration of this loop.
326 void* result =
327 mremap(real_alloc, 0, kChunkSize, MREMAP_MAYMOVE | MREMAP_FIXED,
328 reinterpret_cast<void*>(to_map));
329 if (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(result) == -1) {
330 if (errno == ENOMEM) {
331 // Undo earlier, successful mappings.
332 munmap(real_alloc, kChunkSize);
333#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
334 vas->FreePages(in_sandbox_page_reservation, rounded_length);
335#else
336 munmap(virtual_alloc, rounded_length);
337#endif
338 return nullptr;
339 }
340 FATAL("mremap failed with error %d: %s", errno, strerror(errno));
341 }
342 }
343 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&regions_mutex_);
344 regions_[virtual_alloc] = real_alloc;
345 return virtual_alloc;
346 }
347
348 void Free(void* data, size_t length) override {
349 if (length < kChunkSize) {
350 return ArrayBufferAllocatorBase::Free(data, length);
351 }
352 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&regions_mutex_);
353 void* real_alloc = regions_[data];
354 munmap(real_alloc, kChunkSize);
355 size_t rounded_length = RoundUp(length, kChunkSize);
356#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
357 VirtualAddressSpace* vas = i::Sandbox::current()->address_space();
358 vas->FreePages(reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(data), rounded_length);
359#else
360 munmap(data, rounded_length);
361#endif
362 regions_.erase(data);
363 }
364
365 private:
366 // Aiming for a "Huge Page" (2M on Linux x64) to go easy on the TLB.
367 static constexpr size_t kChunkSize = 2 * 1024 * 1024;
368
369 std::unordered_map<void*, void*> regions_;
370 base::SpinningMutex regions_mutex_;
371};
372
373#endif // V8_OS_LINUX

378template <int N>
379void ThrowError(Isolate* isolate, const char (&message)[N]) {
380 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) return;
381 isolate->ThrowError(message);
382}
383
384void ThrowError(Isolate* isolate, Local<String> message) {
385 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) return;
386 isolate->ThrowError(message);
387}
388
389void ThrowException(Isolate* isolate, Local<Value> exception) {
390 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) return;
391 isolate->ThrowException(exception);
392}

394static MaybeLocal<Value> TryGetValue(v8::Isolate* isolate,
395 Local<Context> context,
396 Local<v8::Object> object,
397 const char* property) {
398 MaybeLocal<String> v8_str = String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, property);
399 if (v8_str.IsEmpty()) return {};
400 return object->Get(context, v8_str.ToLocalChecked());
401}
402
403static Local<Value> GetValue(v8::Isolate* isolate, Local<Context> context,
404 Local<v8::Object> object, const char* property) {
405 return TryGetValue(isolate, context, object, property).ToLocalChecked();
406}
407
408std::shared_ptr<Worker> GetWorkerFromInternalField(Isolate* isolate,
409 Local<Object> object) {
410 if (object->InternalFieldCount() != 1) {
411 ThrowError(isolate, "this is not a Worker");
412 return nullptr;
413 }
414
415 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> handle =
416 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*object->GetInternalField(0));
417 if (IsSmi(*handle)) {
418 ThrowError(isolate, "Worker is defunct because main thread is terminating");
419 return nullptr;
420 }
421 auto managed = i::Cast<i::Managed<Worker>>(handle);
422 return managed->get();
423}
424
425base::Thread::Options GetThreadOptions(const char* name) {
426 // On some systems (OSX 10.6) the stack size default is 0.5Mb or less
427 // which is not enough to parse the big literal expressions used in tests.
428 // The stack size should be at least StackGuard::kLimitSize + some
429 // OS-specific padding for thread startup code. 2Mbytes seems to be enough.
430 return base::Thread::Options(name, 2 * i::MB);
431}

439static constexpr char kIncludedCategoriesParam[] = "included_categories";
440static constexpr char kTraceConfigParam[] = "trace_config";
441
442class TraceConfigParser {
443 public:
444 static void FillTraceConfig(v8::Isolate* isolate,
445 platform::tracing::TraceConfig* trace_config,
446 const char* json_str) {
447 HandleScope outer_scope(isolate);
448 Local<Context> context = Context::New(isolate);
449 Context::Scope context_scope(context);
450 HandleScope inner_scope(isolate);
451
452 Local<String> source =
453 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, json_str).ToLocalChecked();
454 Local<Value> result = JSON::Parse(context, source).ToLocalChecked();
455 Local<v8::Object> trace_config_object = result.As<v8::Object>();
456 // Try reading 'trace_config' property from a full chrome trace config.
457 // https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/master/docs/memory-infra/memory_infra_startup_tracing.md#the-advanced-way
458 Local<Value> maybe_trace_config_object =
459 GetValue(isolate, context, trace_config_object, kTraceConfigParam);
460 if (maybe_trace_config_object->IsObject()) {
461 trace_config_object = maybe_trace_config_object.As<Object>();
462 }
463
464 UpdateIncludedCategoriesList(isolate, context, trace_config_object,
465 trace_config);
466 }
467
468 private:
469 static int UpdateIncludedCategoriesList(
470 v8::Isolate* isolate, Local<Context> context, Local<v8::Object> object,
471 platform::tracing::TraceConfig* trace_config) {
472 Local<Value> value =
473 GetValue(isolate, context, object, kIncludedCategoriesParam);
474 if (value->IsArray()) {
475 Local<Array> v8_array = value.As<Array>();
476 for (int i = 0, length = v8_array->Length(); i < length; ++i) {
477 Local<Value> v = v8_array->Get(context, i)
478 .ToLocalChecked()
479 ->ToString(context)
480 .ToLocalChecked();
481 String::Utf8Value str(isolate, v->ToString(context).ToLocalChecked());
482 trace_config->AddIncludedCategory(*str);
483 }
484 return v8_array->Length();
485 }
486 return 0;
487 }
488};
489
490} // namespace
491
492static platform::tracing::TraceConfig* CreateTraceConfigFromJSON(
493 v8::Isolate* isolate, const char* json_str) {
494 platform::tracing::TraceConfig* trace_config =
495 new platform::tracing::TraceConfig();
496 TraceConfigParser::FillTraceConfig(isolate, trace_config, json_str);
497 return trace_config;
498}

546
547ScriptCompiler::CachedData* Shell::LookupCodeCache(Isolate* isolate,
548 Local<Value> source) {
549 i::ParkedMutexGuard lock_guard(
550 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)->main_thread_local_isolate(),
551 cached_code_mutex_.Pointer());
552 CHECK(source->IsString());
553 v8::String::Utf8Value key(isolate, source);
554 DCHECK(*key);
555 auto entry = cached_code_map_.find(*key);
556 if (entry != cached_code_map_.end() && entry->second) {
557 int length = entry->second->length;
558 uint8_t* cache = new uint8_t[length];
559 memcpy(cache, entry->second->data, length);
560 ScriptCompiler::CachedData* cached_data = new ScriptCompiler::CachedData(
561 cache, length, ScriptCompiler::CachedData::BufferOwned);
562 return cached_data;
563 }
564 return nullptr;
565}
566
567void Shell::StoreInCodeCache(Isolate* isolate, Local<Value> source,
568 const ScriptCompiler::CachedData* cache_data) {
569 i::ParkedMutexGuard lock_guard(
570 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)->main_thread_local_isolate(),
571 cached_code_mutex_.Pointer());
572 CHECK(source->IsString());
573 if (cache_data == nullptr) return;
574 v8::String::Utf8Value key(isolate, source);
575 DCHECK(*key);
576 int length = cache_data->length;
577 uint8_t* cache = new uint8_t[length];
578 memcpy(cache, cache_data->data, length);
579 cached_code_map_[*key] = std::unique_ptr<ScriptCompiler::CachedData>(
580 new ScriptCompiler::CachedData(cache, length,
581 ScriptCompiler::CachedData::BufferOwned));
582}

584// Dummy external source stream which returns the whole source in one go.
585// TODO(leszeks): Also test chunking the data.
586class DummySourceStream : public v8::ScriptCompiler::ExternalSourceStream {
587 public:
588 DummySourceStream(Isolate* isolate, Local<String> source) : done_(false) {
589 source_length_ = source->Length();
590 source_buffer_ = std::make_unique<uint16_t[]>(source_length_);
591 source->WriteV2(isolate, 0, source_length_, source_buffer_.get());
592 }
593
594 size_t GetMoreData(const uint8_t** src) override {
595 if (done_) {
596 return 0;
597 }
598 *src = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(source_buffer_.release());
599 done_ = true;
600
601 return source_length_ * 2;
602 }
603
604 private:
605 uint32_t source_length_;
606 std::unique_ptr<uint16_t[]> source_buffer_;
607 bool done_;
608};

610// Run a ScriptStreamingTask in a separate thread.
611class StreamerThread : public v8::base::Thread {
612 public:
613 static void StartThreadForTaskAndJoin(
614 v8::ScriptCompiler::ScriptStreamingTask* task) {
615 StreamerThread thread(task);
616 CHECK(thread.Start());
617 thread.Join();
618 }
619
620 explicit StreamerThread(v8::ScriptCompiler::ScriptStreamingTask* task)
621 : Thread(Thread::Options()), task_(task) {}
622
623 void Run() override { task_->Run(); }
624
625 private:
626 v8::ScriptCompiler::ScriptStreamingTask* task_;
627};

662}

664template <>
665MaybeLocal<Module> Compile(Local<Context> context,
666 ScriptCompiler::Source* source,
667 ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions options) {
668 return ScriptCompiler::CompileModule(context->GetIsolate(), source, options);
669}
670
671} // namespace
672
673template <class T>
674MaybeLocal<T> Shell::CompileString(Isolate* isolate, Local<Context> context,
675 Local<String> source,
676 const ScriptOrigin& origin) {
677 if (options.streaming_compile) {
678 v8::ScriptCompiler::StreamedSource streamed_source(
679 std::make_unique<DummySourceStream>(isolate, source),
680 v8::ScriptCompiler::StreamedSource::TWO_BYTE);
681 std::unique_ptr<v8::ScriptCompiler::ScriptStreamingTask> streaming_task(
682 v8::ScriptCompiler::StartStreaming(isolate, &streamed_source,
683 std::is_same_v<T, Module>
684 ? v8::ScriptType::kModule
685 : v8::ScriptType::kClassic));
686 StreamerThread::StartThreadForTaskAndJoin(streaming_task.get());
687 return CompileStreamed<T>(context, &streamed_source, source, origin);
688 }
689
690 ScriptCompiler::CachedData* cached_code = nullptr;
691 if (options.compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache) {
692 cached_code = LookupCodeCache(isolate, source);
693 }
694 ScriptCompiler::Source script_source(source, origin, cached_code);
695 MaybeLocal<T> result =
696 Compile<T>(context, &script_source,
697 cached_code ? ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache
698 : ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions);
699 if (cached_code) CHECK(!cached_code->rejected);
700 return result;
701}
702
703namespace {
704// For testing.
705const int kHostDefinedOptionsLength = 2;
706const uint32_t kHostDefinedOptionsMagicConstant = 0xF1F2F3F0;
707
708const char kDataURLPrefix[] = "data:text/javascript,";
709
710std::string ToSTLString(Isolate* isolate, Local<String> v8_str) {
711 String::Utf8Value utf8(isolate, v8_str);
712 // Should not be able to fail since the input is a String.
713 CHECK(*utf8);
714 return *utf8;
715}
716
717// Per-context Module data, allowing sharing of module maps
718// across top-level module loads.
719class ModuleEmbedderData {
720 private:
721 class ModuleGlobalHash {
722 public:
723 explicit ModuleGlobalHash(Isolate* isolate) : isolate_(isolate) {}
724 size_t operator()(const Global<Module>& module) const {
725 return module.Get(isolate_)->GetIdentityHash();
726 }
727
728 private:
729 Isolate* isolate_;
730 };
731
732 public:
733 static constexpr i::ExternalPointerTag kManagedTag =
734 i::kD8ModuleEmbedderDataTag;
735
736 explicit ModuleEmbedderData(Isolate* isolate)
737 : isolate_(isolate),
738 module_to_specifier_map(10, ModuleGlobalHash(isolate)),
739 json_module_to_parsed_json_map(
740 10, module_to_specifier_map.hash_function()) {}
741
742 std::string GetModuleSpecifier(Local<Module> module) {
743 Global<Module> global_module(isolate_, module);
744 auto specifier_it = module_to_specifier_map.find(global_module);
745 CHECK(specifier_it != module_to_specifier_map.end());
746 return specifier_it->second;
747 }
748
749 Local<Module> GetModule(
750 std::pair<std::string, ModuleType> module_specifier_and_type) {
751 auto module_it = module_map.find(module_specifier_and_type);
752 CHECK(module_it != module_map.end());
753 return module_it->second.Get(isolate_);
754 }
755
756 Local<Object> GetModuleSource(
757 std::pair<std::string, ModuleType> module_specifier_and_type) {
758 auto module_source_it = module_source_map.find(module_specifier_and_type);
759 CHECK(module_source_it != module_source_map.end());
760 return module_source_it->second.Get(isolate_);
761 }
762
763 Local<Value> GetJsonModuleValue(Local<Module> module) {
764 auto json_value_it =
765 json_module_to_parsed_json_map.find(Global<Module>(isolate_, module));
766 CHECK(json_value_it != json_module_to_parsed_json_map.end());
767 return json_value_it->second.Get(isolate_);
768 }
769
770 static ModuleType ModuleTypeFromImportSpecifierAndAttributes(
771 Local<Context> context, const std::string& specifier,
772 Local<FixedArray> import_attributes, bool hasPositions) {
773 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
774 const int kV8AssertionEntrySize = hasPositions ? 3 : 2;
775 for (int i = 0; i < import_attributes->Length();
776 i += kV8AssertionEntrySize) {
777 Local<String> v8_assertion_key =
778 import_attributes->Get(context, i).As<v8::String>();
779 std::string assertion_key = ToSTLString(isolate, v8_assertion_key);
780
781 if (assertion_key == "type") {
782 Local<String> v8_assertion_value =
783 import_attributes->Get(context, i + 1).As<String>();
784 std::string assertion_value = ToSTLString(isolate, v8_assertion_value);
785 if (assertion_value == "json") {
786 return ModuleType::kJSON;
787 } else {
788 // JSON and WebAssembly are currently the only supported non-JS types
789 return ModuleType::kInvalid;
790 }
791 }
792 }
793
794 // If no type is asserted, check for the extension. Otherwise default to JS.
795 if (specifier.ends_with(".wasm")) {
796 return ModuleType::kWebAssembly;
797 }
798 return ModuleType::kJavaScript;
799 }
800
801 Isolate* isolate_;
802 // Map from (normalized module specifier, module type) pair to Module.
803 std::map<std::pair<std::string, ModuleType>, Global<Module>> module_map;
804 // Map from (normalized module specifier, module type) pair to ModuleSource.
805 std::map<std::pair<std::string, ModuleType>, Global<Object>>
806 module_source_map;
807 // Map from Module to its URL as defined in the ScriptOrigin
808 std::unordered_map<Global<Module>, std::string, ModuleGlobalHash>
809 module_to_specifier_map;
810 // Map from JSON Module to its parsed content, for use in module
811 // JSONModuleEvaluationSteps
812 std::unordered_map<Global<Module>, Global<Value>, ModuleGlobalHash>
813 json_module_to_parsed_json_map;
814
815 // Origin location used for resolving modules when referrer is null.
816 std::string origin;
817};
818
819enum { kModuleEmbedderDataIndex, kInspectorClientIndex };
820
821std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> InitializeModuleEmbedderData(
822 Local<Context> context) {
823 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
824 const size_t kModuleEmbedderDataEstimate = 4 * 1024; // module map.
825 i::DirectHandle<i::Managed<ModuleEmbedderData>> module_data_managed =
826 i::Managed<ModuleEmbedderData>::From(
827 i_isolate, kModuleEmbedderDataEstimate,
828 std::make_shared<ModuleEmbedderData>(context->GetIsolate()));
829 v8::Local<v8::Value> module_data = Utils::ToLocal(module_data_managed);
830 context->SetEmbedderData(kModuleEmbedderDataIndex, module_data);
831 return module_data_managed->get();
832}
833
834std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> GetModuleDataFromContext(
835 Local<Context> context) {
836 v8::Local<v8::Value> module_data =
837 context->GetEmbedderData(kModuleEmbedderDataIndex);
838 i::DirectHandle<i::Managed<ModuleEmbedderData>> module_data_managed =
839 i::Cast<i::Managed<ModuleEmbedderData>>(
840 Utils::OpenDirectHandle<Value, i::Object>(module_data));
841 return module_data_managed->get();
842}
843
844ScriptOrigin CreateScriptOrigin(Isolate* isolate, Local<String> resource_name,
845 v8::ScriptType type) {
846 Local<PrimitiveArray> options =
847 PrimitiveArray::New(isolate, kHostDefinedOptionsLength);
848 options->Set(isolate, 0,
849 v8::Uint32::New(isolate, kHostDefinedOptionsMagicConstant));
850 options->Set(isolate, 1, resource_name);
851 return ScriptOrigin(resource_name, 0, 0, false, -1, Local<Value>(), false,
852 false, type == v8::ScriptType::kModule, options);
853}
854
855bool IsValidHostDefinedOptions(Local<Context> context, Local<Data> options,
856 Local<Value> resource_name) {
857 if (!options->IsFixedArray()) return false;
858 Local<FixedArray> array = options.As<FixedArray>();
859 if (array->Length() != kHostDefinedOptionsLength) return false;
860 uint32_t magic = 0;
861 if (!array->Get(context, 0).As<Value>()->Uint32Value(context).To(&magic)) {
862 return false;
863 }
864 if (magic != kHostDefinedOptionsMagicConstant) return false;
865 return array->Get(context, 1).As<String>()->StrictEquals(resource_name);
866}
867
868class D8WasmAsyncResolvePromiseTask : public v8::Task {
869 public:
870 D8WasmAsyncResolvePromiseTask(v8::Isolate* isolate,
871 v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
872 v8::Local<v8::Promise::Resolver> resolver,
873 v8::Local<v8::Value> result,
874 WasmAsyncSuccess success)
875 : isolate_(isolate),
876 context_(isolate, context),
877 resolver_(isolate, resolver),
878 result_(isolate, result),
879 success_(success) {}
880
881 void Run() override {
882 v8::HandleScope scope(isolate_);
883 v8::Local<v8::Context> context = context_.Get(isolate_);
884 v8::Context::Scope context_scope(context);
885 MicrotasksScope microtasks_scope(context,
886 MicrotasksScope::kDoNotRunMicrotasks);
887 v8::Local<v8::Promise::Resolver> resolver = resolver_.Get(isolate_);
888 v8::Local<v8::Value> result = result_.Get(isolate_);
889
890 Maybe<bool> ret = success_ == WasmAsyncSuccess::kSuccess
891 ? resolver->Resolve(context, result)
892 : resolver->Reject(context, result);
893 // It's guaranteed that no exceptions will be thrown by these
894 // operations, but execution might be terminating.
895 CHECK(ret.IsJust() ? ret.FromJust() : isolate_->IsExecutionTerminating());
896 }
897
898 private:
899 v8::Isolate* isolate_;
900 v8::Global<v8::Context> context_;
901 v8::Global<v8::Promise::Resolver> resolver_;
902 v8::Global<v8::Value> result_;
903 WasmAsyncSuccess success_;
904};
905
906void D8WasmAsyncResolvePromiseCallback(
907 v8::Isolate* isolate, v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
908 v8::Local<v8::Promise::Resolver> resolver, v8::Local<v8::Value> result,
909 WasmAsyncSuccess success) {
910 // We have to resolve the promise in a separate task which is not a cancelable
911 // task, to avoid a deadlock when {quit()} is called in the then-handler of
912 // the result promise.
913 g_platform->GetForegroundTaskRunner(isolate)->PostTask(
914 std::make_unique<D8WasmAsyncResolvePromiseTask>(
915 isolate, context, resolver, result, success));
916}
917
918} // namespace
919
920// Executes a string within the current v8 context.
921bool Shell::ExecuteString(Isolate* isolate, Local<String> source,
922 Local<String> name,
923 ReportExceptions report_exceptions,
924 Global<Value>* out_result) {
925 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
926 if (i_isolate->is_execution_terminating()) return true;
927 if (i::v8_flags.parse_only) {
928 i::VMState<PARSER> state(i_isolate);
929 i::Handle<i::String> str = Utils::OpenHandle(*(source));
930
931 // Set up ParseInfo.
932 i::UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
933 i::ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(i_isolate);
934
935 i::UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags =
936 i::UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForToplevelCompile(
937 i_isolate, true, i::construct_language_mode(i::v8_flags.use_strict),
938 i::REPLMode::kNo, ScriptType::kClassic, i::v8_flags.lazy);
939
940 if (options.compile_options & v8::ScriptCompiler::kEagerCompile) {
941 flags.set_is_eager(true);
942 }
943
944 i::ParseInfo parse_info(i_isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
945
946 i::Handle<i::Script> script = parse_info.CreateScript(
947 i_isolate, str, i::kNullMaybeHandle, ScriptOriginOptions());
948 if (!i::parsing::ParseProgram(&parse_info, script, i_isolate,
949 i::parsing::ReportStatisticsMode::kYes)) {
950 parse_info.pending_error_handler()->PrepareErrors(
951 i_isolate, parse_info.ast_value_factory());
952 parse_info.pending_error_handler()->ReportErrors(i_isolate, script);
953
954 fprintf(stderr, "Failed parsing\n");
955 return false;
956 }
957 return true;
958 }
959
960 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
961 TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
962 try_catch.SetVerbose(report_exceptions == kReportExceptions);
963
964 // Explicitly check for stack overflows. This method can be called
965 // recursively, and since we consume quite some stack space for the C++
966 // frames, the stack check in the called frame might be too late.
967 if (i::StackLimitCheck{i_isolate}.HasOverflowed()) {
968 i_isolate->StackOverflow();
969 return false;
970 }
971
972 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
973 Local<Context> realm =
974 Local<Context>::New(isolate, data->realms_[data->realm_current_]);
975 Context::Scope context_scope(realm);
976 Local<Context> context(isolate->GetCurrentContext());
977 ScriptOrigin origin = CreateScriptOrigin(isolate, name, ScriptType::kClassic);
978
979 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> module_data =
980 GetModuleDataFromContext(realm);
981 module_data->origin = ToSTLString(isolate, name);
982
983 for (int i = 1; i < options.repeat_compile; ++i) {
984 HandleScope handle_scope_for_compiling(isolate);
985 if (CompileString<Script>(isolate, context, source, origin).IsEmpty()) {
986 return false;
987 }
988 }
989 Local<Script> script;
990 if (!CompileString<Script>(isolate, context, source, origin)
991 .ToLocal(&script)) {
992 return false;
993 }
994
995 if (options.code_cache_options ==
996 ShellOptions::CodeCacheOptions::kProduceCache) {
997 // Serialize and store it in memory for the next execution.
998 ScriptCompiler::CachedData* cached_data =
999 ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCache(script->GetUnboundScript());
1000 StoreInCodeCache(isolate, source, cached_data);
1001 delete cached_data;
1002 }
1003 if (options.compile_only) return true;
1004 if (options.compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache) {
1005 i::DirectHandle<i::Script> i_script(
1006 i::Cast<i::Script>(
1007 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*script)->shared()->script()),
1008 i_isolate);
1009 // TODO(cbruni, chromium:1244145): remove once context-allocated.
1010 i_script->set_host_defined_options(i::Cast<i::FixedArray>(
1011 *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*(origin.GetHostDefinedOptions()))));
1012 }
1013
1014 MaybeLocal<Value> maybe_result = script->Run(realm);
1015
1016 if (options.code_cache_options ==
1017 ShellOptions::CodeCacheOptions::kProduceCacheAfterExecute) {
1018 // Serialize and store it in memory for the next execution.
1019 ScriptCompiler::CachedData* cached_data =
1020 ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCache(script->GetUnboundScript());
1021 StoreInCodeCache(isolate, source, cached_data);
1022 delete cached_data;
1023 }
1024 data->realm_current_ = data->realm_switch_;
1025
1026 Local<Value> result;
1027 if (!maybe_result.ToLocal(&result)) {
1028 if (try_catch.HasTerminated()) return true;
1029 DCHECK(try_catch.HasCaught());
1030 return false;
1031 } else if (out_result != nullptr) {
1032 out_result->Reset(isolate, result);
1033 }
1034
1035 // It's possible that a FinalizationRegistry cleanup task threw an error.
1036 return !try_catch.HasCaught();
1037}
1038
1039namespace {
1040
1041bool IsAbsolutePath(const std::string& path) {
1042#if defined(V8_OS_WIN)
1043 // This is an incorrect approximation, but should
1044 // work for all our test-running cases.
1045 return path.find(':') != std::string::npos;
1046#else
1047 return path[0] == '/';
1048#endif
1049}
1050
1051std::string GetWorkingDirectory() {
1052#if defined(V8_OS_WIN)
1053 char system_buffer[MAX_PATH];
1054 // Unicode paths are unsupported, which is fine as long as
1055 // the test directory doesn't include any such paths.
1056 DWORD len = GetCurrentDirectoryA(MAX_PATH, system_buffer);
1057 CHECK_GT(len, 0);
1058 return system_buffer;
1059#else
1060 char curdir[PATH_MAX];
1061 CHECK_NOT_NULL(getcwd(curdir, PATH_MAX));
1062 return curdir;
1063#endif
1064}
1065
1066// Returns the directory part of path, without the trailing '/'.
1067std::string DirName(const std::string& path) {
1068 DCHECK(IsAbsolutePath(path));
1069 size_t last_slash = path.find_last_of('/');
1070 DCHECK(last_slash != std::string::npos);
1071 return path.substr(0, last_slash);
1072}
1073
1074// Resolves path to an absolute path if necessary, and does some
1075// normalization (eliding references to the current directory
1076// and replacing backslashes with slashes).
1077std::string NormalizePath(const std::string& path,
1078 const std::string& dir_name) {
1079 std::string absolute_path;
1080 if (IsAbsolutePath(path)) {
1081 absolute_path = path;
1082 } else {
1083 absolute_path = dir_name + '/' + path;
1084 }
1085 std::replace(absolute_path.begin(), absolute_path.end(), '\\', '/');
1086 std::vector<std::string> segments;
1087 std::istringstream segment_stream(absolute_path);
1088 std::string segment;
1089 while (std::getline(segment_stream, segment, '/')) {
1090 if (segment == "..") {
1091 if (!segments.empty()) segments.pop_back();
1092 } else if (segment != ".") {
1093 segments.push_back(segment);
1094 }
1095 }
1096 // Join path segments.
1097 std::ostringstream os;
1098 if (segments.size() > 1) {
1099 std::copy(segments.begin(), segments.end() - 1,
1100 std::ostream_iterator<std::string>(os, "/"));
1101 os << *segments.rbegin();
1102 } else {
1103 os << "/";
1104 if (!segments.empty()) os << segments[0];
1105 }
1106 return os.str();
1107}
1108
1109// Resolves specifier to an absolute path if necessary, and does some
1110// normalization (eliding references to the current directory
1111// and replacing backslashes with slashes).
1112//
1113// If specifier is a data url, returns it unchanged.
1114std::string NormalizeModuleSpecifier(const std::string& specifier,
1115 const std::string& dir_name) {
1116 if (specifier.starts_with(kDataURLPrefix)) return specifier;
1117 return NormalizePath(specifier, dir_name);
1118}
1119
1120MaybeLocal<Module> ResolveModuleCallback(Local<Context> context,
1121 Local<String> specifier,
1122 Local<FixedArray> import_attributes,
1123 Local<Module> referrer) {
1124 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
1125 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> module_data =
1126 GetModuleDataFromContext(context);
1127 std::string referrer_specifier = module_data->GetModuleSpecifier(referrer);
1128
1129 std::string stl_specifier = ToSTLString(isolate, specifier);
1130 std::string absolute_path =
1131 NormalizeModuleSpecifier(stl_specifier, DirName(referrer_specifier));
1132 ModuleType module_type =
1133 ModuleEmbedderData::ModuleTypeFromImportSpecifierAndAttributes(
1134 context, stl_specifier, import_attributes, true);
1135 return module_data->GetModule(std::make_pair(absolute_path, module_type));
1136}
1137
1138MaybeLocal<Object> ResolveModuleSourceCallback(
1139 Local<Context> context, Local<String> specifier,
1140 Local<FixedArray> import_attributes, Local<Module> referrer) {
1141 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
1142 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> module_data =
1143 GetModuleDataFromContext(context);
1144 std::string referrer_specifier = module_data->GetModuleSpecifier(referrer);
1145
1146 std::string stl_specifier = ToSTLString(isolate, specifier);
1147 std::string absolute_path =
1148 NormalizeModuleSpecifier(stl_specifier, DirName(referrer_specifier));
1149 ModuleType module_type =
1150 ModuleEmbedderData::ModuleTypeFromImportSpecifierAndAttributes(
1151 context, stl_specifier, import_attributes, true);
1152
1153 return module_data->GetModuleSource(
1154 std::make_pair(absolute_path, module_type));
1155}
1156
1157} // anonymous namespace
1158
1159MaybeLocal<Object> Shell::FetchModuleSource(Local<Module> referrer,
1160 Local<Context> context,
1161 const std::string& module_specifier,
1162 ModuleType module_type) {
1163 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
1164 DCHECK(IsAbsolutePath(module_specifier));
1165 auto file = ReadFileData(isolate, module_specifier.c_str());
1166
1167 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> module_data =
1168 GetModuleDataFromContext(context);
1169 if (!file) {
1170 std::string msg = "d8: Error reading module from " + module_specifier;
1171 if (!referrer.IsEmpty()) {
1172 std::string referrer_specifier =
1173 module_data->GetModuleSpecifier(referrer);
1174 msg += "\n imported by " + referrer_specifier;
1175 }
1176 ThrowError(isolate,
1177 v8::String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, msg.c_str()).ToLocalChecked());
1178 return MaybeLocal<Object>();
1179 }
1180
1181 Local<Object> module_source;
1182 switch (module_type) {
1183 case ModuleType::kWebAssembly: {
1184 if (!v8::WasmModuleObject::Compile(
1185 isolate,
1186 MemorySpan<const uint8_t>(static_cast<uint8_t*>(file->memory()),
1187 file->size()))
1188 .ToLocal(&module_source)) {
1189 return MaybeLocal<Object>();
1190 }
1191 break;
1192 }
1193 default:
1194 // https://tc39.es/proposal-source-phase-imports/#table-abstract-methods-of-module-records
1195 // For Module Records that do not have a source representation,
1196 // GetModuleSource() must always return a throw completion whose [[Value]]
1197 // is a ReferenceError.
1198 ThrowException(
1199 isolate, v8::Exception::SyntaxError(String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
1200 isolate, "Module source can not be imported for type")));
1201 return MaybeLocal<Object>();
1202 }
1203
1204 CHECK(
1205 module_data->module_source_map
1206 .insert(std::make_pair(std::make_pair(module_specifier, module_type),
1207 Global<Object>(isolate, module_source)))
1208 .second);
1209 return module_source;
1210}
1211
1212// file_name must be either an absolute path to the filesystem or a data URL.
1213MaybeLocal<Module> Shell::FetchModuleTree(Local<Module> referrer,
1214 Local<Context> context,
1215 const std::string& module_specifier,
1216 ModuleType module_type) {
1217 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
1218 const bool is_data_url = module_specifier.starts_with(kDataURLPrefix);
1219 MaybeLocal<String> source_text;
1220 if (is_data_url) {
1221 source_text = String::NewFromUtf8(
1222 isolate, module_specifier.c_str() + strlen(kDataURLPrefix));
1223 } else {
1224 DCHECK(IsAbsolutePath(module_specifier));
1225 source_text = ReadFile(isolate, module_specifier.c_str(), false);
1226 if (source_text.IsEmpty() && options.fuzzy_module_file_extensions) {
1227 std::string fallback_file_name = module_specifier + ".js";
1228 source_text = ReadFile(isolate, fallback_file_name.c_str(), false);
1229 if (source_text.IsEmpty()) {
1230 fallback_file_name = module_specifier + ".mjs";
1231 source_text = ReadFile(isolate, fallback_file_name.c_str());
1232 }
1233 }
1234 }
1235
1236 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> module_data =
1237 GetModuleDataFromContext(context);
1238 if (source_text.IsEmpty()) {
1239 std::string msg = "d8: Error reading module from " + module_specifier;
1240 if (!referrer.IsEmpty()) {
1241 std::string referrer_specifier =
1242 module_data->GetModuleSpecifier(referrer);
1243 msg += "\n imported by " + referrer_specifier;
1244 }
1245 ThrowError(isolate,
1246 v8::String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, msg.c_str()).ToLocalChecked());
1247 return MaybeLocal<Module>();
1248 }
1249
1250 Local<String> resource_name =
1251 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, module_specifier.c_str()).ToLocalChecked();
1252 ScriptOrigin origin =
1253 CreateScriptOrigin(isolate, resource_name, ScriptType::kModule);
1254
1255 Local<Module> module;
1256 if (module_type == ModuleType::kJavaScript) {
1257 ScriptCompiler::Source source(source_text.ToLocalChecked(), origin);
1258 if (!CompileString<Module>(isolate, context, source_text.ToLocalChecked(),
1259 origin)
1260 .ToLocal(&module)) {
1261 return MaybeLocal<Module>();
1262 }
1263 } else if (module_type == ModuleType::kJSON) {
1264 Local<Value> parsed_json;
1265 if (!v8::JSON::Parse(context, source_text.ToLocalChecked())
1266 .ToLocal(&parsed_json)) {
1267 return MaybeLocal<Module>();
1268 }
1269
1270 auto export_names = v8::to_array<Local<String>>(
1271 {String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, "default").ToLocalChecked()});
1272
1273 module = v8::Module::CreateSyntheticModule(
1274 isolate,
1275 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, module_specifier.c_str()).ToLocalChecked(),
1276 export_names, Shell::JSONModuleEvaluationSteps);
1277
1278 CHECK(module_data->json_module_to_parsed_json_map
1279 .insert(std::make_pair(Global<Module>(isolate, module),
1280 Global<Value>(isolate, parsed_json)))
1281 .second);
1282 } else {
1283 UNREACHABLE();
1284 }
1285
1286 CHECK(
1287 module_data->module_map
1288 .insert(std::make_pair(std::make_pair(module_specifier, module_type),
1289 Global<Module>(isolate, module)))
1290 .second);
1291 CHECK(module_data->module_to_specifier_map
1292 .insert(std::make_pair(Global<Module>(isolate, module),
1293 module_specifier))
1294 .second);
1295
1296 // data URLs don't support further imports, so we're done.
1297 if (is_data_url) return module;
1298
1299 std::string dir_name = DirName(module_specifier);
1300
1301 Local<FixedArray> module_requests = module->GetModuleRequests();
1302 for (int i = 0, length = module_requests->Length(); i < length; ++i) {
1303 Local<ModuleRequest> module_request =
1304 module_requests->Get(context, i).As<ModuleRequest>();
1305 std::string specifier =
1306 ToSTLString(isolate, module_request->GetSpecifier());
1307 std::string normalized_specifier =
1308 NormalizeModuleSpecifier(specifier, dir_name);
1309 Local<FixedArray> import_attributes = module_request->GetImportAttributes();
1310 ModuleType request_module_type =
1311 ModuleEmbedderData::ModuleTypeFromImportSpecifierAndAttributes(
1312 context, normalized_specifier, import_attributes, true);
1313
1314 if (request_module_type == ModuleType::kInvalid) {
1315 ThrowError(isolate, "Invalid module type was asserted");
1316 return MaybeLocal<Module>();
1317 }
1318
1319 if (module_request->GetPhase() == ModuleImportPhase::kSource) {
1320 if (module_data->module_source_map.count(
1321 std::make_pair(normalized_specifier, request_module_type))) {
1322 continue;
1323 }
1324
1325 if (FetchModuleSource(module, context, normalized_specifier,
1326 request_module_type)
1327 .IsEmpty()) {
1328 return MaybeLocal<Module>();
1329 }
1330 } else {
1331 if (module_data->module_map.count(
1332 std::make_pair(normalized_specifier, request_module_type))) {
1333 continue;
1334 }
1335
1336 if (FetchModuleTree(module, context, normalized_specifier,
1337 request_module_type)
1338 .IsEmpty()) {
1339 return MaybeLocal<Module>();
1340 }
1341 }
1342 }
1343
1344 return module;
1345}
1346
1347MaybeLocal<Value> Shell::JSONModuleEvaluationSteps(Local<Context> context,
1348 Local<Module> module) {
1349 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
1350
1351 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> module_data =
1352 GetModuleDataFromContext(context);
1353 Local<Value> json_value = module_data->GetJsonModuleValue(module);
1354
1355 TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
1356 Maybe<bool> result = module->SetSyntheticModuleExport(
1357 isolate,
1358 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "default",
1359 NewStringType::kInternalized),
1360 json_value);
1361
1362 // Setting the default export should never fail.
1363 CHECK(!try_catch.HasCaught());
1364 CHECK(!result.IsNothing() && result.FromJust());
1365
1366 Local<Promise::Resolver> resolver =
1367 Promise::Resolver::New(context).ToLocalChecked();
1368 resolver->Resolve(context, Undefined(isolate)).ToChecked();
1369 return resolver->GetPromise();
1370}
1371
1372struct DynamicImportData {
1373 DynamicImportData(Isolate* isolate_, Local<Context> context_,
1374 Local<Value> referrer_, Local<String> specifier_,
1375 ModuleImportPhase phase_,
1376 Local<FixedArray> import_attributes_,
1377 Local<Promise::Resolver> resolver_)
1378 : isolate(isolate_), phase(phase_) {
1379 context.Reset(isolate, context_);
1380 referrer.Reset(isolate, referrer_);
1381 specifier.Reset(isolate, specifier_);
1382 import_attributes.Reset(isolate, import_attributes_);
1383 resolver.Reset(isolate, resolver_);
1384 }
1385
1386 Isolate* isolate;
1387 // The initiating context. It can be the Realm created by d8, or the context
1388 // created by ShadowRealm built-in.
1389 Global<Context> context;
1390 Global<Value> referrer;
1391 Global<String> specifier;
1392 ModuleImportPhase phase;
1393 Global<FixedArray> import_attributes;
1394 Global<Promise::Resolver> resolver;
1395};
1396
1397namespace {
1398
1399enum ModuleResolutionDataIndex : uint32_t {
1400 kResolver = 0,
1401 kNamespaceOrSource = 1,
1402};
1403
1404} // namespace
1405
1406void Shell::ModuleResolutionSuccessCallback(
1407 const FunctionCallbackInfo<Value>& info) {
1408 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
1409 Isolate* isolate(info.GetIsolate());
1410 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
1411 Local<Array> module_resolution_data(info.Data().As<Array>());
1412 Local<Context> context(isolate->GetCurrentContext());
1413
1414 Local<Promise::Resolver> resolver(
1415 module_resolution_data->Get(context, ModuleResolutionDataIndex::kResolver)
1416 .ToLocalChecked()
1417 .As<Promise::Resolver>());
1418 Local<Value> namespace_or_source(
1419 module_resolution_data
1420 ->Get(context, ModuleResolutionDataIndex::kNamespaceOrSource)
1421 .ToLocalChecked());
1422
1423 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
1424 Local<Context> realm = data->realms_[data->realm_current_].Get(isolate);
1425 Context::Scope context_scope(realm);
1426
1427 resolver->Resolve(realm, namespace_or_source).ToChecked();
1428}
1429
1430void Shell::ModuleResolutionFailureCallback(
1431 const FunctionCallbackInfo<Value>& info) {
1432 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
1433 Isolate* isolate(info.GetIsolate());
1434 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
1435 Local<Array> module_resolution_data(info.Data().As<Array>());
1436 Local<Context> context(isolate->GetCurrentContext());
1437
1438 Local<Promise::Resolver> resolver(
1439 module_resolution_data->Get(context, ModuleResolutionDataIndex::kResolver)
1440 .ToLocalChecked()
1441 .As<Promise::Resolver>());
1442
1443 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
1444 Local<Context> realm = data->realms_[data->realm_current_].Get(isolate);
1445 Context::Scope context_scope(realm);
1446
1447 DCHECK_EQ(info.Length(), 1);
1448 resolver->Reject(realm, info[0]).ToChecked();
1449}
1450
1451MaybeLocal<Promise> Shell::HostImportModuleDynamically(
1452 Local<Context> context, Local<Data> host_defined_options,
1453 Local<Value> resource_name, Local<String> specifier,
1454 Local<FixedArray> import_attributes) {
1455 return HostImportModuleWithPhaseDynamically(
1456 context, host_defined_options, resource_name, specifier,
1457 ModuleImportPhase::kEvaluation, import_attributes);
1458}
1459
1460MaybeLocal<Promise> Shell::HostImportModuleWithPhaseDynamically(
1461 Local<Context> context, Local<Data> host_defined_options,
1462 Local<Value> resource_name, Local<String> specifier,
1463 ModuleImportPhase phase, Local<FixedArray> import_attributes) {
1464 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
1465
1466 MaybeLocal<Promise::Resolver> maybe_resolver =
1467 Promise::Resolver::New(context);
1468 Local<Promise::Resolver> resolver;
1469 if (!maybe_resolver.ToLocal(&resolver)) return MaybeLocal<Promise>();
1470
1471 if (!resource_name->IsNull() &&
1472 !IsValidHostDefinedOptions(context, host_defined_options,
1473 resource_name)) {
1474 resolver
1475 ->Reject(context, v8::Exception::TypeError(String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
1476 isolate, "Invalid host defined options")))
1477 .ToChecked();
1478 } else {
1479 DynamicImportData* data =
1480 new DynamicImportData(isolate, context, resource_name, specifier, phase,
1481 import_attributes, resolver);
1482 PerIsolateData::Get(isolate)->AddDynamicImportData(data);
1483 isolate->EnqueueMicrotask(Shell::DoHostImportModuleDynamically, data);
1484 }
1485 return resolver->GetPromise();
1486}
1487
1488void Shell::HostInitializeImportMetaObject(Local<Context> context,
1489 Local<Module> module,
1490 Local<Object> meta) {
1491 Isolate* isolate = context->GetIsolate();
1492 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
1493
1494 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> module_data =
1495 GetModuleDataFromContext(context);
1496 std::string specifier = module_data->GetModuleSpecifier(module);
1497
1498 Local<String> url_key =
1499 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "url", NewStringType::kInternalized);
1500 Local<String> url =
1501 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, specifier.c_str()).ToLocalChecked();
1502 meta->CreateDataProperty(context, url_key, url).ToChecked();
1503}
1504
1505MaybeLocal<Context> Shell::HostCreateShadowRealmContext(
1506 Local<Context> initiator_context) {
1507 Local<Context> context = v8::Context::New(initiator_context->GetIsolate());
1508 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> shadow_realm_data =
1509 InitializeModuleEmbedderData(context);
1510 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> initiator_data =
1511 GetModuleDataFromContext(initiator_context);
1512
1513 // ShadowRealms are synchronously accessible and are always in the same origin
1514 // as the initiator context.
1515 context->SetSecurityToken(initiator_context->GetSecurityToken());
1516 shadow_realm_data->origin = initiator_data->origin;
1517
1518 return context;
1519}
1520
1521void Shell::DoHostImportModuleDynamically(void* import_data) {
1522 DynamicImportData* import_data_ =
1523 static_cast<DynamicImportData*>(import_data);
1524
1525 Isolate* isolate(import_data_->isolate);
1526 Global<Context> global_realm;
1527 Global<Promise::Resolver> global_resolver;
1528 Global<Promise> global_result_promise;
1529 Global<Value> global_namespace_or_source;
1530
1531 TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
1532 try_catch.SetVerbose(true);
1533
1534 {
1535 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
1536 Local<Context> realm = import_data_->context.Get(isolate);
1537 Local<Value> referrer = import_data_->referrer.Get(isolate);
1538 Local<String> v8_specifier = import_data_->specifier.Get(isolate);
1539 ModuleImportPhase phase = import_data_->phase;
1540 Local<FixedArray> import_attributes =
1541 import_data_->import_attributes.Get(isolate);
1542 Local<Promise::Resolver> resolver = import_data_->resolver.Get(isolate);
1543
1544 global_realm.Reset(isolate, realm);
1545 global_resolver.Reset(isolate, resolver);
1546
1547 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
1548 data->DeleteDynamicImportData(import_data_);
1549
1550 Context::Scope context_scope(realm);
1551 std::string specifier = ToSTLString(isolate, v8_specifier);
1552
1553 ModuleType module_type =
1554 ModuleEmbedderData::ModuleTypeFromImportSpecifierAndAttributes(
1555 realm, specifier, import_attributes, false);
1556
1557 if (module_type == ModuleType::kInvalid) {
1558 ThrowError(isolate, "Invalid module type was asserted");
1559 CHECK(try_catch.HasCaught());
1560 resolver->Reject(realm, try_catch.Exception()).ToChecked();
1561 return;
1562 }
1563
1564 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> module_data =
1565 GetModuleDataFromContext(realm);
1566
1567 std::string source_url = referrer->IsNull()
1568 ? module_data->origin
1569 : ToSTLString(isolate, referrer.As<String>());
1570 std::string dir_name =
1571 DirName(NormalizePath(source_url, GetWorkingDirectory()));
1572 std::string absolute_path = NormalizeModuleSpecifier(specifier, dir_name);
1573
1574 switch (phase) {
1575 case ModuleImportPhase::kSource: {
1576 Local<Object> module_source;
1577 auto module_it = module_data->module_source_map.find(
1578 std::make_pair(absolute_path, module_type));
1579 if (module_it != module_data->module_source_map.end()) {
1580 module_source = module_it->second.Get(isolate);
1581 } else if (!FetchModuleSource(Local<Module>(), realm, absolute_path,
1582 module_type)
1583 .ToLocal(&module_source)) {
1584 CHECK(try_catch.HasCaught());
1585 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) {
1586 Shell::ReportException(isolate, try_catch);
1587 } else {
1588 resolver->Reject(realm, try_catch.Exception()).ToChecked();
1589 }
1590 return;
1591 }
1592 Local<Promise::Resolver> module_resolver =
1593 Promise::Resolver::New(realm).ToLocalChecked();
1594 module_resolver->Resolve(realm, module_source).ToChecked();
1595
1596 global_namespace_or_source.Reset(isolate, module_source);
1597 global_result_promise.Reset(isolate, module_resolver->GetPromise());
1598 break;
1599 }
1600 case v8::ModuleImportPhase::kEvaluation: {
1601 Local<Module> root_module;
1602 auto module_it = module_data->module_map.find(
1603 std::make_pair(absolute_path, module_type));
1604 if (module_it != module_data->module_map.end()) {
1605 root_module = module_it->second.Get(isolate);
1606 } else if (!FetchModuleTree(Local<Module>(), realm, absolute_path,
1607 module_type)
1608 .ToLocal(&root_module)) {
1609 CHECK(try_catch.HasCaught());
1610 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) {
1611 Shell::ReportException(isolate, try_catch);
1612 } else {
1613 resolver->Reject(realm, try_catch.Exception()).ToChecked();
1614 }
1615 return;
1616 }
1617
1618 if (root_module
1619 ->InstantiateModule(realm, ResolveModuleCallback,
1620 ResolveModuleSourceCallback)
1621 .FromMaybe(false)) {
1622 MaybeLocal<Value> maybe_result = root_module->Evaluate(realm);
1623 CHECK(!maybe_result.IsEmpty());
1624 global_result_promise.Reset(
1625 isolate, maybe_result.ToLocalChecked().As<Promise>());
1626 global_namespace_or_source.Reset(isolate,
1627 root_module->GetModuleNamespace());
1628 }
1629 break;
1630 }
1631 default: {
1632 UNREACHABLE();
1633 }
1634 }
1635 }
1636
1637 if (global_result_promise.IsEmpty()) {
1638 DCHECK(try_catch.HasCaught());
1639 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
1640 Local<Context> realm = global_realm.Get(isolate);
1641 Local<Promise::Resolver> resolver = global_resolver.Get(isolate);
1642 resolver->Reject(realm, try_catch.Exception()).ToChecked();
1643 return;
1644 }
1645
1646 {
1647 // This method is invoked from a microtask, where in general we may have
1648 // an non-trivial stack. Emptying the message queue below may trigger the
1649 // execution of a stackless GC. We need to override the embedder stack
1650 // state, to force scanning the stack, if this happens.
1651 i::Heap* heap = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)->heap();
1652 i::EmbedderStackStateScope scope(
1653 heap, i::EmbedderStackStateOrigin::kExplicitInvocation,
1654 StackState::kMayContainHeapPointers);
1655 EmptyMessageQueues(isolate);
1656 }
1657
1658 // Setup callbacks, and then chain them to the result promise.
1659 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
1660 Local<Context> realm = global_realm.Get(isolate);
1661 Local<Promise::Resolver> resolver = global_resolver.Get(isolate);
1662 Local<Promise> result_promise = global_result_promise.Get(isolate);
1663 Local<Value> namespace_or_source = global_namespace_or_source.Get(isolate);
1664
1665 Local<Array> module_resolution_data = v8::Array::New(isolate);
1666 module_resolution_data->SetPrototypeV2(realm, v8::Null(isolate)).ToChecked();
1667 module_resolution_data
1668 ->Set(realm, ModuleResolutionDataIndex::kResolver, resolver)
1669 .ToChecked();
1670 module_resolution_data
1671 ->Set(realm, ModuleResolutionDataIndex::kNamespaceOrSource,
1672 namespace_or_source)
1673 .ToChecked();
1674 Local<Function> callback_success;
1675 CHECK(Function::New(realm, ModuleResolutionSuccessCallback,
1676 module_resolution_data)
1677 .ToLocal(&callback_success));
1678 Local<Function> callback_failure;
1679 CHECK(Function::New(realm, ModuleResolutionFailureCallback,
1680 module_resolution_data)
1681 .ToLocal(&callback_failure));
1682 result_promise->Then(realm, callback_success, callback_failure)
1683 .ToLocalChecked();
1684}
1685
1686bool Shell::ExecuteModule(Isolate* isolate, const char* file_name) {
1687 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
1688 Global<Module> global_root_module;
1689 Global<Promise> global_result_promise;
1690
1691 // Use a non-verbose TryCatch and report exceptions manually using
1692 // Shell::ReportException, because some errors (such as file errors) are
1693 // thrown without entering JS and thus do not trigger
1694 // isolate->ReportPendingMessages().
1695 TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
1696
1697 {
1698 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
1699 Local<Context> realm = data->realms_[data->realm_current_].Get(isolate);
1700 Context::Scope context_scope(realm);
1701
1702 std::string absolute_path =
1703 NormalizeModuleSpecifier(file_name, GetWorkingDirectory());
1704
1705 std::shared_ptr<ModuleEmbedderData> module_data =
1706 GetModuleDataFromContext(realm);
1707 Local<Module> root_module;
1708 auto module_it = module_data->module_map.find(
1709 std::make_pair(absolute_path, ModuleType::kJavaScript));
1710 if (module_it != module_data->module_map.end()) {
1711 root_module = module_it->second.Get(isolate);
1712 } else if (!FetchModuleTree(Local<Module>(), realm, absolute_path,
1713 ModuleType::kJavaScript)
1714 .ToLocal(&root_module)) {
1715 CHECK(try_catch.HasCaught());
1716 ReportException(isolate, try_catch);
1717 return false;
1718 }
1719 global_root_module.Reset(isolate, root_module);
1720
1721 module_data->origin = absolute_path;
1722
1723 MaybeLocal<Value> maybe_result;
1724 if (root_module
1725 ->InstantiateModule(realm, ResolveModuleCallback,
1726 ResolveModuleSourceCallback)
1727 .FromMaybe(false)) {
1728 maybe_result = root_module->Evaluate(realm);
1729 CHECK(!maybe_result.IsEmpty());
1730 global_result_promise.Reset(isolate,
1731 maybe_result.ToLocalChecked().As<Promise>());
1732 }
1733 }
1734
1735 if (!global_result_promise.IsEmpty()) {
1736 EmptyMessageQueues(isolate);
1737 } else {
1738 DCHECK(try_catch.HasCaught());
1739 ReportException(isolate, try_catch);
1740 return false;
1741 }
1742
1743 // Loop until module execution finishes
1744 while (isolate->HasPendingBackgroundTasks() ||
1745 (i::ValueHelper::HandleAsValue(global_result_promise)->State() ==
1746 Promise::kPending &&
1747 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)
1748 ->default_microtask_queue()
1749 ->size() > 0)) {
1750 Shell::CompleteMessageLoop(isolate);
1751 }
1752
1753 {
1754 Local<Promise> result_promise = global_result_promise.Get(isolate);
1755 Local<Module> root_module = global_root_module.Get(isolate);
1756
1757 if (result_promise->State() == Promise::kRejected) {
1758 // If the exception has been caught by the promise pipeline, we rethrow
1759 // here in order to ReportException.
1760 // TODO(cbruni): Clean this up after we create a new API for the case
1761 // where TLA is enabled.
1762 if (!try_catch.HasCaught()) {
1763 isolate->ThrowException(result_promise->Result());
1764 } else {
1765 DCHECK_EQ(try_catch.Exception(), result_promise->Result());
1766 }
1767 ReportException(isolate, try_catch);
1768 return false;
1769 }
1770
1771 auto [stalled_modules, stalled_messages] =
1772 root_module->GetStalledTopLevelAwaitMessages(isolate);
1773 DCHECK_EQ(stalled_modules.size(), stalled_messages.size());
1774 if (stalled_messages.size() > 0) {
1775 Local<Message> message = stalled_messages[0];
1776 ReportException(isolate, message, v8::Exception::Error(message->Get()));
1777 return false;
1778 }
1779 }
1780
1781 DCHECK(!try_catch.HasCaught());
1782 return true;
1783}
1784
1785// Treat every line as a JSON value and parse it.
1786bool Shell::LoadJSON(Isolate* isolate, const char* file_name) {
1787 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
1788 PerIsolateData* isolate_data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
1789 Local<Context> realm =
1790 isolate_data->realms_[isolate_data->realm_current_].Get(isolate);
1791 Context::Scope context_scope(realm);
1792 TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
1793
1794 std::string absolute_path = NormalizePath(file_name, GetWorkingDirectory());
1795 int length = 0;
1796 std::unique_ptr<char[]> data(ReadChars(absolute_path.c_str(), &length));
1797 if (length == 0) {
1798 printf("Error reading '%s'\n", file_name);
1799 base::OS::ExitProcess(1);
1800 }
1801 std::stringstream stream(data.get());
1802 std::string line;
1803 while (std::getline(stream, line, '\n')) {
1804 for (int r = 0; r < DeserializationRunCount(); ++r) {
1805 Local<String> source =
1806 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, line.c_str()).ToLocalChecked();
1807 MaybeLocal<Value> maybe_value = JSON::Parse(realm, source);
1808
1809 Local<Value> value;
1810 if (!maybe_value.ToLocal(&value)) {
1811 DCHECK(try_catch.HasCaught());
1812 ReportException(isolate, try_catch);
1813 return false;
1814 }
1815 }
1816 }
1817 return true;
1818}
1819
1820PerIsolateData::PerIsolateData(Isolate* isolate)
1821 : isolate_(isolate), realms_(nullptr) {
1822 isolate->SetData(0, this);
1823 if (i::v8_flags.expose_async_hooks) {
1824 async_hooks_wrapper_ = new AsyncHooks(isolate);
1825 }
1826 ignore_unhandled_promises_ = false;
1827}
1828
1829PerIsolateData::~PerIsolateData() {
1830 isolate_->SetData(0, nullptr); // Not really needed, just to be sure...
1831 if (i::v8_flags.expose_async_hooks) {
1832 delete async_hooks_wrapper_; // This uses the isolate
1833 }
1834#if defined(LEAK_SANITIZER)
1835 for (DynamicImportData* data : import_data_) {
1836 delete data;
1837 }
1838#endif
1839}
1840
1841void PerIsolateData::RemoveUnhandledPromise(Local<Promise> promise) {
1842 if (ignore_unhandled_promises_) return;
1843 // Remove handled promises from the list
1844 DCHECK_EQ(promise->GetIsolate(), isolate_);
1845 for (auto it = unhandled_promises_.begin(); it != unhandled_promises_.end();
1846 ++it) {
1847 v8::Local<v8::Promise> unhandled_promise = std::get<0>(*it).Get(isolate_);
1848 if (unhandled_promise == promise) {
1849 unhandled_promises_.erase(it--);
1850 }
1851 }
1852}
1853
1854void PerIsolateData::AddUnhandledPromise(Local<Promise> promise,
1855 Local<Message> message,
1856 Local<Value> exception) {
1857 if (ignore_unhandled_promises_) return;
1858 DCHECK_EQ(promise->GetIsolate(), isolate_);
1859 unhandled_promises_.emplace_back(v8::Global<v8::Promise>(isolate_, promise),
1860 v8::Global<v8::Message>(isolate_, message),
1861 v8::Global<v8::Value>(isolate_, exception));
1862}
1863
1864int PerIsolateData::HandleUnhandledPromiseRejections() {
1865 // Avoid recursive calls to HandleUnhandledPromiseRejections.
1866 if (ignore_unhandled_promises_) return 0;
1867 if (isolate_->IsExecutionTerminating()) return 0;
1868 ignore_unhandled_promises_ = true;
1869 v8::HandleScope scope(isolate_);
1870 // Ignore promises that get added during error reporting.
1871 size_t i = 0;
1872 for (; i < unhandled_promises_.size(); i++) {
1873 const auto& tuple = unhandled_promises_[i];
1874 Local<v8::Message> message = std::get<1>(tuple).Get(isolate_);
1875 Local<v8::Value> value = std::get<2>(tuple).Get(isolate_);
1876 Shell::ReportException(isolate_, message, value);
1877 }
1878 unhandled_promises_.clear();
1879 ignore_unhandled_promises_ = false;
1880 return static_cast<int>(i);
1881}
1882
1883void PerIsolateData::AddDynamicImportData(DynamicImportData* data) {
1884#if defined(LEAK_SANITIZER)
1885 import_data_.insert(data);
1886#endif
1887}
1888void PerIsolateData::DeleteDynamicImportData(DynamicImportData* data) {
1889#if defined(LEAK_SANITIZER)
1890 import_data_.erase(data);
1891#endif
1892 delete data;
1893}
1894
1895Local<FunctionTemplate> PerIsolateData::GetTestApiObjectCtor() const {
1896 return test_api_object_ctor_.Get(isolate_);
1897}
1898
1899void PerIsolateData::SetTestApiObjectCtor(Local<FunctionTemplate> ctor) {
1900 test_api_object_ctor_.Reset(isolate_, ctor);
1901}
1902
1903Local<FunctionTemplate> PerIsolateData::GetDomNodeCtor() const {
1904 return dom_node_ctor_.Get(isolate_);
1905}
1906
1907void PerIsolateData::SetDomNodeCtor(Local<FunctionTemplate> ctor) {
1908 dom_node_ctor_.Reset(isolate_, ctor);
1909}
1910
1911bool PerIsolateData::HasRunningSubscribedWorkers() {
1912 // Only consider subscribed workers, so that code that spawns a worker and
1913 // never subscribes to message events will quit.
1914 return !worker_message_callbacks_.empty();
1915}
1916
1917void PerIsolateData::RegisterWorker(std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker) {
1918 registered_workers_.insert(std::move(worker));
1919}
1920
1921void PerIsolateData::SubscribeWorkerOnMessage(
1922 const std::shared_ptr<Worker>& worker, Local<Context> context,
1923 Local<Function> callback) {
1924 if (!registered_workers_.contains(worker)) {
1925 // The worker has already terminated, so it won't be posting any more
1926 // messages. Don't try to subscribe to its events.
1927 fprintf(
1928 stderr,
1929 "Trying to subscribe to message events from a terminated worker -- "
1930 "consider registering the event handler before the event loop runs.\n");
1931 return;
1932 }
1933 worker_message_callbacks_.emplace(
1934 worker, std::make_pair(Global<Context>(isolate_, context),
1935 Global<Function>(isolate_, callback)));
1936}
1937
1938std::pair<Local<Context>, Local<Function>> PerIsolateData::GetWorkerOnMessage(
1939 const std::shared_ptr<Worker>& worker) const {
1940 auto it = worker_message_callbacks_.find(worker);
1941 if (it == worker_message_callbacks_.end()) {
1942 return {};
1943 }
1944 return {it->second.first.Get(isolate_), it->second.second.Get(isolate_)};
1945}
1946
1947void PerIsolateData::UnregisterWorker(const std::shared_ptr<Worker>& worker) {
1948 registered_workers_.erase(worker);
1949 worker_message_callbacks_.erase(worker);
1950}
1951
1952PerIsolateData::RealmScope::RealmScope(Isolate* isolate,
1953 const Global<Context>& context)
1954 : data_(PerIsolateData::Get(isolate)) {
1955 data_->realm_count_ = 1;
1956 data_->realm_current_ = 0;
1957 data_->realm_switch_ = 0;
1958 data_->realms_ = new Global<Context>[1];
1959 data_->realms_[0].Reset(data_->isolate_, context);
1960}
1961
1962PerIsolateData::RealmScope::~RealmScope() {
1963 // Drop realms to avoid keeping them alive.
1964 data_->realm_count_ = 0;
1965 delete[] data_->realms_;
1966}
1967
1968PerIsolateData::ExplicitRealmScope::ExplicitRealmScope(PerIsolateData* data,
1969 int index)
1970 : data_(data), index_(index) {
1971 realm_ = Local<Context>::New(data->isolate_, data->realms_[index_]);
1972 realm_->Enter();
1973 previous_index_ = data->realm_current_;
1974 data->realm_current_ = data->realm_switch_ = index_;
1975}
1976
1977PerIsolateData::ExplicitRealmScope::~ExplicitRealmScope() {
1978 realm_->Exit();
1979 data_->realm_current_ = data_->realm_switch_ = previous_index_;
1980}
1981
1982Local<Context> PerIsolateData::ExplicitRealmScope::context() const {
1983 return realm_;
1984}
1985
1986int PerIsolateData::RealmFind(Local<Context> context) {
1987 for (int i = 0; i < realm_count_; ++i) {
1988 if (realms_[i] == context) return i;
1989 }
1990 return -1;
1991}
1992
1993int PerIsolateData::RealmIndexOrThrow(
1994 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info, int arg_offset) {
1995 if (info.Length() < arg_offset || !info[arg_offset]->IsNumber()) {
1996 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Invalid argument");
1997 return -1;
1998 }
1999 int index = info[arg_offset]
2000 ->Int32Value(info.GetIsolate()->GetCurrentContext())
2001 .FromMaybe(-1);
2002 if (index < 0 || index >= realm_count_ || realms_[index].IsEmpty()) {
2003 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Invalid realm index");
2004 return -1;
2005 }
2006 return index;
2007}
2008
2009// GetTimestamp() returns a time stamp as double, measured in milliseconds.
2010// When v8_flags.verify_predictable mode is enabled it returns result of
2011// v8::Platform::MonotonicallyIncreasingTime().
2012double Shell::GetTimestamp() {
2013 if (i::v8_flags.verify_predictable) {
2014 return g_platform->MonotonicallyIncreasingTime();
2015 } else {
2016 base::TimeDelta delta = base::TimeTicks::Now() - kInitialTicks;
2017 return delta.InMillisecondsF();
2018 }
2019}
2020uint64_t Shell::GetTracingTimestampFromPerformanceTimestamp(
2021 double performance_timestamp) {
2022 // Don't use this in --verify-predictable mode, predictable timestamps don't
2023 // work well with tracing.
2024 DCHECK(!i::v8_flags.verify_predictable);
2025 base::TimeDelta delta =
2026 base::TimeDelta::FromMillisecondsD(performance_timestamp);
2027 // See TracingController::CurrentTimestampMicroseconds().
2028 int64_t internal_value = (delta + kInitialTicks).ToInternalValue();
2029 DCHECK_GE(internal_value, 0);
2030 return internal_value;
2031}

2033#ifdef V8_OS_LINUX
2034void SendPerfControlCommand(const char* command) {
2035 if (Shell::options.perf_ctl_fd != -1 && Shell::options.perf_ack_fd != -1) {
2036 size_t command_len = strlen(command);
2037 ssize_t ret = write(Shell::options.perf_ctl_fd, command, command_len);
2038 if (ret == -1) {
2039 fprintf(stderr, "perf_ctl write error: %s\n", strerror(errno));
2040 }
2041 CHECK_EQ(ret, command_len);
2042
2043 char ack[5];
2044 ret = read(Shell::options.perf_ack_fd, ack, 5);
2045 if (ret == -1) {
2046 fprintf(stderr, "perf_ack read error: %s\n", strerror(errno));
2047 }
2048 CHECK_EQ(ret, 5);
2049 CHECK_EQ(strcmp(ack, "ack\n"), 0);
2050 }
2051}
2052#endif
2053
2054// performance.now() returns GetTimestamp().
2055void Shell::PerformanceNow(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2056 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2057 info.GetReturnValue().Set(GetTimestamp());
2058}
2059
2060// performance.mark() records and returns a PerformanceEntry with the current
2061// timestamp.
2062void Shell::PerformanceMark(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2063 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2064 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2065 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
2066
2067 if (info.Length() < 1 || !info[0]->IsString()) {
2068 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Invalid 'name' argument");
2069 return;
2070 }
2071 Local<String> name = info[0].As<String>();
2072
2073 double timestamp = GetTimestamp();
2074
2075 Local<Object> performance_entry = Object::New(isolate);
2076 performance_entry
2077 ->DefineOwnProperty(context,
2078 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "entryType"),
2079 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "mark"), ReadOnly)
2080 .Check();
2081 performance_entry
2082 ->DefineOwnProperty(context, String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "name"),
2083 name, ReadOnly)
2084 .Check();
2085 performance_entry
2086 ->DefineOwnProperty(context,
2087 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "startTime"),
2088 Number::New(isolate, timestamp), ReadOnly)
2089 .Check();
2090 performance_entry
2091 ->DefineOwnProperty(context,
2092 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "duration"),
2093 Integer::New(isolate, 0), ReadOnly)
2094 .Check();
2095
2096 info.GetReturnValue().Set(performance_entry);
2097
2098#ifdef V8_OS_LINUX
2099 if (options.scope_linux_perf_to_mark_measure) {
2100 SendPerfControlCommand("enable");
2101 }
2102#endif
2103}
2104
2105// performance.measure() records and returns a PerformanceEntry with a duration
2106// since a given mark, or since zero.
2107void Shell::PerformanceMeasure(
2108 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2109 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2110 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2111 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
2112
2113 if (info.Length() < 1 || !info[0]->IsString()) {
2114 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Invalid 'name' argument");
2115 return;
2116 }
2117 v8::Local<String> name = info[0].As<String>();
2118
2119 double start_timestamp = 0;
2120 if (info.Length() >= 2) {
2121#ifdef V8_OS_LINUX
2122 if (options.scope_linux_perf_to_mark_measure) {
2123 SendPerfControlCommand("disable");
2124 }
2125#endif
2126
2127 Local<Value> start_mark = info[1].As<Value>();
2128 if (!start_mark->IsObject()) {
2129 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(),
2130 "Invalid 'startMark' argument: Not an Object");
2131 return;
2132 }
2133 Local<Value> start_time_field;
2134 if (!start_mark.As<Object>()
2135 ->Get(context, String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "startTime"))
2136 .ToLocal(&start_time_field)) {
2137 return;
2138 }
2139 if (!start_time_field->IsNumber()) {
2140 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(),
2141 "Invalid 'startMark' argument: No numeric 'startTime' field");
2142 return;
2143 }
2144 start_timestamp = start_time_field.As<Number>()->Value();
2145 }
2146 if (info.Length() > 2) {
2147 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Too many arguments");
2148 return;
2149 }
2150
2151 double end_timestamp = GetTimestamp();
2152
2153 if (options.trace_enabled) {
2154 size_t hash = base::hash_combine(name->GetIdentityHash(), start_timestamp,
2155 end_timestamp);
2156
2157 String::Utf8Value utf8(isolate, name);
2158 TRACE_EVENT_COPY_NESTABLE_ASYNC_BEGIN_WITH_TIMESTAMP1(
2159 "v8", *utf8, static_cast<uint64_t>(hash),
2160 GetTracingTimestampFromPerformanceTimestamp(start_timestamp),
2161 "startTime", start_timestamp);
2162 TRACE_EVENT_COPY_NESTABLE_ASYNC_END_WITH_TIMESTAMP0(
2163 "v8", *utf8, static_cast<uint64_t>(hash),
2164 GetTracingTimestampFromPerformanceTimestamp(end_timestamp));
2165 }
2166
2167 Local<Object> performance_entry = Object::New(isolate);
2168 performance_entry
2169 ->DefineOwnProperty(
2170 context, String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "entryType"),
2171 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "measure"), ReadOnly)
2172 .Check();
2173 performance_entry
2174 ->DefineOwnProperty(context, String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "name"),
2175 name, ReadOnly)
2176 .Check();
2177 performance_entry
2178 ->DefineOwnProperty(context,
2179 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "startTime"),
2180 Number::New(isolate, start_timestamp), ReadOnly)
2181 .Check();
2182 performance_entry
2183 ->DefineOwnProperty(
2184 context, String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "duration"),
2185 Number::New(isolate, end_timestamp - start_timestamp), ReadOnly)
2186 .Check();
2187
2188 info.GetReturnValue().Set(performance_entry);
2189}
2190
2191// performance.measureMemory() implements JavaScript Memory API proposal.
2192// See https://github.com/ulan/javascript-agent-memory/blob/master/explainer.md.
2193void Shell::PerformanceMeasureMemory(
2194 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2195 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2196 v8::MeasureMemoryMode mode = v8::MeasureMemoryMode::kSummary;
2197 v8::Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2198 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
2199 if (info.Length() >= 1 && info[0]->IsObject()) {
2200 Local<Object> object = info[0].As<Object>();
2201 Local<Value> value = TryGetValue(isolate, context, object, "detailed")
2202 .FromMaybe(Local<Value>());
2203 if (value.IsEmpty()) {
2204 // Exception was thrown and scheduled, so return from the callback.
2205 return;
2206 }
2207 if (value->IsBoolean() && value->BooleanValue(isolate)) {
2208 mode = v8::MeasureMemoryMode::kDetailed;
2209 }
2210 }
2211 Local<v8::Promise::Resolver> promise_resolver =
2212 v8::Promise::Resolver::New(context).ToLocalChecked();
2213 info.GetIsolate()->MeasureMemory(
2214 v8::MeasureMemoryDelegate::Default(isolate, context, promise_resolver,
2215 mode),
2216 v8::MeasureMemoryExecution::kEager);
2217 info.GetReturnValue().Set(promise_resolver->GetPromise());
2218}

2220// Realm.current() returns the index of the currently active realm.
2221void Shell::RealmCurrent(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2222 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2223 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2224 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
2225 int index = data->RealmFind(isolate->GetEnteredOrMicrotaskContext());
2226 if (index == -1) return;
2227 info.GetReturnValue().Set(index);
2228}
2229
2230// Realm.owner(o) returns the index of the realm that created o.
2231void Shell::RealmOwner(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2232 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2233 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2234 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
2235 if (info.Length() < 1 || !info[0]->IsObject()) {
2236 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Invalid argument");
2237 return;
2238 }
2239 Local<Object> object =
2240 info[0]->ToObject(isolate->GetCurrentContext()).ToLocalChecked();
2241 i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> i_object = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*object);
2242 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*i_object) &&
2243 i::Cast<i::JSGlobalProxy>(i_object)->IsDetached()) {
2244 return;
2245 }
2246 Local<Context> creation_context;
2247 if (!object->GetCreationContext(isolate).ToLocal(&creation_context)) {
2248 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "object doesn't have creation context");
2249 return;
2250 }
2251 int index = data->RealmFind(creation_context);
2252 if (index == -1) return;
2253 info.GetReturnValue().Set(index);
2254}
2255
2256// Realm.global(i) returns the global object of realm i.
2257// (Note that properties of global objects cannot be read/written cross-realm.)
2258void Shell::RealmGlobal(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2259 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2260 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(info.GetIsolate());
2261 int index = data->RealmIndexOrThrow(info, 0);
2262 if (index == -1) return;
2263 // TODO(chromium:324812): Ideally Context::Global should never return raw
2264 // global objects but return a global proxy. Currently it returns global
2265 // object when the global proxy is detached from the global object. The
2266 // following is a workaround till we fix Context::Global so we don't leak
2267 // global objects.
2268 Local<Object> global =
2269 Local<Context>::New(info.GetIsolate(), data->realms_[index])->Global();
2270 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> i_global = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global);
2271 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*i_global)) {
2272 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
2273 i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> i_global_proxy(
2274 i::Cast<i::JSGlobalObject>(i_global)->global_proxy(), i_isolate);
2275 global = Utils::ToLocal(i_global_proxy);
2276 }
2277 info.GetReturnValue().Set(global);
2278}
2279
2280MaybeLocal<Context> Shell::CreateRealm(
2281 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info, int index,
2282 v8::MaybeLocal<Value> global_object) {
2283 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2284 const char* kGlobalHandleLabel = "d8::realm";
2285 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2286 TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
2287 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
2288 if (index < 0) {
2289 Global<Context>* old_realms = data->realms_;
2290 index = data->realm_count_;
2291 data->realms_ = new Global<Context>[++data->realm_count_];
2292 for (int i = 0; i < index; ++i) {
2293 Global<Context>& realm = data->realms_[i];
2294 realm.Reset(isolate, old_realms[i]);
2295 if (!realm.IsEmpty()) {
2296 realm.AnnotateStrongRetainer(kGlobalHandleLabel);
2297 }
2298 old_realms[i].Reset();
2299 }
2300 delete[] old_realms;
2301 }
2302 Local<ObjectTemplate> global_template = CreateGlobalTemplate(isolate);
2303 Local<Context> context =
2304 Context::New(isolate, nullptr, global_template, global_object);
2305 if (context.IsEmpty()) return MaybeLocal<Context>();
2306 DCHECK(!try_catch.HasCaught());
2307 InitializeModuleEmbedderData(context);
2308 data->realms_[index].Reset(isolate, context);
2309 data->realms_[index].AnnotateStrongRetainer(kGlobalHandleLabel);
2310 info.GetReturnValue().Set(index);
2311 return context;
2312}
2313
2314void Shell::DisposeRealm(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info,
2315 int index) {
2316 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2317 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2318 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
2319 Local<Context> context = data->realms_[index].Get(isolate);
2320 data->realms_[index].Reset();
2321 // ContextDisposedNotification expects the disposed context to be entered.
2322 v8::Context::Scope scope(context);
2323 isolate->ContextDisposedNotification();
2324}

2326// Realm.create() creates a new realm with a distinct security token
2327// and returns its index.
2328void Shell::RealmCreate(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2329 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2330 CreateRealm(info, -1, v8::MaybeLocal<Value>());
2331}
