2333// Realm.createAllowCrossRealmAccess() creates a new realm with the same
2334// security token as the current realm.
2335void Shell::RealmCreateAllowCrossRealmAccess(
2336 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2337 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2338 Local<Context> context;
2339 if (CreateRealm(info, -1, v8::MaybeLocal<Value>()).ToLocal(&context)) {
2340 context->SetSecurityToken(
2341 info.GetIsolate()->GetEnteredOrMicrotaskContext()->GetSecurityToken());
2342 }
2343}
2344
2345// Realm.navigate(i) creates a new realm with a distinct security token
2346// in place of realm i.
2347void Shell::RealmNavigate(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2348 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2349 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2350 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
2351 int index = data->RealmIndexOrThrow(info, 0);
2352 if (index == -1) return;
2353 if (index == 0 || index == data->realm_current_ ||
2354 index == data->realm_switch_) {
2355 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Invalid realm index");
2356 return;
2357 }
2358
2359 Local<Context> context = Local<Context>::New(isolate, data->realms_[index]);
2360 v8::MaybeLocal<Value> global_object = context->Global();
2361
2362 // Context::Global doesn't return JSGlobalProxy if DetachGlobal is called in
2363 // advance.
2364 if (!global_object.IsEmpty()) {
2365 HandleScope scope(isolate);
2366 if (!IsJSGlobalProxy(
2367 *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_object.ToLocalChecked()))) {
2368 global_object = v8::MaybeLocal<Value>();
2369 }
2370 }
2371
2372 DisposeRealm(info, index);
2373 CreateRealm(info, index, global_object);
2374}

2376// Realm.detachGlobal(i) detaches the global objects of realm i from realm i.
2377void Shell::RealmDetachGlobal(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2378 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2379 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2380 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
2381 int index = data->RealmIndexOrThrow(info, 0);
2382 if (index == -1) return;
2383 if (index == 0 || index == data->realm_current_ ||
2384 index == data->realm_switch_) {
2385 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Invalid realm index");
2386 return;
2387 }
2388
2389 HandleScope scope(isolate);
2390 Local<Context> realm = Local<Context>::New(isolate, data->realms_[index]);
2391 realm->DetachGlobal();
2392}

2399 int index = data->RealmIndexOrThrow(info, 0);
2400 if (index == -1) return;
2401 if (index == 0 || index == data->realm_current_ ||
2402 index == data->realm_switch_) {
2403 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Invalid realm index");
2404 return;

2409// Realm.switch(i) switches to the realm i for consecutive interactive inputs.
2410void Shell::RealmSwitch(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {

2415 if (index == -1) return;
2416 data->realm_switch_ = index;

2418
2419// Realm.eval(i, s) evaluates s in realm i and returns the result.
2420void Shell::RealmEval(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2421 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2422 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2423 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
2424 int index = data->RealmIndexOrThrow(info, 0);
2425 if (index == -1) return;
2426 if (info.Length() < 2) {
2427 ThrowError(isolate, "Invalid argument");
2428 return;
2429 }
2430
2431 Local<String> source;
2432 if (!ReadSource(info, 1, CodeType::kString).ToLocal(&source)) {
2433 ThrowError(isolate, "Invalid argument");
2434 return;
2435 }
2436 ScriptOrigin origin =
2437 CreateScriptOrigin(isolate, String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "(d8)"),
2438 ScriptType::kClassic);
2439
2440 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) return;
2441 ScriptCompiler::Source script_source(source, origin);
2442 Local<UnboundScript> script;
2443 if (!ScriptCompiler::CompileUnboundScript(isolate, &script_source)
2444 .ToLocal(&script)) {
2445 return;
2446 }
2447 Local<Value> result;
2448 {
2449 PerIsolateData::ExplicitRealmScope realm_scope(data, index);
2450 if (!script->BindToCurrentContext()
2451 ->Run(realm_scope.context())
2452 .ToLocal(&result)) {
2453 return;
2454 }
2455 }
2456 info.GetReturnValue().Set(result);
2457}

2459// Realm.shared is an accessor for a single shared value across realms.

2461 const PropertyCallbackInfo<Value>& info) {
2462 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2463 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2464 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
2465 if (data->realm_shared_.IsEmpty()) return;
2466 info.GetReturnValue().Set(data->realm_shared_);
2467}
2468
2469void Shell::RealmSharedSet(Local<Name> property, Local<Value> value,
2470 const PropertyCallbackInfo<void>& info) {
2471 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2472 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2473 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
2474 data->realm_shared_.Reset(isolate, value);
2475}
2476
2477void Shell::LogGetAndStop(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2478 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2479 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2480 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
2481 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2482
2483 std::string file_name = i_isolate->v8_file_logger()->file_name();
2484 if (!i::LogFile::IsLoggingToTemporaryFile(file_name)) {
2485 ThrowError(isolate, "Only capturing from temporary files is supported.");
2486 return;
2487 }
2488 if (!i_isolate->v8_file_logger()->is_logging()) {
2489 ThrowError(isolate, "Logging not enabled.");
2490 return;
2491 }
2492
2493 std::string raw_log;
2494 FILE* log_file = i_isolate->v8_file_logger()->TearDownAndGetLogFile();
2495 if (!log_file) {
2496 ThrowError(isolate, "Log file does not exist.");
2497 return;
2498 }
2499
2500 bool exists = false;
2501 raw_log = i::ReadFile(log_file, &exists, true);
2502 base::Fclose(log_file);
2503
2504 if (!exists) {
2505 ThrowError(isolate, "Unable to read log file.");
2506 return;
2507 }
2508 Local<String> result =
2509 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, raw_log.c_str(), NewStringType::kNormal,
2510 static_cast<int>(raw_log.size()))
2511 .ToLocalChecked();
2512
2513 info.GetReturnValue().Set(result);
2514}
2515
2516void Shell::TestVerifySourcePositions(
2517 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2518 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2519 // Check if the argument is a valid function.
2520 if (info.Length() != 1) {
2521 ThrowError(isolate, "Expected function as single argument.");
2522 return;
2523 }
2524 auto arg_handle = Utils::OpenHandle(*info[0]);
2525 if (!IsHeapObject(*arg_handle) ||
2526 !IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(
2527 *i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(arg_handle))) {
2528 ThrowError(isolate, "Expected function as single argument.");
2529 return;
2530 }
2531
2532 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
2533 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2534
2535 auto callable =
2536 i::Cast<i::JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction>(arg_handle);
2537 while (IsJSBoundFunction(*callable)) {
2538 internal::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2539 auto bound_function = i::Cast<i::JSBoundFunction>(callable);
2540 auto bound_target = bound_function->bound_target_function();
2541 if (!IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(bound_target)) {
2542 internal::AllowGarbageCollection allow_gc;
2543 ThrowError(isolate, "Expected function as bound target.");
2544 return;
2545 }
2546 callable = handle(
2547 i::Cast<i::JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction>(bound_target),
2548 i_isolate);
2549 }
2550
2551 i::DirectHandle<i::JSFunction> function = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(callable);
2552 if (!function->shared()->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2553 ThrowError(isolate, "Function has no BytecodeArray attached.");
2554 return;
2555 }
2556 i::Handle<i::BytecodeArray> bytecodes =
2557 handle(function->shared()->GetBytecodeArray(i_isolate), i_isolate);
2558 i::interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator bytecode_iterator(bytecodes);
2559 bool has_baseline = function->shared()->HasBaselineCode();
2560 i::Handle<i::TrustedByteArray> bytecode_offsets;
2561 std::unique_ptr<i::baseline::BytecodeOffsetIterator> offset_iterator;
2562 if (has_baseline) {
2563 bytecode_offsets = handle(
2564 i::Cast<i::TrustedByteArray>(
2565 function->shared()->GetCode(i_isolate)->bytecode_offset_table()),
2566 i_isolate);
2567 offset_iterator = std::make_unique<i::baseline::BytecodeOffsetIterator>(
2568 bytecode_offsets, bytecodes);
2569 // A freshly initiated BytecodeOffsetIterator points to the prologue.
2570 DCHECK_EQ(offset_iterator->current_pc_start_offset(), 0);
2571 DCHECK_EQ(offset_iterator->current_bytecode_offset(),
2572 i::kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset);
2573 offset_iterator->Advance();
2574 }
2575 while (!bytecode_iterator.done()) {
2576 if (has_baseline) {
2577 if (offset_iterator->current_bytecode_offset() !=
2578 bytecode_iterator.current_offset()) {
2579 ThrowError(isolate, "Baseline bytecode offset mismatch.");
2580 return;
2581 }
2582 // Check that we map every address to this bytecode correctly.
2583 // The start address is exclusive and the end address inclusive.
2584 for (i::Address pc = offset_iterator->current_pc_start_offset() + 1;
2585 pc <= offset_iterator->current_pc_end_offset(); ++pc) {
2586 i::baseline::BytecodeOffsetIterator pc_lookup(bytecode_offsets,
2587 bytecodes);
2588 pc_lookup.AdvanceToPCOffset(pc);
2589 if (pc_lookup.current_bytecode_offset() !=
2590 bytecode_iterator.current_offset()) {
2591 ThrowError(isolate,
2592 "Baseline bytecode offset mismatch for PC lookup.");
2593 return;
2594 }
2595 }
2596 }
2597 bytecode_iterator.Advance();
2598 if (has_baseline && !bytecode_iterator.done()) {
2599 if (offset_iterator->done()) {
2600 ThrowError(isolate, "Missing bytecode(s) in baseline offset mapping.");
2601 return;
2602 }
2603 offset_iterator->Advance();
2604 }
2605 }
2606 if (has_baseline && !offset_iterator->done()) {
2607 ThrowError(isolate, "Excess offsets in baseline offset mapping.");
2608 return;
2609 }
2610}

2662
2663void Shell::SetPromiseHooks(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2664 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2665 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2666 if (i::v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
2667 // Setting promise hooks dynamically has unexpected timing side-effects
2668 // with certain promise optimizations. We might not get all callbacks for
2669 // previously scheduled Promises or optimized code-paths that skip Promise
2670 // creation.
2671 ThrowError(isolate,
2672 "d8.promise.setHooks is disabled with "
2673 "--correctness-fuzzer-suppressions");
2674 return;
2675 }
2676#ifdef V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
2677 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
2678 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2679
2680 context->SetPromiseHooks(
2681 info[0]->IsFunction() ? info[0].As<Function>() : Local<Function>(),
2682 info[1]->IsFunction() ? info[1].As<Function>() : Local<Function>(),
2683 info[2]->IsFunction() ? info[2].As<Function>() : Local<Function>(),
2684 info[3]->IsFunction() ? info[3].As<Function>() : Local<Function>());
2685
2686 info.GetReturnValue().Set(v8::Undefined(isolate));
2687#else // V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
2688 ThrowError(isolate,
2689 "d8.promise.setHooks is disabled due to missing build flag "
2690 "v8_enabale_javascript_in_promise_hooks");
2691#endif // V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
2692}
2693
2694void Shell::SerializerSerialize(
2695 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2696 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2697 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2698 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2699 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
2700
2701 ValueSerializer serializer(isolate);
2702 serializer.WriteHeader();
2703 for (int i = 0; i < info.Length(); i++) {
2704 bool ok;
2705 if (!serializer.WriteValue(context, info[i]).To(&ok)) return;
2706 }
2707 Local<v8::ArrayBuffer> buffer;
2708 {
2709 std::pair<uint8_t*, size_t> pair = serializer.Release();
2710 buffer = ArrayBuffer::New(isolate, pair.second);
2711 memcpy(buffer->GetBackingStore()->Data(), pair.first, pair.second);
2712 free(pair.first);
2713 }
2714 info.GetReturnValue().Set(buffer);
2715}
2716
2717void Shell::SerializerDeserialize(
2718 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2719 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2720 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2721 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2722 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
2723
2724 if (!info[0]->IsArrayBuffer()) {
2725 ThrowError(isolate, "Can only deserialize from an ArrayBuffer");
2726 return;
2727 }
2728 std::shared_ptr<BackingStore> backing_store =
2729 info[0].As<ArrayBuffer>()->GetBackingStore();
2730 ValueDeserializer deserializer(
2731 isolate, static_cast<const uint8_t*>(backing_store->Data()),
2732 backing_store->ByteLength());
2733 bool ok;
2734 if (!deserializer.ReadHeader(context).To(&ok)) return;
2735 Local<Value> result;
2736 if (!deserializer.ReadValue(context).ToLocal(&result)) return;
2737 info.GetReturnValue().Set(result);
2738}
2739
2740void Shell::ProfilerSetOnProfileEndListener(
2741 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2742 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2743 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2744 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2745 if (!info[0]->IsFunction()) {
2746 ThrowError(isolate, "The OnProfileEnd listener has to be a function");
2747 return;
2748 }
2749 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&profiler_end_callback_lock_);
2750 profiler_end_callback_[isolate] =
2751 std::make_pair(Global<Function>(isolate, info[0].As<Function>()),
2752 Global<Context>(isolate, isolate->GetCurrentContext()));
2753}
2754
2755bool Shell::HasOnProfileEndListener(Isolate* isolate) {
2756 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&profiler_end_callback_lock_);
2757 return profiler_end_callback_.find(isolate) != profiler_end_callback_.end();
2758}
2759
2760void Shell::ResetOnProfileEndListener(Isolate* isolate) {
2761 // If the inspector is enabled, then the installed console is not the
2762 // D8Console.
2763 if (options.enable_inspector) return;
2764 {
2765 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&profiler_end_callback_lock_);
2766 profiler_end_callback_.erase(isolate);
2767 }
2768
2769 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
2770 D8Console* console =
2771 reinterpret_cast<D8Console*>(i_isolate->console_delegate());
2772 if (console) {
2773 console->DisposeProfiler();
2774 }
2775}
2776
2777void Shell::ProfilerTriggerSample(
2778 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2779 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2780 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
2781 D8Console* console =
2782 reinterpret_cast<D8Console*>(i_isolate->console_delegate());
2783 if (console && console->profiler()) {
2784 console->profiler()->CollectSample(isolate);
2785 }
2786}
2787
2788void Shell::TriggerOnProfileEndListener(Isolate* isolate, std::string profile) {
2789 CHECK(HasOnProfileEndListener(isolate));
2790 Local<Function> callback;
2791 Local<Context> context;
2792 Local<Value> argv[1] = {
2793 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, profile.c_str()).ToLocalChecked()};
2794 {
2795 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&profiler_end_callback_lock_);
2796 auto& callback_pair = profiler_end_callback_[isolate];
2797 callback = callback_pair.first.Get(isolate);
2798 context = callback_pair.second.Get(isolate);
2799 }
2800 TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
2801 try_catch.SetVerbose(true);
2802 USE(callback->Call(context, Undefined(isolate), 1, argv));
2803}
2804
2805void WriteToFile(FILE* file, const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info,
2806 int first_arg_index = 0) {
2807 for (int i = first_arg_index; i < info.Length(); i++) {
2808 HandleScope handle_scope(info.GetIsolate());
2809 if (i != first_arg_index) {
2810 fprintf(file, " ");
2811 }
2812
2813 // Explicitly catch potential exceptions in toString().
2814 v8::TryCatch try_catch(info.GetIsolate());
2815 Local<Value> arg = info[i];
2816 Local<String> str_obj;
2817
2818 if (arg->IsSymbol()) {
2819 arg = arg.As<Symbol>()->Description(info.GetIsolate());
2820 }
2821 if (!arg->ToString(info.GetIsolate()->GetCurrentContext())
2822 .ToLocal(&str_obj)) {
2823 try_catch.ReThrow();
2824 return;
2825 }
2826
2827 v8::String::Utf8Value str(info.GetIsolate(), str_obj);
2828 size_t n = fwrite(*str, sizeof(**str), str.length(), file);
2829 if (n != str.length()) {
2830 printf("Error in fwrite\n");
2831 base::OS::ExitProcess(1);
2832 }
2833 }
2834}
2835
2836void WriteAndFlush(FILE* file,
2837 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2838 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2839 WriteToFile(file, info);
2840 fprintf(file, "\n");
2841 fflush(file);
2842}
2843
2844void Shell::Print(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2845 WriteAndFlush(stdout, info);
2846}
2847
2848void Shell::PrintErr(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2849 WriteAndFlush(stderr, info);
2850}
2851
2852void Shell::WriteStdout(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2853 WriteToFile(stdout, info);
2854}
2855
2856// There are two overloads of writeFile().
2857//
2858// The first parameter is always the filename.
2859//
2860// If there are exactly 2 arguments, and the second argument is an ArrayBuffer
2861// or an ArrayBufferView, write the binary contents into the file.
2862//
2863// Otherwise, convert arguments to UTF-8 strings, and write them to the file,
2864// separated by space.
2865void Shell::WriteFile(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2866 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2867 String::Utf8Value file_name(info.GetIsolate(), info[0]);
2868 if (*file_name == nullptr) {
2869 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Error converting filename to string");
2870 return;
2871 }
2872 FILE* file;
2873 if (info.Length() == 2 &&
2874 (info[1]->IsArrayBuffer() || info[1]->IsArrayBufferView())) {
2875 file = base::Fopen(*file_name, "wb");
2876 if (file == nullptr) {
2877 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Error opening file");
2878 return;
2879 }
2880
2881 void* data;
2882 size_t length;
2883 if (info[1]->IsArrayBuffer()) {
2884 Local<v8::ArrayBuffer> buffer = Local<v8::ArrayBuffer>::Cast(info[1]);
2885 length = buffer->ByteLength();
2886 data = buffer->Data();
2887 } else {
2888 Local<v8::ArrayBufferView> buffer_view =
2889 Local<v8::ArrayBufferView>::Cast(info[1]);
2890 length = buffer_view->ByteLength();
2891 data = static_cast<uint8_t*>(buffer_view->Buffer()->Data()) +
2892 buffer_view->ByteOffset();
2893 }
2894 fwrite(data, 1, length, file);
2895 } else {
2896 file = base::Fopen(*file_name, "w");
2897 if (file == nullptr) {
2898 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Error opening file");
2899 return;
2900 }
2901 WriteToFile(file, info, 1);
2902 }
2903 base::Fclose(file);
2904}
2905
2906void Shell::ReadFile(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2907 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2908 String::Utf8Value file_name(info.GetIsolate(), info[0]);
2909 if (*file_name == nullptr) {
2910 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Error converting filename to string");
2911 return;
2912 }
2913 if (info.Length() == 2) {
2914 String::Utf8Value format(info.GetIsolate(), info[1]);
2915 if (*format && std::strcmp(*format, "binary") == 0) {
2916 ReadBuffer(info);
2917 return;
2918 }
2919 }
2920 Local<String> source;
2921 if (!ReadFile(info.GetIsolate(), *file_name).ToLocal(&source)) return;
2922 info.GetReturnValue().Set(source);
2923}
2924
2925#if V8_TARGET_OS_LINUX && V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2926void Shell::CreateWasmMemoryMapDescriptor(
2927 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2928 CHECK(i::v8_flags.experimental_wasm_memory_control);
2929 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2930 String::Utf8Value file_name(info.GetIsolate(), info[0]);
2931 if (*file_name == nullptr) {
2932 ThrowError(info.GetIsolate(), "Error converting filename to string");
2933 return;
2934 }
2935
2936 int file_descriptor = open(*file_name, O_RDWR);
2937
2938 WasmMemoryMapDescriptor::WasmFileDescriptor wasm_fd =
2939 static_cast<WasmMemoryMapDescriptor::WasmFileDescriptor>(file_descriptor);
2940 info.GetReturnValue().Set(
2941 v8::WasmMemoryMapDescriptor::New(info.GetIsolate(), wasm_fd));
2942}
2943#endif // V8_TARGET_OS_LINUX
2944
2945Local<String> Shell::ReadFromStdin(Isolate* isolate) {
2946 static const int kBufferSize = 256;
2947 char buffer[kBufferSize];
2948 Local<String> accumulator = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "");
2949 int length;
2950 // Flush stdout before reading stdin, as stdout isn't guaranteed to be flushed
2951 // automatically.
2952 fflush(stdout);
2953 while (true) {
2954 // Continue reading if the line ends with an escape '\\' or the line has
2955 // not been fully read into the buffer yet (does not end with '\n').
2956 // If fgets gets an error, just give up.
2957 char* input = nullptr;
2958 input = fgets(buffer, kBufferSize, stdin);
2959 if (input == nullptr) return Local<String>();
2960 length = static_cast<int>(strlen(buffer));
2961 if (length == 0) {
2962 return accumulator;
2963 } else if (buffer[length - 1] != '\n') {
2964 accumulator = String::Concat(
2965 isolate, accumulator,
2966 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, buffer, NewStringType::kNormal, length)
2967 .ToLocalChecked());
2968 } else if (length > 1 && buffer[length - 2] == '\\') {
2969 buffer[length - 2] = '\n';
2970 accumulator =
2971 String::Concat(isolate, accumulator,
2972 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, buffer,
2973 NewStringType::kNormal, length - 1)
2974 .ToLocalChecked());
2975 } else {
2976 return String::Concat(
2977 isolate, accumulator,
2978 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, buffer, NewStringType::kNormal,
2979 length - 1)
2980 .ToLocalChecked());
2981 }
2982 }
2983}
2984
2985void Shell::ExecuteFile(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2986 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
2987 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
2988 for (int i = 0; i < info.Length(); i++) {
2989 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2990 String::Utf8Value file_name(isolate, info[i]);
2991 if (*file_name == nullptr) {
2992 std::ostringstream oss;
2993 oss << "Cannot convert file[" << i << "] name to string.";
2994 ThrowError(
2995 isolate,
2996 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, oss.str().c_str()).ToLocalChecked());
2997 return;
2998 }
2999 Local<String> source;
3000 if (!ReadFile(isolate, *file_name).ToLocal(&source)) return;
3001 if (!ExecuteString(
3002 info.GetIsolate(), source,
3003 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, *file_name).ToLocalChecked(),
3004 options.quiet_load ? kNoReportExceptions : kReportExceptions)) {
3005 std::ostringstream oss;
3006 oss << "Error executing file: \"" << *file_name << '"';
3007 ThrowError(
3008 isolate,
3009 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, oss.str().c_str()).ToLocalChecked());
3010 return;
3011 }
3012 }
3013}
3014
3015class SetTimeoutTask : public v8::Task {
3016 public:
3017 SetTimeoutTask(v8::Isolate* isolate, v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
3018 v8::Local<v8::Function> callback)
3019 : isolate_(isolate),
3020 context_(isolate, context),
3021 callback_(isolate, callback) {}
3022
3023 void Run() override {
3024 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
3025 Local<Context> context = context_.Get(isolate_);
3026 Local<Function> callback = callback_.Get(isolate_);
3027 Context::Scope context_scope(context);
3028 MaybeLocal<Value> result =
3029 callback->Call(context, Undefined(isolate_), 0, nullptr);
3030 USE(result);
3031 }
3032
3033 private:
3034 v8::Isolate* isolate_;
3035 v8::Global<v8::Context> context_;
3036 v8::Global<v8::Function> callback_;
3037};
3038
3039void Shell::SetTimeout(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3040 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3041 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3042 info.GetReturnValue().Set(v8::Number::New(isolate, 0));
3043 if (info.Length() == 0 || !info[0]->IsFunction()) return;
3044 Local<Function> callback = info[0].As<Function>();
3045 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
3046 g_platform->GetForegroundTaskRunner(isolate)->PostTask(
3047 std::make_unique<SetTimeoutTask>(isolate, context, callback));
3048}

3063
3064void Shell::ReadCodeTypeAndArguments(
3065 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info, int index,
3066 CodeType* code_type, Local<Value>* arguments) {
3067 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3068 if (info.Length() > index && info[index]->IsObject()) {
3069 Local<Object> object = info[index].As<Object>();
3070 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
3071 Local<Value> value;
3072 if (!TryGetValue(isolate, context, object, "type").ToLocal(&value)) {
3073 *code_type = CodeType::kNone;
3074 return;
3075 }
3076 if (!value->IsString()) {
3077 *code_type = CodeType::kInvalid;
3078 return;
3079 }
3080 Local<String> worker_type_string =
3081 value->ToString(context).ToLocalChecked();
3082 String::Utf8Value str(isolate, worker_type_string);
3083 if (strcmp("classic", *str) == 0) {
3084 *code_type = CodeType::kFileName;
3085 } else if (strcmp("string", *str) == 0) {
3086 *code_type = CodeType::kString;
3087 } else if (strcmp("function", *str) == 0) {
3088 *code_type = CodeType::kFunction;
3089 } else {
3090 *code_type = CodeType::kInvalid;
3091 }
3092 if (arguments != nullptr) {
3093 bool got_arguments =
3094 TryGetValue(isolate, context, object, "arguments").ToLocal(arguments);
3095 USE(got_arguments);
3096 }
3097 } else {
3098 *code_type = CodeType::kNone;
3099 }
3100}
3101
3102bool Shell::FunctionAndArgumentsToString(Local<Function> function,
3103 Local<Value> arguments,
3104 Local<String>* source,
3105 Isolate* isolate) {
3106 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
3107 MaybeLocal<String> maybe_function_string =
3108 function->FunctionProtoToString(context);
3109 Local<String> function_string;
3110 if (!maybe_function_string.ToLocal(&function_string)) {
3111 ThrowError(isolate, "Failed to convert function to string");
3112 return false;
3113 }
3114 *source = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "(");
3115 *source = String::Concat(isolate, *source, function_string);
3116 Local<String> middle = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, ")(");
3117 *source = String::Concat(isolate, *source, middle);
3118 if (!arguments.IsEmpty() && !arguments->IsUndefined()) {
3119 if (!arguments->IsArray()) {
3120 ThrowError(isolate, "'arguments' must be an array");
3121 return false;
3122 }
3123 Local<String> comma = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, ",");
3124 Local<Array> array = arguments.As<Array>();
3125 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < array->Length(); ++i) {
3126 if (i > 0) {
3127 *source = String::Concat(isolate, *source, comma);
3128 }
3129 MaybeLocal<Value> maybe_argument = array->Get(context, i);
3130 Local<Value> argument;
3131 if (!maybe_argument.ToLocal(&argument)) {
3132 ThrowError(isolate, "Failed to get argument");
3133 return false;
3134 }
3135 Local<String> argument_string;
3136 if (!JSON::Stringify(context, argument).ToLocal(&argument_string)) {
3137 ThrowError(isolate, "Failed to convert argument to string");
3138 return false;
3139 }
3140 *source = String::Concat(isolate, *source, argument_string);
3141 }
3142 }
3143 Local<String> suffix = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, ")");
3144 *source = String::Concat(isolate, *source, suffix);
3145 return true;
3146}
3147
3148// ReadSource() supports reading source code through `info[index]` as specified
3149// by the `default_type` or an optional options bag provided in `info[index+1]`
3150// (e.g. `options={type: 'code_type', arguments:[...]}`).
3151MaybeLocal<String> Shell::ReadSource(
3152 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info, int index,
3153 CodeType default_type) {
3154 CodeType code_type;
3155 Local<Value> arguments;
3156 ReadCodeTypeAndArguments(info, index + 1, &code_type, &arguments);
3157
3158 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3159 Local<String> source;
3160 if (code_type == CodeType::kNone) {
3161 code_type = default_type;
3162 }
3163 switch (code_type) {
3164 case CodeType::kFunction:
3165 if (!info[index]->IsFunction()) {
3166 return MaybeLocal<String>();
3167 }
3168 // Source: ( function_to_string )( params )
3169 if (!FunctionAndArgumentsToString(info[index].As<Function>(), arguments,
3170 &source, isolate)) {
3171 return MaybeLocal<String>();
3172 }
3173 break;
3174 case CodeType::kFileName: {
3175 if (!info[index]->IsString()) {
3176 return MaybeLocal<String>();
3177 }
3178 String::Utf8Value filename(isolate, info[index]);
3179 if (!Shell::ReadFile(isolate, *filename).ToLocal(&source)) {
3180 return MaybeLocal<String>();
3181 }
3182 break;
3183 }
3184 case CodeType::kString:
3185 if (!info[index]->IsString()) {
3186 return MaybeLocal<String>();
3187 }
3188 source = info[index].As<String>();
3189 break;
3190 case CodeType::kNone:
3191 case CodeType::kInvalid:
3192 return MaybeLocal<String>();
3193 }
3194 return source;
3195}
3196
3197void Shell::WorkerNew(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3198 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3199 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3200 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
3201 if (info.Length() < 1 || (!info[0]->IsString() && !info[0]->IsFunction())) {
3202 ThrowError(isolate, "1st argument must be a string or a function");
3203 return;
3204 }
3205
3206 Local<String> source;
3207 if (!ReadSource(info, 0, CodeType::kFileName).ToLocal(&source)) {
3208 ThrowError(isolate, "Invalid argument");
3209 return;
3210 }
3211
3212 if (!info.IsConstructCall()) {
3213 ThrowError(isolate, "Worker must be constructed with new");
3214 return;
3215 }
3216
3217 // Initialize the embedder field to 0; if we return early without
3218 // creating a new Worker (because the main thread is terminating) we can
3219 // early-out from the instance calls.
3220 info.This()->SetInternalField(0, v8::Integer::New(isolate, 0));
3221
3222 {
3223 // Don't allow workers to create more workers if the main thread
3224 // is waiting for existing running workers to terminate.
3225 i::ParkedMutexGuard lock_guard(
3226 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)->main_thread_local_isolate(),
3227 workers_mutex_.Pointer());
3228 if (!allow_new_workers_) return;
3229
3230 String::Utf8Value script(isolate, source);
3231 if (!*script) {
3232 ThrowError(isolate, "Can't get worker script");
3233 return;
3234 }
3235
3236 // The C++ worker object's lifetime is shared between the Managed<Worker>
3237 // object on the heap, which the JavaScript object points to, and an
3238 // internal std::shared_ptr in the worker thread itself.
3239 auto worker = std::make_shared<Worker>(isolate, *script);
3240 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
3241 const size_t kWorkerSizeEstimate = 4 * 1024 * 1024; // stack + heap.
3242 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> managed =
3243 i::Managed<Worker>::From(i_isolate, kWorkerSizeEstimate, worker);
3244 info.This()->SetInternalField(0, Utils::ToLocal(managed));
3245 base::Thread::Priority priority =
3246 options.apply_priority ? base::Thread::Priority::kUserBlocking
3247 : base::Thread::Priority::kDefault;
3248 if (!Worker::StartWorkerThread(isolate, worker, priority)) {
3249 ThrowError(isolate, "Can't start thread");
3250 return;
3251 }
3252 PerIsolateData::Get(isolate)->RegisterWorker(worker);
3253 }
3254}
3255
3256void Shell::WorkerPostMessage(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3257 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3258 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3259 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
3260
3261 if (info.Length() < 1) {
3262 ThrowError(isolate, "Invalid argument");
3263 return;
3264 }
3265
3266 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker =
3267 GetWorkerFromInternalField(isolate, info.This());
3268 if (!worker.get()) {
3269 return;
3270 }
3271
3272 Local<Value> message = info[0];
3273 Local<Value> transfer =
3274 info.Length() >= 2 ? info[1] : Undefined(isolate).As<Value>();
3275 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data =
3276 Shell::SerializeValue(isolate, message, transfer);
3277 if (data) {
3278 worker->PostMessage(std::move(data));
3279 }
3280}
3281
3282void Shell::WorkerGetMessage(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3283 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3284 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3285 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
3286 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker =
3287 GetWorkerFromInternalField(isolate, info.This());
3288 if (!worker.get()) {
3289 return;
3290 }
3291
3292 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data = worker->GetMessage(isolate);
3293 if (data) {
3294 Local<Value> value;
3295 if (Shell::DeserializeValue(isolate, std::move(data)).ToLocal(&value)) {
3296 info.GetReturnValue().Set(value);
3297 }
3298 }
3299}
3300
3301// Task processing one onmessage event received from a Worker.
3302class OnMessageFromWorkerTask : public v8::Task {
3303 public:
3304 OnMessageFromWorkerTask(v8::Isolate* isolate, v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
3305 v8::Local<v8::Value> callback,
3306 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data)
3307 : isolate_(isolate),
3308 context_(isolate, context),
3309 callback_(isolate, callback),
3310 data_(std::move(data)) {}
3311
3312 void Run() override {
3313 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
3314 Local<Context> context = context_.Get(isolate_);
3315 Context::Scope context_scope(context);
3316 MicrotasksScope microtasks_scope(context,
3317 MicrotasksScope::kDoNotRunMicrotasks);
3318
3319 Local<Object> global = context->Global();
3320
3321 // Get the message handler.
3322 Local<Value> onmessage = callback_.Get(isolate_);
3323 if (!onmessage->IsFunction()) return;
3324 Local<Function> onmessage_fun = onmessage.As<Function>();
3325
3326 v8::TryCatch try_catch(isolate_);
3327 try_catch.SetVerbose(true);
3328 Local<Value> value;
3329 if (Shell::DeserializeValue(isolate_, std::move(data_)).ToLocal(&value)) {
3330 DCHECK(!isolate_->IsExecutionTerminating());
3331 Local<Object> event = v8::Object::New(isolate_);
3332 event
3333 ->CreateDataProperty(
3334 context,
3335 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate_, "data",
3336 NewStringType::kInternalized),
3337 value)
3338 .ToChecked();
3339 Local<Value> argv[] = {event};
3340 MaybeLocal<Value> result = onmessage_fun->Call(context, global, 1, argv);
3341 USE(result);
3342 }
3343 }
3344
3345 private:
3346 v8::Isolate* isolate_;
3347 v8::Global<v8::Context> context_;
3348 v8::Global<v8::Value> callback_;
3349 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data_;
3350};
3351
3352// Check, on the main thread, whether a worker has any enqueued any message
3353// events. Workers post this task when posting a message, instead of posting
3354// OnMessageFromWorkerTask directly, to avoid races between message posting
3355// and onmessage subscription.
3356class CheckMessageFromWorkerTask : public v8::Task {
3357 public:
3358 CheckMessageFromWorkerTask(v8::Isolate* isolate,
3359 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker)
3360 : isolate_(isolate), worker_(std::move(worker)) {}
3361
3362 void Run() override {
3363 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
3364
3365 // Get the callback for onmessage events from this worker. It's important to
3366 // do this here, and not in OnMessageFromWorkerTask, because we may get a
3367 // CleanUpWorkerTask scheduled before the posted OnMessageFromWorkerTask
3368 // executes, which will
3369 auto callback_pair =
3370 PerIsolateData::Get(isolate_)->GetWorkerOnMessage(worker_);
3371 // Bail out if there's no callback -- leave the message queue untouched so
3372 // that we don't lose the messages and can read them with GetMessage later.
3373 // This is slightly different to browser behaviour, where events can be
3374 // missed, but it's helpful for d8's GetMessage behaviour.
3375 if (callback_pair.second.IsEmpty()) return;
3376
3377 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> result;
3378 while ((result = worker_->TryGetMessage())) {
3379 // Each onmessage callback call is posted as a separate task.
3380 g_platform->GetForegroundTaskRunner(isolate_)->PostTask(
3381 std::make_unique<OnMessageFromWorkerTask>(
3382 isolate_, callback_pair.first, callback_pair.second,
3383 std::move(result)));
3384 }
3385 }
3386
3387 private:
3388 v8::Isolate* isolate_;
3389 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker_;
3390};
3391
3392// Unregister the given isolate from message events from the given worker.
3393// This must be done before the isolate or worker are destroyed, so that the
3394// global handles for context and callback are cleaned up correctly -- thus the
3395// event loop blocks until all workers are unregistered.
3396class CleanUpWorkerTask : public v8::Task {
3397 public:
3398 CleanUpWorkerTask(v8::Isolate* isolate, std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker)
3399 : isolate_(isolate), worker_(std::move(worker)) {}
3400
3401 void Run() override {
3402 PerIsolateData::Get(isolate_)->UnregisterWorker(std::move(worker_));
3403 }
3404
3405 private:
3406 v8::Isolate* isolate_;
3407 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker_;
3408};
3409
3410void Shell::WorkerOnMessageGetter(
3411 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3412 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3413 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3414 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
3415
3416 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker =
3417 GetWorkerFromInternalField(isolate, info.This());
3418 if (!worker.get()) {
3419 return;
3420 }
3421 Local<Function> callback =
3422 PerIsolateData::Get(isolate)->GetWorkerOnMessage(worker).second;
3423
3424 if (!callback.IsEmpty()) {
3425 info.GetReturnValue().Set(callback);
3426 }
3427}
3428
3429void Shell::WorkerOnMessageSetter(
3430 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3431 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3432 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3433 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
3434
3435 if (info.Length() < 1) {
3436 ThrowError(isolate, "Invalid argument");
3437 return;
3438 }
3439
3440 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker =
3441 GetWorkerFromInternalField(isolate, info.This());
3442 if (!worker.get()) {
3443 return;
3444 }
3445
3446 Local<Value> callback = info[0];
3447 if (!callback->IsFunction()) return;
3448
3449 PerIsolateData::Get(isolate)->SubscribeWorkerOnMessage(
3450 worker, isolate->GetCurrentContext(), Local<Function>::Cast(callback));
3451}

3453void Shell::WorkerTerminate(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3454 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));

3460 worker->Terminate();

3463void Shell::WorkerTerminateAndWait(
3464 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3465 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3466 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3467 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
3468 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker =
3469 GetWorkerFromInternalField(isolate, info.This());
3470 if (!worker.get()) {
3471 return;
3472 }
3473
3474 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)
3475 ->main_thread_local_isolate()
3476 ->ExecuteMainThreadWhileParked([worker](const i::ParkedScope& parked) {
3477 worker->TerminateAndWaitForThread(parked);
3478 });
3479}
3480
3481void Shell::QuitOnce(v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>* info) {
3482 int exit_code = (*info)[0]
3483 ->Int32Value(info->GetIsolate()->GetCurrentContext())
3484 .FromMaybe(0);
3485 Isolate* isolate = info->GetIsolate();
3486 ResetOnProfileEndListener(isolate);
3487 isolate->Exit();
3488
3489 // As we exit the process anyway, we do not dispose the platform and other
3490 // global data and manually unlock to quell DCHECKs. Other isolates might
3491 // still be running, so disposing here can cause them to crash.
3492 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
3493 if (i_isolate->thread_manager()->IsLockedByCurrentThread()) {
3494 i_isolate->thread_manager()->Unlock();
3495 }
3496
3497 // When disposing the shared space isolate, the workers (client isolates) need
3498 // to be terminated first.
3499 if (i_isolate->is_shared_space_isolate()) {
3500 i_isolate->main_thread_local_isolate()->ExecuteMainThreadWhileParked(
3501 [](const i::ParkedScope& parked) { WaitForRunningWorkers(parked); });
3502 }
3503
3504 OnExit(isolate, false);
3505 base::OS::ExitProcess(exit_code);
3506}
3507
3508void Shell::Terminate(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3509 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3510 // Triggering termination from JS can cause some non-determinism thus we
3511 // skip it for correctness fuzzing.
3512 // Termination also currently breaks Fuzzilli's REPRL mechanism as the
3513 // scheduled termination will prevent the next testcase sent by Fuzzilli from
3514 // being processed. This will in turn desynchronize the communication
3515 // between d8 and Fuzzilli, leading to a crash.
3516 if (!i::v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions && !fuzzilli_reprl) {
3517 auto v8_isolate = info.GetIsolate();
3518 if (!v8_isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) v8_isolate->TerminateExecution();
3519 }
3520}
3521
3522void Shell::Quit(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3523 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3524 base::CallOnce(&quit_once_, &QuitOnce,
3525 const_cast<v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>*>(&info));
3526}

3528void Shell::Version(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
3529 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
3530 info.GetReturnValue().Set(
3531 String::NewFromUtf8(info.GetIsolate(), V8::GetVersion())
3532 .ToLocalChecked());
3533}
3534
3535void Shell::ReportException(Isolate* isolate, Local<v8::Message> message,
3536 Local<v8::Value> exception_obj) {
3537 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
3538 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
3539 bool enter_context = context.IsEmpty();
3540 if (enter_context) {
3541 context = Local<Context>::New(isolate, evaluation_context_);
3542 context->Enter();
3543 }
3544 // Converts a V8 value to a C string.
3545 auto ToCString = [](const v8::String::Utf8Value& value) {
3546 return *value ? *value : "<string conversion failed>";
3547 };
3548
3549 v8::String::Utf8Value exception(isolate, exception_obj);
3550 const char* exception_string = ToCString(exception);
3551 if (message.IsEmpty()) {
3552 // V8 didn't provide any extra information about this error; just
3553 // print the exception.
3554 printf("%s\n", exception_string);
3555 } else if (message->GetScriptOrigin().Options().IsWasm()) {
3556 // Print wasm-function[(function index)]:(offset): (message).
3557 int function_index = message->GetWasmFunctionIndex();
3558 int offset = message->GetStartColumn(context).FromJust();
3559 printf("wasm-function[%d]:0x%x: %s\n", function_index, offset,
3560 exception_string);
3561 } else {
3562 // Print (filename):(line number): (message).
3563 v8::String::Utf8Value filename(isolate,
3564 message->GetScriptOrigin().ResourceName());
3565 const char* filename_string = ToCString(filename);
3566 int linenum = message->GetLineNumber(context).FromMaybe(-1);
3567 printf("%s:%i: %s\n", filename_string, linenum, exception_string);
3568 Local<String> sourceline;
3569 if (message->GetSourceLine(context).ToLocal(&sourceline)) {
3570 // Print line of source code.
3571 v8::String::Utf8Value sourcelinevalue(isolate, sourceline);
3572 const char* sourceline_string = ToCString(sourcelinevalue);
3573 printf("%s\n", sourceline_string);
3574 // Print wavy underline (GetUnderline is deprecated).
3575 int start = message->GetStartColumn(context).FromJust();
3576 for (int i = 0; i < start; i++) {
3577 printf(" ");
3578 }
3579 int end = message->GetEndColumn(context).FromJust();
3580 for (int i = start; i < end; i++) {
3581 printf("^");
3582 }
3583 printf("\n");
3584 }
3585 }
3586 Local<Value> stack_trace_string;
3587 if (v8::TryCatch::StackTrace(context, exception_obj)
3588 .ToLocal(&stack_trace_string) &&
3589 stack_trace_string->IsString()) {
3590 v8::String::Utf8Value stack_trace(isolate, stack_trace_string.As<String>());
3591 printf("%s\n", ToCString(stack_trace));
3592 }
3593 printf("\n");
3594 if (enter_context) context->Exit();
3595}
3596
3597void Shell::ReportException(v8::Isolate* isolate,
3598 const v8::TryCatch& try_catch) {
3599 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) {
3600 printf("Got Execution Termination Exception\n");
3601 } else {
3602 ReportException(isolate, try_catch.Message(), try_catch.Exception());
3603 }
3604}

3606void Counter::Bind(const char* name, bool is_histogram) {
3607 base::OS::StrNCpy(name_, kMaxNameSize, name, kMaxNameSize);
3608 // Explicitly null-terminate, in case {name} is longer than {kMaxNameSize}.
3609 name_[kMaxNameSize - 1] = '\0';
3610 is_histogram_ = is_histogram;
3611}
3612
3613void Counter::AddSample(int sample) {
3614 count_.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_relaxed);
3615 sample_total_.fetch_add(sample, std::memory_order_relaxed);
3616}

3618CounterCollection::CounterCollection() {
3619 magic_number_ = 0xDEADFACE;
3620 max_counters_ = kMaxCounters;
3621 max_name_size_ = Counter::kMaxNameSize;
3622 counters_in_use_ = 0;
3623}
3624
3625Counter* CounterCollection::GetNextCounter() {
3626 if (counters_in_use_ == kMaxCounters) return nullptr;
3627 return &counters_[counters_in_use_++];
3628}
3629
3630void Shell::MapCounters(v8::Isolate* isolate, const char* name) {
3631 counters_file_ = base::OS::MemoryMappedFile::create(
3632 name, sizeof(CounterCollection), &local_counters_);
3633 void* memory =
3634 (counters_file_ == nullptr) ? nullptr : counters_file_->memory();
3635 if (memory == nullptr) {
3636 printf("Could not map counters file %s\n", name);
3637 base::OS::ExitProcess(1);
3638 }
3639 counters_ = static_cast<CounterCollection*>(memory);
3640 isolate->SetCounterFunction(LookupCounter);
3641 isolate->SetCreateHistogramFunction(CreateHistogram);
3642 isolate->SetAddHistogramSampleFunction(AddHistogramSample);
3643}
3644
3645Counter* Shell::GetCounter(const char* name, bool is_histogram) {
3646 Counter* counter = nullptr;
3647 {
3648 base::SharedMutexGuard<base::kShared> mutex_guard(&counter_mutex_);
3649 auto map_entry = counter_map_->find(name);
3650 if (map_entry != counter_map_->end()) {
3651 counter = map_entry->second;
3652 }
3653 }
3654
3655 if (counter == nullptr) {
3656 base::SharedMutexGuard<base::kExclusive> mutex_guard(&counter_mutex_);
3657
3658 counter = (*counter_map_)[name];
3659
3660 if (counter == nullptr) {
3661 counter = counters_->GetNextCounter();
3662 if (counter == nullptr) {
3663 // Too many counters.
3664 return nullptr;
3665 }
3666 (*counter_map_)[name] = counter;
3667 counter->Bind(name, is_histogram);
3668 }
3669 }
3670
3671 DCHECK_EQ(is_histogram, counter->is_histogram());
3672 return counter;
3673}
3674
3675int* Shell::LookupCounter(const char* name) {
3676 Counter* counter = GetCounter(name, false);
3677 return counter ? counter->ptr() : nullptr;
3678}
3679
3680void* Shell::CreateHistogram(const char* name, int min, int max,
3681 size_t buckets) {
3682 return GetCounter(name, true);
3683}
3684
3685void Shell::AddHistogramSample(void* histogram, int sample) {
3686 Counter* counter = reinterpret_cast<Counter*>(histogram);
3687 counter->AddSample(sample);
3688}

3690// Turn a value into a human-readable string.
3691Local<String> Shell::Stringify(Isolate* isolate, Local<Value> value) {
3692 v8::Local<v8::Context> context =
3693 v8::Local<v8::Context>::New(isolate, evaluation_context_);
3694 if (stringify_function_.IsEmpty()) {
3695 Local<String> source =
3696 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, stringify_source_).ToLocalChecked();
3697 Local<String> name = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "d8-stringify");
3698 ScriptOrigin origin(name);
3699 Local<Script> script =
3700 Script::Compile(context, source, &origin).ToLocalChecked();
3701 stringify_function_.Reset(
3702 isolate, script->Run(context).ToLocalChecked().As<Function>());
3703 }
3704 Local<Function> fun = Local<Function>::New(isolate, stringify_function_);
3705 Local<Value> argv[1] = {value};
3706 v8::TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
3707 MaybeLocal<Value> result = fun->Call(context, Undefined(isolate), 1, argv);
3708 if (result.IsEmpty()) return String::Empty(isolate);
3709 return result.ToLocalChecked().As<String>();
3710}

3715
3716 info.GetReturnValue().Set(v8::Number::New(isolate, 1));
3717}

3727
3728Local<FunctionTemplate> NewDOMFunctionTemplate(
3729 Isolate* isolate, JSApiInstanceType instance_type) {
3730 return FunctionTemplate::New(
3731 isolate, nullptr, Local<Value>(), Local<Signature>(), 0,
3732 ConstructorBehavior::kAllow, SideEffectType::kHasSideEffect, nullptr,
3733 static_cast<uint16_t>(instance_type));
3734}
3735
3736Local<FunctionTemplate> Shell::CreateEventTargetTemplate(Isolate* isolate) {
3737 Local<FunctionTemplate> event_target =
3738 NewDOMFunctionTemplate(isolate, JSApiInstanceType::kEventTarget);
3739 return event_target;
3740}
3741
3742Local<FunctionTemplate> Shell::CreateNodeTemplates(
3743 Isolate* isolate, Local<FunctionTemplate> event_target) {
3744 Local<FunctionTemplate> node =
3745 NewDOMFunctionTemplate(isolate, JSApiInstanceType::kNode);
3746 node->Inherit(event_target);
3747
3748 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
3749 data->SetDomNodeCtor(node);
3750
3751 Local<ObjectTemplate> proto_template = node->PrototypeTemplate();
3752 Local<Signature> signature = v8::Signature::New(isolate, node);
3753 Local<FunctionTemplate> nodeType = FunctionTemplate::New(
3754 isolate, NodeTypeCallback, Local<Value>(), signature, 0,
3755 ConstructorBehavior::kThrow, SideEffectType::kHasSideEffect, nullptr,
3756 static_cast<uint16_t>(JSApiInstanceType::kGenericApiObject),
3757 static_cast<uint16_t>(JSApiInstanceType::kElement),
3758 static_cast<uint16_t>(JSApiInstanceType::kHTMLDivElement));
3759 nodeType->SetAcceptAnyReceiver(false);
3760 proto_template->SetAccessorProperty(
3761 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "nodeType"), nodeType);
3762
3763 Local<FunctionTemplate> element =
3764 NewDOMFunctionTemplate(isolate, JSApiInstanceType::kElement);
3765 element->Inherit(node);
3766
3767 Local<FunctionTemplate> html_element =
3768 NewDOMFunctionTemplate(isolate, JSApiInstanceType::kHTMLElement);
3769 html_element->Inherit(element);
3770
3771 Local<FunctionTemplate> div_element =
3772 NewDOMFunctionTemplate(isolate, JSApiInstanceType::kHTMLDivElement);
3773 div_element->Inherit(html_element);
3774
3775 return div_element;
3776}

3778Local<ObjectTemplate> Shell::CreateGlobalTemplate(Isolate* isolate) {
3779 Local<ObjectTemplate> global_template = ObjectTemplate::New(isolate);
3780 global_template->Set(Symbol::GetToStringTag(isolate),
3781 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "global"));
3782 global_template->Set(isolate, "version",
3783 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, Version));
3784
3785 global_template->Set(isolate, "print", FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, Print));
3786 global_template->Set(isolate, "printErr",
3787 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, PrintErr));
3788 global_template->Set(isolate, "write",
3789 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, WriteStdout));
3790 if (!i::v8_flags.fuzzing) {
3791 global_template->Set(isolate, "writeFile",
3792 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, WriteFile));
3793 }
3794 global_template->Set(isolate, "read",
3795 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, ReadFile));
3796 global_template->Set(isolate, "readbuffer",
3797 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, ReadBuffer));
3798 global_template->Set(isolate, "readline",
3799 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, ReadLine));
3800 global_template->Set(isolate, "load",
3801 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, ExecuteFile));
3802 global_template->Set(isolate, "setTimeout",
3803 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, SetTimeout));
3804 // Some Emscripten-generated code tries to call 'quit', which in turn would
3805 // call C's exit(). This would lead to memory leaks, because there is no way
3806 // we can terminate cleanly then, so we need a way to hide 'quit'.
3807 if (!options.omit_quit) {
3808 global_template->Set(isolate, "quit", FunctionTemplate::New(isolate, Quit));
3809 }
3810 global_template->Set(isolate, "testRunner",
3811 Shell::CreateTestRunnerTemplate(isolate));
3812 global_template->Set(isolate, "Realm", Shell::CreateRealmTemplate(isolate));
3813 global_template->Set(isolate, "performance",
3814 Shell::CreatePerformanceTemplate(isolate));
3815 global_template->Set(isolate, "Worker", Shell::CreateWorkerTemplate(isolate));
3816
3817 // Prevent fuzzers from creating side effects.
3818 if (!i::v8_flags.fuzzing) {
3819 global_template->Set(isolate, "os", Shell::CreateOSTemplate(isolate));
3820 }
3821 global_template->Set(isolate, "d8", Shell::CreateD8Template(isolate));
3822
3823 if (i::v8_flags.expose_async_hooks) {
3824 global_template->Set(isolate, "async_hooks",
3825 Shell::CreateAsyncHookTemplate(isolate));
3826 }
3827
3828 return global_template;
3829}

4065
4066static void PrintMessageCallback(Local<Message> message, Local<Value> error) {
4067 switch (message->ErrorLevel()) {
4068 case v8::Isolate::kMessageWarning:
4069 case v8::Isolate::kMessageLog:
4070 case v8::Isolate::kMessageInfo:
4071 case v8::Isolate::kMessageDebug: {
4072 break;
4073 }
4074
4075 case v8::Isolate::kMessageError: {
4076 Shell::ReportException(message->GetIsolate(), message, error);
4077 return;
4078 }
4079
4080 default: {
4081 UNREACHABLE();
4082 }
4083 }
4084 // Converts a V8 value to a C string.
4085 auto ToCString = [](const v8::String::Utf8Value& value) {
4086 return *value ? *value : "<string conversion failed>";
4087 };
4088 Isolate* isolate = message->GetIsolate();
4089 v8::String::Utf8Value msg(isolate, message->Get());
4090 const char* msg_string = ToCString(msg);
4091 // Print (filename):(line number): (message).
4092 v8::String::Utf8Value filename(isolate,
4093 message->GetScriptOrigin().ResourceName());
4094 const char* filename_string = ToCString(filename);
4095 Maybe<int> maybeline = message->GetLineNumber(isolate->GetCurrentContext());
4096 int linenum = maybeline.IsJust() ? maybeline.FromJust() : -1;
4097 printf("%s:%i: %s\n", filename_string, linenum, msg_string);
4098}
4099
4100void Shell::PromiseRejectCallback(v8::PromiseRejectMessage data) {
4101 if (options.ignore_unhandled_promises) return;
4102 if (data.GetEvent() == v8::kPromiseRejectAfterResolved ||
4103 data.GetEvent() == v8::kPromiseResolveAfterResolved) {
4104 // Ignore reject/resolve after resolved.
4105 return;
4106 }
4107 v8::Local<v8::Promise> promise = data.GetPromise();
4108 v8::Isolate* isolate = promise->GetIsolate();
4109 PerIsolateData* isolate_data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
4110
4111 if (data.GetEvent() == v8::kPromiseHandlerAddedAfterReject) {
4112 isolate_data->RemoveUnhandledPromise(promise);
4113 return;
4114 }
4115
4116 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
4117 bool capture_exceptions =
4118 i_isolate->get_capture_stack_trace_for_uncaught_exceptions();
4119 isolate->SetCaptureStackTraceForUncaughtExceptions(true);
4120 v8::Local<Value> exception = data.GetValue();
4121 v8::Local<Message> message;
4122 // Assume that all objects are stack-traces.
4123 if (exception->IsObject()) {
4124 message = v8::Exception::CreateMessage(isolate, exception);
4125 }
4126 if (!exception->IsNativeError() &&
4127 (message.IsEmpty() || message->GetStackTrace().IsEmpty())) {
4128 // If there is no real Error object, manually create a stack trace.
4129 exception = v8::Exception::Error(
4130 v8::String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "Unhandled Promise."));
4131 message = Exception::CreateMessage(isolate, exception);
4132 }
4133 isolate->SetCaptureStackTraceForUncaughtExceptions(capture_exceptions);
4134
4135 isolate_data->AddUnhandledPromise(promise, message, exception);
4136}
4137
4138void Shell::Initialize(Isolate* isolate, D8Console* console,
4139 bool isOnMainThread) {
4140 isolate->SetPromiseRejectCallback(PromiseRejectCallback);
4141 isolate->SetWasmAsyncResolvePromiseCallback(
4142 D8WasmAsyncResolvePromiseCallback);
4143 if (isOnMainThread) {
4144 // Set up counters
4145 if (i::v8_flags.map_counters[0] != '\0') {
4146 MapCounters(isolate, i::v8_flags.map_counters);
4147 }
4148 // Disable default message reporting.
4149 isolate->AddMessageListenerWithErrorLevel(
4150 PrintMessageCallback,
4151 v8::Isolate::kMessageError | v8::Isolate::kMessageWarning |
4152 v8::Isolate::kMessageInfo | v8::Isolate::kMessageDebug |
4153 v8::Isolate::kMessageLog);
4154 }
4155
4156 isolate->SetHostImportModuleDynamicallyCallback(
4157 Shell::HostImportModuleDynamically);
4158 isolate->SetHostImportModuleWithPhaseDynamicallyCallback(
4159 Shell::HostImportModuleWithPhaseDynamically);
4160 isolate->SetHostInitializeImportMetaObjectCallback(
4161 Shell::HostInitializeImportMetaObject);
4162 isolate->SetHostCreateShadowRealmContextCallback(
4163 Shell::HostCreateShadowRealmContext);
4164
4165 debug::SetConsoleDelegate(isolate, console);
4166}
4167
4168Local<String> Shell::WasmLoadSourceMapCallback(Isolate* isolate,
4169 const char* path) {
4170 return Shell::ReadFile(isolate, path, false).ToLocalChecked();
4171}
4172
4173MaybeLocal<Context> Shell::CreateEvaluationContext(Isolate* isolate) {
4174 // This needs to be a critical section since this is not thread-safe
4175 i::ParkedMutexGuard lock_guard(
4176 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)->main_thread_local_isolate(),
4177 context_mutex_.Pointer());
4178 // Initialize the global objects
4179 Local<ObjectTemplate> global_template = CreateGlobalTemplate(isolate);
4180 EscapableHandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
4181 Local<Context> context = Context::New(isolate, nullptr, global_template);
4182 if (context.IsEmpty()) {
4183 DCHECK(isolate->IsExecutionTerminating());
4184 return {};
4185 }
4186 if (i::v8_flags.perf_prof_annotate_wasm ||
4187 i::v8_flags.vtune_prof_annotate_wasm) {
4188 isolate->SetWasmLoadSourceMapCallback(Shell::WasmLoadSourceMapCallback);
4189 }
4190 InitializeModuleEmbedderData(context);
4191 Context::Scope scope(context);
4192 if (options.include_arguments) {
4193 const std::vector<const char*>& args = options.arguments;
4194 int size = static_cast<int>(args.size());
4195 Local<Array> array = Array::New(isolate, size);
4196 for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
4197 Local<String> arg =
4198 v8::String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, args[i]).ToLocalChecked();
4199 Local<Number> index = v8::Number::New(isolate, i);
4200 array->Set(context, index, arg).FromJust();
4201 }
4202 Local<String> name = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
4203 isolate, "arguments", NewStringType::kInternalized);
4204 context->Global()->Set(context, name, array).FromJust();
4205 }
4206 {
4207 // setup console global.
4208 Local<String> name = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
4209 isolate, "console", NewStringType::kInternalized);
4210 Local<Value> console =
4211 context->GetExtrasBindingObject()->Get(context, name).ToLocalChecked();
4212 context->Global()->Set(context, name, console).FromJust();
4213 }
4214
4215 return handle_scope.Escape(context);
4216}
4217
4218void Shell::WriteIgnitionDispatchCountersFile(v8::Isolate* isolate) {
4219 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
4220 Local<Context> context = Context::New(isolate);
4221 Context::Scope context_scope(context);
4222
4223 i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> dispatch_counters =
4224 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)
4225 ->interpreter()
4226 ->GetDispatchCountersObject();
4227 std::ofstream dispatch_counters_stream(
4228 i::v8_flags.trace_ignition_dispatches_output_file);
4229 dispatch_counters_stream << *String::Utf8Value(
4230 isolate, JSON::Stringify(context, Utils::ToLocal(dispatch_counters))
4231 .ToLocalChecked());
4232}
4233
4234namespace {
4235int LineFromOffset(Local<debug::Script> script, int offset) {
4236 debug::Location location = script->GetSourceLocation(offset);
4237 return location.GetLineNumber();
4238}
4239
4240void WriteLcovDataForRange(std::vector<uint32_t>* lines, int start_line,
4241 int end_line, uint32_t count) {
4242 // Ensure space in the array.
4243 lines->resize(std::max(static_cast<size_t>(end_line + 1), lines->size()), 0);
4244 // Boundary lines could be shared between two functions with different
4245 // invocation counts. Take the maximum.
4246 (*lines)[start_line] = std::max((*lines)[start_line], count);
4247 (*lines)[end_line] = std::max((*lines)[end_line], count);
4248 // Invocation counts for non-boundary lines are overwritten.
4249 for (int k = start_line + 1; k < end_line; k++) (*lines)[k] = count;
4250}
4251
4252void WriteLcovDataForNamedRange(std::ostream& sink,
4253 std::vector<uint32_t>* lines,
4254 const std::string& name, int start_line,
4255 int end_line, uint32_t count) {
4256 WriteLcovDataForRange(lines, start_line, end_line, count);
4257 sink << "FN:" << start_line + 1 << "," << name << std::endl;
4258 sink << "FNDA:" << count << "," << name << std::endl;
4259}
4260} // namespace
4261
4262// Write coverage data in LCOV format. See man page for geninfo(1).
4263void Shell::WriteLcovData(v8::Isolate* isolate, const char* file) {
4264 if (!file) return;
4265 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
4266 debug::Coverage coverage = debug::Coverage::CollectPrecise(isolate);
4267 std::ofstream sink(file, std::ofstream::app);
4268 for (size_t i = 0; i < coverage.ScriptCount(); i++) {
4269 debug::Coverage::ScriptData script_data = coverage.GetScriptData(i);
4270 Local<debug::Script> script = script_data.GetScript();
4271 // Skip unnamed scripts.
4272 Local<String> name;
4273 if (!script->Name().ToLocal(&name)) continue;
4274 std::string file_name = ToSTLString(isolate, name);
4275 // Skip scripts not backed by a file.
4276 if (!std::ifstream(file_name).good()) continue;
4277 sink << "SF:";
4278 sink << NormalizePath(file_name, GetWorkingDirectory()) << std::endl;
4279 std::vector<uint32_t> lines;
4280 for (size_t j = 0; j < script_data.FunctionCount(); j++) {
4281 debug::Coverage::FunctionData function_data =
4282 script_data.GetFunctionData(j);
4283
4284 // Write function stats.
4285 {
4286 debug::Location start =
4287 script->GetSourceLocation(function_data.StartOffset());
4288 debug::Location end =
4289 script->GetSourceLocation(function_data.EndOffset());
4290 int start_line = start.GetLineNumber();
4291 int end_line = end.GetLineNumber();
4292 uint32_t count = function_data.Count();
4293
4294 Local<String> function_name;
4295 std::stringstream name_stream;
4296 if (function_data.Name().ToLocal(&function_name)) {
4297 name_stream << ToSTLString(isolate, function_name);
4298 } else {
4299 name_stream << "<" << start_line + 1 << "-";
4300 name_stream << start.GetColumnNumber() << ">";
4301 }
4302
4303 WriteLcovDataForNamedRange(sink, &lines, name_stream.str(), start_line,
4304 end_line, count);
4305 }
4306
4307 // Process inner blocks.
4308 for (size_t k = 0; k < function_data.BlockCount(); k++) {
4309 debug::Coverage::BlockData block_data = function_data.GetBlockData(k);
4310 int start_line = LineFromOffset(script, block_data.StartOffset());
4311 int end_line = LineFromOffset(script, block_data.EndOffset() - 1);
4312 uint32_t count = block_data.Count();
4313 WriteLcovDataForRange(&lines, start_line, end_line, count);
4314 }
4315 }
4316 // Write per-line coverage. LCOV uses 1-based line numbers.
4317 for (size_t j = 0; j < lines.size(); j++) {
4318 sink << "DA:" << (j + 1) << "," << lines[j] << std::endl;
4319 }
4320 sink << "end_of_record" << std::endl;
4321 }
4322}
4323
4324void Shell::OnExit(v8::Isolate* isolate, bool dispose) {
4325 platform::NotifyIsolateShutdown(g_default_platform, isolate);
4326
4327 if (Worker* worker = Worker::GetCurrentWorker()) {
4328 // When invoking `quit` on a worker isolate, the worker needs to reach
4329 // State::kTerminated before invoking Isolate::Dispose. This is because the
4330 // main thread tries to terminate all workers at the end, which can happen
4331 // concurrently to Isolate::Dispose.
4332 worker->EnterTerminatedState();
4333 }
4334
4335 if (dispose) {
4336 isolate->Dispose();
4337 } else {
4338 // Normally, Dispose() prints counters. Benchmarks expect counters to be
4339 // printed on process exit, so do so manually if not disposing.
4340 isolate->DumpAndResetStats();
4341 }
4342
4343 // Simulate errors before disposing V8, as that resets flags (via
4344 // FlagList::ResetAllFlags()), but error simulation reads the random seed.
4345 if (options.simulate_errors && is_valid_fuzz_script()) {
4346 // Simulate several errors detectable by fuzzers behind a flag if the
4347 // minimum file size for fuzzing was executed.
4348 FuzzerMonitor::SimulateErrors();
4349 }
4350
4351 if (dispose) {
4352 V8::Dispose();
4353 V8::DisposePlatform();
4354 }
4355
4356 if (options.dump_counters || options.dump_counters_nvp) {
4357 base::SharedMutexGuard<base::kShared> mutex_guard(&counter_mutex_);
4358 std::vector<std::pair<std::string, Counter*>> counters(
4359 counter_map_->begin(), counter_map_->end());
4360 std::sort(counters.begin(), counters.end());
4361
4362 if (options.dump_counters_nvp) {
4363 // Dump counters as name-value pairs.
4364 for (const auto& pair : counters) {
4365 std::string key = pair.first;
4366 Counter* counter = pair.second;
4367 if (counter->is_histogram()) {
4368 std::cout << "\"c:" << key << "\"=" << counter->count() << "\n";
4369 std::cout << "\"t:" << key << "\"=" << counter->sample_total()
4370 << "\n";
4371 } else {
4372 std::cout << "\"" << key << "\"=" << counter->count() << "\n";
4373 }
4374 }
4375 } else {
4376 // Dump counters in formatted boxes.
4377 constexpr int kNameBoxSize = 64;
4378 constexpr int kValueBoxSize = 13;
4379 std::cout << "+" << std::string(kNameBoxSize, '-') << "+"
4380 << std::string(kValueBoxSize, '-') << "+\n";
4381 std::cout << "| Name" << std::string(kNameBoxSize - 5, ' ') << "| Value"
4382 << std::string(kValueBoxSize - 6, ' ') << "|\n";
4383 std::cout << "+" << std::string(kNameBoxSize, '-') << "+"
4384 << std::string(kValueBoxSize, '-') << "+\n";
4385 for (const auto& pair : counters) {
4386 std::string key = pair.first;
4387 Counter* counter = pair.second;
4388 if (counter->is_histogram()) {
4389 std::cout << "| c:" << std::setw(kNameBoxSize - 4) << std::left << key
4390 << " | " << std::setw(kValueBoxSize - 2) << std::right
4391 << counter->count() << " |\n";
4392 std::cout << "| t:" << std::setw(kNameBoxSize - 4) << std::left << key
4393 << " | " << std::setw(kValueBoxSize - 2) << std::right
4394 << counter->sample_total() << " |\n";
4395 } else {
4396 std::cout << "| " << std::setw(kNameBoxSize - 2) << std::left << key
4397 << " | " << std::setw(kValueBoxSize - 2) << std::right
4398 << counter->count() << " |\n";
4399 }
4400 }
4401 std::cout << "+" << std::string(kNameBoxSize, '-') << "+"
4402 << std::string(kValueBoxSize, '-') << "+\n";
4403 }
4404 }
4405
4406 if (options.dump_system_memory_stats) {
4407 int peak_memory_usage = base::OS::GetPeakMemoryUsageKb();
4408 std::cout << "System peak memory usage (kb): " << peak_memory_usage
4409 << std::endl;
4410 // TODO(jdapena): call rusage platform independent call, and extract peak
4411 // memory usage to print it
4412 }
4413
4414 // Only delete the counters if we are done executing; after calling `quit`,
4415 // other isolates might still be running and accessing that memory. This is a
4416 // memory leak, which is OK in this case.
4417 if (dispose) {
4418 delete counters_file_;
4419 delete counter_map_;
4420 }
4421}
4422
4423void Dummy(char* arg) {}
4424
4425V8_NOINLINE void FuzzerMonitor::SimulateErrors() {
4426 // Initialize a fresh RNG to not interfere with JS execution.
4427 std::unique_ptr<base::RandomNumberGenerator> rng;
4428 int64_t seed = i::v8_flags.random_seed;
4429 if (seed != 0) {
4430 rng = std::make_unique<base::RandomNumberGenerator>(seed);
4431 } else {
4432 rng = std::make_unique<base::RandomNumberGenerator>();
4433 }
4434
4435 double p = rng->NextDouble();
4436 if (p < 0.1) {
4437 ControlFlowViolation();
4438 } else if (p < 0.2) {
4439 DCheck();
4440 } else if (p < 0.3) {
4441 Fatal();
4442 } else if (p < 0.4) {
4443 ObservableDifference();
4444 } else if (p < 0.5) {
4445 UndefinedBehavior();
4446 } else if (p < 0.6) {
4447 UseAfterFree();
4448 } else if (p < 0.7) {
4449 UseOfUninitializedValue();
4450 }
4451}
4452
4453V8_NOINLINE void FuzzerMonitor::ControlFlowViolation() {
4454 // Control flow violation caught by CFI.
4455 void (*func)() = (void (*)()) & Dummy;
4456 func();
4457}
4458
4459V8_NOINLINE void FuzzerMonitor::DCheck() {
4460 // Caught in debug builds.
4461 DCHECK(false);
4462}
4463
4464V8_NOINLINE void FuzzerMonitor::Fatal() {
4465 // Caught in all build types.
4466 FATAL("Fake error.");
4467}
4468
4469V8_NOINLINE void FuzzerMonitor::ObservableDifference() {
4470 // Observable difference caught by differential fuzzing.
4471 printf("___fake_difference___\n");
4472}
4473
4474V8_NOINLINE void FuzzerMonitor::UndefinedBehavior() {
4475 // Caught by UBSAN.
4476 int32_t val = -1;
4477 USE(val << val);
4478}
4479
4480V8_NOINLINE void FuzzerMonitor::UseAfterFree() {
4481 // Use-after-free caught by ASAN.
4482#if defined(__clang__) // GCC-12 detects this at compile time!
4483 std::vector<bool>* storage = new std::vector<bool>(3);
4484 delete storage;
4485 USE(storage->at(1));
4486#endif
4487}
4488
4489V8_NOINLINE void FuzzerMonitor::UseOfUninitializedValue() {
4490// Use-of-uninitialized-value caught by MSAN.
4491#if defined(__clang__)
4492 int uninitialized[1];
4493 if (uninitialized[0]) USE(uninitialized);
4494#endif
4495}
4496
4497char* Shell::ReadChars(const char* name, int* size_out) {
4498 if (options.read_from_tcp_port >= 0) {
4499 return ReadCharsFromTcpPort(name, size_out);
4500 }
4501
4502 FILE* file = base::OS::FOpen(name, "rb");
4503 if (file == nullptr) return nullptr;
4504
4505 fseek(file, 0, SEEK_END);
4506 size_t size = ftell(file);
4507 rewind(file);
4508
4509 char* chars = new char[size + 1];
4510 chars[size] = '\0';
4511 for (size_t i = 0; i < size;) {
4512 i += fread(&chars[i], 1, size - i, file);
4513 if (ferror(file)) {
4514 base::Fclose(file);
4515 delete[] chars;
4516 return nullptr;
4517 }
4518 }
4519 base::Fclose(file);
4520 *size_out = static_cast<int>(size);
4521 return chars;
4522}
4523
4524MaybeLocal<PrimitiveArray> Shell::ReadLines(Isolate* isolate,
4525 const char* name) {
4526 int length;
4527 std::unique_ptr<char[]> data(ReadChars(name, &length));
4528
4529 if (data.get() == nullptr) {
4530 return MaybeLocal<PrimitiveArray>();
4531 }
4532 std::stringstream stream(data.get());
4533 std::string line;
4534 std::vector<std::string> lines;
4535 while (std::getline(stream, line, '\n')) {
4536 lines.emplace_back(line);
4537 }
4538 // Create a Local<PrimitiveArray> off the read lines.
4539 int size = static_cast<int>(lines.size());
4540 Local<PrimitiveArray> exports = PrimitiveArray::New(isolate, size);
4541 for (int i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
4542 MaybeLocal<String> maybe_str = v8::String::NewFromUtf8(
4543 isolate, lines[i].c_str(), NewStringType::kNormal,
4544 static_cast<int>(lines[i].length()));
4545 Local<String> str;
4546 if (!maybe_str.ToLocal(&str)) {
4547 return MaybeLocal<PrimitiveArray>();
4548 }
4549 exports->Set(isolate, i, str);
4550 }
4551 return exports;
4552}
4553
4554void Shell::ReadBuffer(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
4555 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
4556 static_assert(sizeof(char) == sizeof(uint8_t),
4557 "char and uint8_t should both have 1 byte");
4558 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
4559 String::Utf8Value filename(isolate, info[0]);
4560 int length;
4561 if (*filename == nullptr) {
4562 ThrowError(isolate, "Error loading file");
4563 return;
4564 }
4565
4566 uint8_t* data = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(ReadChars(*filename, &length));
4567 if (data == nullptr) {
4568 ThrowError(isolate, "Error reading file");
4569 return;
4570 }
4571 Local<v8::ArrayBuffer> buffer = ArrayBuffer::New(isolate, length);
4572 memcpy(buffer->GetBackingStore()->Data(), data, length);
4573 delete[] data;
4574
4575 info.GetReturnValue().Set(buffer);
4576}
4577
4578void Shell::ReadLine(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
4579 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
4580 info.GetReturnValue().Set(ReadFromStdin(info.GetIsolate()));
4581}
4582
4583// Reads a file into a memory blob.
4584std::unique_ptr<base::OS::MemoryMappedFile> Shell::ReadFileData(
4585 Isolate* isolate, const char* name, bool should_throw) {
4586 std::unique_ptr<base::OS::MemoryMappedFile> file(
4587 base::OS::MemoryMappedFile::open(
4588 name, base::OS::MemoryMappedFile::FileMode::kReadOnly));
4589 if (!file) {
4590 if (should_throw) {
4591 std::ostringstream oss;
4592 oss << "Error loading file: " << name;
4593 ThrowError(isolate,
4594 v8::String::NewFromUtf8(
4595 isolate, oss.str().substr(0, String::kMaxLength).c_str())
4596 .ToLocalChecked());
4597 }
4598 return nullptr;
4599 }
4600 return file;
4601}
4602
4603// Reads a file into a v8 string.
4604MaybeLocal<String> Shell::ReadFile(Isolate* isolate, const char* name,
4605 bool should_throw) {
4606 auto file = ReadFileData(isolate, name, should_throw);
4607 if (!file) {
4608 return MaybeLocal<String>();
4609 }
4610 int size = static_cast<int>(file->size());
4611 char* chars = static_cast<char*>(file->memory());
4612 if (i::v8_flags.use_external_strings && i::String::IsAscii(chars, size)) {
4613 String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* resource =
4614 new ExternalOwningOneByteStringResource(std::move(file));
4615 return String::NewExternalOneByte(isolate, resource);
4616 }
4617 return String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, chars, NewStringType::kNormal, size);
4618}
4619
4620void Shell::WriteChars(const char* name, uint8_t* buffer, size_t buffer_size) {
4621 FILE* file = base::Fopen(name, "w");
4622 if (file == nullptr) return;
4623 fwrite(buffer, 1, buffer_size, file);
4624 base::Fclose(file);
4625}
4626
4627void Shell::RunShell(Isolate* isolate) {
4628 Global<Context> context;
4629 {
4630 HandleScope scope(isolate);
4631 context.Reset(isolate, Local<Context>::New(isolate, evaluation_context_));
4632 }
4633 PerIsolateData::RealmScope realm_scope(isolate, context);
4634 printf("V8 version %s\n", V8::GetVersion());
4635 while (true) {
4636 Global<Value> global_result;
4637 bool success;
4638 {
4639 HandleScope scope(isolate);
4640 Context::Scope context_scope(context.Get(isolate));
4641 printf("d8> ");
4642 Local<String> input = Shell::ReadFromStdin(isolate);
4643 if (input.IsEmpty()) break;
4644 Local<String> name = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "(d8)");
4645 success = ExecuteString(isolate, input, name, kReportExceptions,
4646 &global_result);
4647 CHECK_EQ(success, !global_result.IsEmpty());
4648 }
4649 if (!FinishExecuting(isolate, context)) success = false;
4650 if (success) {
4651 HandleScope scope(isolate);
4652 Context::Scope context_scope(context.Get(isolate));
4653 Local<Value> result = global_result.Get(isolate);
4654 if (options.test_shell) {
4655 if (!result->IsUndefined()) {
4656 // If all went well and the result wasn't undefined then print
4657 // the returned value.
4658 v8::String::Utf8Value str(isolate, result);
4659 fwrite(*str, sizeof(**str), str.length(), stdout);
4660 printf("\n");
4661 }
4662 } else {
4663 v8::String::Utf8Value str(isolate, Stringify(isolate, result));
4664 fwrite(*str, sizeof(**str), str.length(), stdout);
4665 printf("\n");
4666 }
4667 }
4668 }
4669 printf("\n");
4670}
4671
4672class InspectorFrontend final : public v8_inspector::V8Inspector::Channel {
4673 public:
4674 explicit InspectorFrontend(Local<Context> context) {
4675 isolate_ = context->GetIsolate();
4676 context_.Reset(isolate_, context);
4677 }
4678 ~InspectorFrontend() override = default;
4679
4680 private:
4681 void sendResponse(
4682 int callId,
4683 std::unique_ptr<v8_inspector::StringBuffer> message) override {
4684 Send(message->string());
4685 }
4686 void sendNotification(
4687 std::unique_ptr<v8_inspector::StringBuffer> message) override {
4688 Send(message->string());
4689 }
4690 void flushProtocolNotifications() override {}
4691
4692 void Send(const v8_inspector::StringView& string) {
4693 v8::Isolate::AllowJavascriptExecutionScope allow_script(isolate_);
4694 v8::HandleScope handle_scope(isolate_);
4695 int length = static_cast<int>(string.length());
4696 DCHECK_LT(length, v8::String::kMaxLength);
4697 Local<String> message =
4698 (string.is8Bit()
4699 ? v8::String::NewFromOneByte(
4700 isolate_,
4701 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(string.characters8()),
4702 v8::NewStringType::kNormal, length)
4703 : v8::String::NewFromTwoByte(
4704 isolate_,
4705 reinterpret_cast<const uint16_t*>(string.characters16()),
4706 v8::NewStringType::kNormal, length))
4707 .ToLocalChecked();
4708 Local<String> callback_name = v8::String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
4709 isolate_, "receive", NewStringType::kInternalized);
4710 Local<Context> context = context_.Get(isolate_);
4711 Local<Value> callback =
4712 context->Global()->Get(context, callback_name).ToLocalChecked();
4713 if (callback->IsFunction()) {
4714 v8::TryCatch try_catch(isolate_);
4715 Local<Value> args[] = {message};
4716 USE(callback.As<Function>()->Call(context, Undefined(isolate_), 1, args));
4717#ifdef DEBUG
4718 if (try_catch.HasCaught()) {
4719 Local<Object> exception = try_catch.Exception().As<Object>();
4720 Local<String> key = v8::String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
4721 isolate_, "message", NewStringType::kInternalized);
4722 Local<String> expected = v8::String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
4723 isolate_, "Maximum call stack size exceeded");
4724 Local<Value> value = exception->Get(context, key).ToLocalChecked();
4725 DCHECK(value->StrictEquals(expected));
4726 }
4727#endif
4728 }
4729 }
4730
4731 Isolate* isolate_;
4732 Global<Context> context_;
4733};
4734
4735class InspectorClient : public v8_inspector::V8InspectorClient {
4736 public:
4737 InspectorClient(Isolate* isolate, const Global<Context>& global_context,
4738 bool connect) {
4739 if (!connect) return;
4740 isolate_ = isolate;
4741 Local<Context> context = global_context.Get(isolate);
4742 channel_.reset(new InspectorFrontend(context));
4743 inspector_ = v8_inspector::V8Inspector::create(isolate_, this);
4744 session_ =
4745 inspector_->connect(1, channel_.get(), v8_inspector::StringView(),
4746 v8_inspector::V8Inspector::kFullyTrusted,
4747 v8_inspector::V8Inspector::kNotWaitingForDebugger);
4748 context->SetAlignedPointerInEmbedderData(kInspectorClientIndex, this);
4749 inspector_->contextCreated(v8_inspector::V8ContextInfo(
4750 context, kContextGroupId, v8_inspector::StringView()));
4751
4752 Local<Value> function =
4753 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate_, SendInspectorMessage)
4754 ->GetFunction(context)
4755 .ToLocalChecked();
4756 Local<String> function_name = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
4757 isolate_, "send", NewStringType::kInternalized);
4758 CHECK(context->Global()->Set(context, function_name, function).FromJust());
4759
4760 context_.Reset(isolate_, global_context);
4761 }
4762
4763 void runMessageLoopOnPause(int contextGroupId) override {
4764 v8::Isolate::AllowJavascriptExecutionScope allow_script(isolate_);
4765 v8::HandleScope handle_scope(isolate_);
4766 Local<String> callback_name = v8::String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
4767 isolate_, "handleInspectorMessage", NewStringType::kInternalized);
4768 Local<Context> context = context_.Get(isolate_);
4769 Local<Value> callback =
4770 context->Global()->Get(context, callback_name).ToLocalChecked();
4771 if (!callback->IsFunction()) return;
4772
4773 // Running the message loop below may trigger the execution of a stackless
4774 // GC. We need to override the embedder stack state, to force scanning the
4775 // stack, if this happens.
4776 i::Heap* heap = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate_)->heap();
4777 i::EmbedderStackStateScope stack_scanning_scope(
4778 heap, i::EmbedderStackStateOrigin::kExplicitInvocation,
4779 v8::StackState::kMayContainHeapPointers);
4780
4781 v8::TryCatch try_catch(isolate_);
4782 try_catch.SetVerbose(true);
4783 is_paused = true;
4784
4785 while (is_paused) {
4786 USE(callback.As<Function>()->Call(context, Undefined(isolate_), 0, {}));
4787 if (try_catch.HasCaught()) {
4788 is_paused = false;
4789 }
4790 }
4791 }
4792
4793 void quitMessageLoopOnPause() override { is_paused = false; }
4794
4795 private:
4796 static v8_inspector::V8InspectorSession* GetSession(Local<Context> context) {
4797 InspectorClient* inspector_client = static_cast<InspectorClient*>(
4798 context->GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(kInspectorClientIndex));
4799 return inspector_client->session_.get();
4800 }
4801
4802 Local<Context> ensureDefaultContextInGroup(int group_id) override {
4803 DCHECK(isolate_);
4804 DCHECK_EQ(kContextGroupId, group_id);
