4805 return context_.Get(isolate_);
4806 }
4807
4808 static void SendInspectorMessage(
4809 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
4810 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
4811 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
4812 v8::HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
4813 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
4814 info.GetReturnValue().Set(Undefined(isolate));
4815 Local<String> message = info[0]->ToString(context).ToLocalChecked();
4816 v8_inspector::V8InspectorSession* session =
4817 InspectorClient::GetSession(context);
4818 uint32_t length = message->Length();
4819 std::unique_ptr<uint16_t[]> buffer(new uint16_t[length]);
4820 message->WriteV2(isolate, 0, length, buffer.get());
4821 v8_inspector::StringView message_view(buffer.get(), length);
4822 {
4823 v8::SealHandleScope seal_handle_scope(isolate);
4824 session->dispatchProtocolMessage(message_view);
4825 }
4826 info.GetReturnValue().Set(True(isolate));
4827 }
4828
4829 static const int kContextGroupId = 1;
4830
4831 std::unique_ptr<v8_inspector::V8Inspector> inspector_;
4832 std::unique_ptr<v8_inspector::V8InspectorSession> session_;
4833 std::unique_ptr<v8_inspector::V8Inspector::Channel> channel_;
4834 bool is_paused = false;
4835 Global<Context> context_;
4836 Isolate* isolate_;
4837};
4838
4839SourceGroup::~SourceGroup() {
4840 delete thread_;
4841 thread_ = nullptr;
4842}
4843
4844bool ends_with(const char* input, const char* suffix) {
4845 size_t input_length = strlen(input);
4846 size_t suffix_length = strlen(suffix);
4847 if (suffix_length <= input_length) {
4848 return strcmp(input + input_length - suffix_length, suffix) == 0;
4849 }
4850 return false;
4851}
4852
4853bool SourceGroup::Execute(Isolate* isolate) {
4854 bool success = true;
4855#ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
4856 if (fuzzilli_reprl) {
4857 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
4858 Local<String> file_name =
4859 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, "fuzzcode.js", NewStringType::kNormal)
4860 .ToLocalChecked();
4861
4862 size_t script_size;
4863 CHECK_EQ(read(REPRL_CRFD, &script_size, 8), 8);
4864 char* buffer = new char[script_size + 1];
4865 char* ptr = buffer;
4866 size_t remaining = script_size;
4867 while (remaining > 0) {
4868 ssize_t rv = read(REPRL_DRFD, ptr, remaining);
4869 CHECK_GE(rv, 0);
4870 remaining -= rv;
4871 ptr += rv;
4872 }
4873 buffer[script_size] = 0;
4874
4875 Local<String> source =
4876 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, buffer, NewStringType::kNormal)
4877 .ToLocalChecked();
4878 delete[] buffer;
4879 Shell::set_script_executed();
4880 if (!Shell::ExecuteString(isolate, source, file_name,
4881 Shell::kReportExceptions)) {
4882 return false;
4883 }
4884 }
4885#endif // V8_FUZZILLI
4886 for (int i = begin_offset_; i < end_offset_; ++i) {
4887 const char* arg = argv_[i];
4888 if (strcmp(arg, "-e") == 0 && i + 1 < end_offset_) {
4889 // Execute argument given to -e option directly.
4890 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
4891 Local<String> file_name = String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate, "unnamed");
4892 Local<String> source =
4893 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, argv_[i + 1]).ToLocalChecked();
4894 Shell::set_script_executed();
4895 if (!Shell::ExecuteString(isolate, source, file_name,
4896 Shell::kReportExceptions)) {
4897 success = false;
4898 break;
4899 }
4900 ++i;
4901 continue;
4902 } else if (ends_with(arg, ".mjs")) {
4903 Shell::set_script_executed();
4904 if (!Shell::ExecuteModule(isolate, arg)) {
4905 success = false;
4906 break;
4907 }
4908 continue;
4909 } else if (strcmp(arg, "--module") == 0 && i + 1 < end_offset_) {
4910 // Treat the next file as a module.
4911 arg = argv_[++i];
4912 Shell::set_script_executed();
4913 if (!Shell::ExecuteModule(isolate, arg)) {
4914 success = false;
4915 break;
4916 }
4917 continue;
4918 } else if (strcmp(arg, "--json") == 0 && i + 1 < end_offset_) {
4919 // Treat the next file as a JSON file.
4920 arg = argv_[++i];
4921 Shell::set_script_executed();
4922 if (!Shell::LoadJSON(isolate, arg)) {
4923 success = false;
4924 break;
4925 }
4926 continue;
4927 } else if (arg[0] == '-') {
4928 // Ignore other options. They have been parsed already.
4929 continue;
4930 }
4931
4932 // Use all other arguments as names of files to load and run.
4933 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
4934 Local<String> file_name =
4935 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate, arg).ToLocalChecked();
4936 Local<String> source;
4937 if (!Shell::ReadFile(isolate, arg).ToLocal(&source)) {
4938 printf("Error reading '%s'\n", arg);
4939 base::OS::ExitProcess(1);
4940 }
4941 Shell::set_script_executed();
4942 Shell::update_script_size(source->Length());
4943 if (!Shell::ExecuteString(isolate, source, file_name,
4944 Shell::kReportExceptions)) {
4945 success = false;
4946 break;
4947 }
4948 }
4949 return success;
4950}
4951
4952SourceGroup::IsolateThread::IsolateThread(SourceGroup* group)
4953 : base::Thread(GetThreadOptions("IsolateThread")), group_(group) {}
4954
4955void SourceGroup::ExecuteInThread() {
4956 Isolate::CreateParams create_params;
4957 create_params.array_buffer_allocator = Shell::array_buffer_allocator;
4958 Isolate* isolate = Isolate::New(create_params);
4959
4960 {
4961 Isolate::Scope isolate_scope(isolate);
4962 D8Console console(isolate);
4963 Shell::Initialize(isolate, &console, false);
4964 PerIsolateData data(isolate);
4965
4966 for (int i = 0; i < Shell::options.stress_runs; ++i) {
4967 next_semaphore_.ParkedWait(
4968 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)->main_thread_local_isolate());
4969 {
4970 Global<Context> global_context;
4971 HandleScope scope(isolate);
4972 {
4973 Local<Context> context;
4974 if (!Shell::CreateEvaluationContext(isolate).ToLocal(&context)) {
4975 DCHECK(isolate->IsExecutionTerminating());
4976 break;
4977 }
4978 global_context.Reset(isolate, context);
4979 }
4980 PerIsolateData::RealmScope realm_scope(isolate, global_context);
4981 InspectorClient inspector_client(isolate, global_context,
4982 Shell::options.enable_inspector);
4983 {
4984 // We cannot use a Context::Scope here, as it keeps a local handle to
4985 // the context and SourceGroup::Execute may execute a non-nestable
4986 // task, e.g. a stackless GC.
4987 global_context.Get(isolate)->Enter();
4988 Execute(isolate);
4989 global_context.Get(isolate)->Exit();
4990 }
4991 Shell::FinishExecuting(isolate, global_context);
4992 }
4993 Shell::CollectGarbage(isolate);
4994 done_semaphore_.Signal();
4995 }
4996
4997 Shell::ResetOnProfileEndListener(isolate);
4998 }
4999
5000 isolate->Dispose();
5001}
5002
5003void SourceGroup::StartExecuteInThread() {
5004 if (thread_ == nullptr) {
5005 thread_ = new IsolateThread(this);
5006 CHECK(thread_->Start());
5007 }
5008 next_semaphore_.Signal();
5009}
5010
5011void SourceGroup::WaitForThread(const i::ParkedScope& parked) {
5012 if (thread_ == nullptr) return;
5013 done_semaphore_.ParkedWait(parked);
5014}
5015
5016void SourceGroup::JoinThread(const i::ParkedScope& parked) {
5017 USE(parked);
5018 if (thread_ == nullptr) return;
5019 thread_->Join();
5020}
5021
5022void SerializationDataQueue::Enqueue(std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data) {
5023 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&mutex_);
5024 data_.push_back(std::move(data));
5025}
5026
5027bool SerializationDataQueue::Dequeue(
5028 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData>* out_data) {
5029 out_data->reset();
5030 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&mutex_);
5031 if (data_.empty()) return false;
5032 *out_data = std::move(data_[0]);
5033 data_.erase(data_.begin());
5034 return true;
5035}
5036
5037bool SerializationDataQueue::IsEmpty() {
5038 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&mutex_);
5039 return data_.empty();
5040}
5041
5042void SerializationDataQueue::Clear() {
5043 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&mutex_);
5044 data_.clear();
5045}
5046
5047Worker::Worker(Isolate* parent_isolate, const char* script)
5048 : script_(i::StrDup(script)), parent_isolate_(parent_isolate) {
5049 state_.store(State::kReady);
5050}
5051
5052Worker::~Worker() {
5053 CHECK(state_.load() == State::kTerminated);
5054 DCHECK_NULL(isolate_);
5055 delete thread_;
5056 thread_ = nullptr;
5057 delete[] script_;
5058 script_ = nullptr;
5059}
5060
5061bool Worker::is_running() const { return state_.load() == State::kRunning; }
5062
5063bool Worker::StartWorkerThread(Isolate* requester,
5064 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker,
5065 base::Thread::Priority priority) {
5066 auto expected = State::kReady;
5067 CHECK(
5068 worker->state_.compare_exchange_strong(expected, State::kPrepareRunning));
5069 auto thread = new WorkerThread(worker, priority);
5070 worker->thread_ = thread;
5071 if (!thread->Start()) return false;
5072 // Wait until the worker is ready to receive messages.
5073 worker->started_semaphore_.ParkedWait(
5074 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(requester)->main_thread_local_isolate());
5075 Shell::AddRunningWorker(std::move(worker));
5076 return true;
5077}
5078
5079void Worker::WorkerThread::Run() {
5080 // Prevent a lifetime cycle from Worker -> WorkerThread -> Worker.
5081 // We must clear the worker_ field of the thread, but we keep the
5082 // worker alive via a stack root until the thread finishes execution
5083 // and removes itself from the running set. Thereafter the only
5084 // remaining reference can be from a JavaScript object via a Managed.
5085 auto worker = std::move(worker_);
5086 worker_ = nullptr;
5087 worker->ExecuteInThread();
5088 Shell::RemoveRunningWorker(worker);
5089}
5090
5091class ProcessMessageTask : public i::CancelableTask {
5092 public:
5093 ProcessMessageTask(i::CancelableTaskManager* task_manager,
5094 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker,
5095 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data)
5096 : i::CancelableTask(task_manager),
5097 worker_(worker),
5098 data_(std::move(data)) {}
5099
5100 void RunInternal() override { worker_->ProcessMessage(std::move(data_)); }
5101
5102 private:
5103 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker_;
5104 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data_;
5105};
5106
5107void Worker::PostMessage(std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data) {
5108 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&worker_mutex_);
5109 if (!is_running()) return;
5110 std::unique_ptr<v8::Task> task(new ProcessMessageTask(
5111 task_manager_, shared_from_this(), std::move(data)));
5112 task_runner_->PostNonNestableTask(std::move(task));
5113}
5114
5115class TerminateTask : public i::CancelableTask {
5116 public:
5117 TerminateTask(i::CancelableTaskManager* task_manager,
5118 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker)
5119 : i::CancelableTask(task_manager), worker_(worker) {}
5120
5121 void RunInternal() override {
5122 auto expected = Worker::State::kTerminating;
5123 CHECK(worker_->state_.compare_exchange_strong(expected,
5124 Worker::State::kTerminated));
5125 }
5126
5127 private:
5128 std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker_;
5129};
5130
5131std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> Worker::GetMessage(Isolate* requester) {
5132 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> result;
5133 while (!out_queue_.Dequeue(&result)) {
5134 // If the worker is no longer running, and there are no messages in the
5135 // queue, don't expect any more messages from it.
5136 if (!is_running()) break;
5137 out_semaphore_.ParkedWait(
5138 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(requester)->main_thread_local_isolate());
5139 }
5140 return result;
5141}
5142
5143std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> Worker::TryGetMessage() {
5144 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> result;
5145 if (!out_queue_.Dequeue(&result)) {
5146 return nullptr;
5147 }
5148 return result;
5149}
5150
5151void Worker::TerminateAndWaitForThread(const i::ParkedScope& parked) {
5152 USE(parked);
5153 Terminate();
5154 {
5155 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&worker_mutex_);
5156 // Prevent double-joining.
5157 if (is_joined_) return;
5158 is_joined_ = true;
5159 }
5160 thread_->Join();
5161}
5162
5163void Worker::Terminate() {
5164 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&worker_mutex_);
5165 auto expected = State::kRunning;
5166 if (!state_.compare_exchange_strong(expected, State::kTerminating)) return;
5167 std::unique_ptr<v8::Task> task(
5168 new TerminateTask(task_manager_, shared_from_this()));
5169 task_runner_->PostTask(std::move(task));
5170 // Also schedule an interrupt in case the worker is running code and never
5171 // returning to the event queue. Since we checked the state before, and we are
5172 // holding the {worker_mutex_}, it's safe to access the isolate.
5173 isolate_->TerminateExecution();
5174}
5175
5176void Worker::EnterTerminatedState() {
5177 base::SpinningMutexGuard lock_guard(&worker_mutex_);
5178 state_.store(State::kTerminated);
5179 CHECK(!is_running());
5180 task_runner_.reset();
5181 task_manager_ = nullptr;
5182}
5183
5184void Worker::ProcessMessage(std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data) {
5185 if (!is_running()) return;
5186 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate_);
5187 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
5188 Local<Context> context = context_.Get(isolate_);
5189 Context::Scope context_scope(context);
5190 Local<Object> global = context->Global();
5191
5192 // Get the message handler.
5193 MaybeLocal<Value> maybe_onmessage = global->Get(
5194 context, String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate_, "onmessage",
5195 NewStringType::kInternalized));
5196 Local<Value> onmessage;
5197 if (!maybe_onmessage.ToLocal(&onmessage) || !onmessage->IsFunction()) return;
5198 Local<Function> onmessage_fun = onmessage.As<Function>();
5199
5200 v8::TryCatch try_catch(isolate_);
5201 try_catch.SetVerbose(true);
5202 Local<Value> value;
5203 if (Shell::DeserializeValue(isolate_, std::move(data)).ToLocal(&value)) {
5204 DCHECK(!isolate_->IsExecutionTerminating());
5205 Local<Object> event = Object::New(isolate_);
5206 event
5207 ->CreateDataProperty(
5208 context,
5209 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate_, "data",
5210 NewStringType::kInternalized),
5211 value)
5212 .ToChecked();
5213 Local<Value> argv[] = {event};
5214 MaybeLocal<Value> result = onmessage_fun->Call(context, global, 1, argv);
5215 USE(result);
5216 }
5217 if (isolate_->IsExecutionTerminating()) {
5218 // Re-schedule an interrupt in case the worker is going to run more code
5219 // and never return to the event queue.
5220 isolate_->TerminateExecution();
5221 }
5222}
5223
5224void Worker::ProcessMessages() {
5225 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate_);
5226 i::SaveAndSwitchContext saved_context(i_isolate, i::Context());
5227 SealHandleScope shs(isolate_);
5228
5229 TryCatch try_catch(isolate_);
5230 try_catch.SetVerbose(true);
5231
5232 while (is_running() && v8::platform::PumpMessageLoop(
5233 g_default_platform, isolate_,
5234 platform::MessageLoopBehavior::kWaitForWork)) {
5235 if (try_catch.HasCaught()) return;
5236 if (is_running()) {
5237 MicrotasksScope::PerformCheckpoint(isolate_);
5238 }
5239 }
5240}
5241
5242// static
5243void Worker::SetCurrentWorker(Worker* worker) {
5244 CHECK_NULL(current_worker_);
5245 current_worker_ = worker;
5246}
5247
5248// static
5249Worker* Worker::GetCurrentWorker() { return current_worker_; }
5250
5251void Worker::ExecuteInThread() {
5252 Isolate::CreateParams create_params;
5253 create_params.array_buffer_allocator = Shell::array_buffer_allocator;
5254 isolate_ = Isolate::New(create_params);
5255
5256 // Make the Worker instance available to the whole thread.
5257 SetCurrentWorker(this);
5258
5259 task_runner_ = g_default_platform->GetForegroundTaskRunner(isolate_);
5260 task_manager_ =
5261 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate_)->cancelable_task_manager();
5262
5263 auto expected = State::kPrepareRunning;
5264 CHECK(state_.compare_exchange_strong(expected, State::kRunning));
5265
5266 // The Worker is now ready to receive messages.
5267 started_semaphore_.Signal();
5268
5269 {
5270 Isolate::Scope isolate_scope(isolate_);
5271 D8Console console(isolate_);
5272 Shell::Initialize(isolate_, &console, false);
5273 PerIsolateData data(isolate_);
5274
5275 CHECK(context_.IsEmpty());
5276
5277 {
5278 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
5279 Local<Context> context;
5280 if (Shell::CreateEvaluationContext(isolate_).ToLocal(&context)) {
5281 context_.Reset(isolate_, context);
5282 CHECK(!context_.IsEmpty());
5283 }
5284 }
5285
5286 if (!context_.IsEmpty()) {
5287 {
5288 bool success;
5289 PerIsolateData::RealmScope realm_scope(isolate_, context_);
5290 {
5291 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
5292 Local<Context> context = context_.Get(isolate_);
5293 Context::Scope context_scope(context);
5294
5295 Local<Object> global = context->Global();
5296 Local<Value> this_value = External::New(isolate_, this);
5297
5298 Local<FunctionTemplate> postmessage_fun_template =
5299 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate_, Worker::PostMessageOut,
5300 this_value);
5301 Local<Function> postmessage_fun;
5302 if (postmessage_fun_template->GetFunction(context).ToLocal(
5303 &postmessage_fun)) {
5304 global
5305 ->Set(
5306 context,
5307 v8::String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
5308 isolate_, "postMessage", NewStringType::kInternalized),
5309 postmessage_fun)
5310 .FromJust();
5311 }
5312
5313 Local<FunctionTemplate> close_fun_template =
5314 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate_, Worker::Close, this_value);
5315 Local<Function> close_fun;
5316 if (close_fun_template->GetFunction(context).ToLocal(&close_fun)) {
5317 global
5318 ->Set(context,
5319 v8::String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
5320 isolate_, "close", NewStringType::kInternalized),
5321 close_fun)
5322 .FromJust();
5323 }
5324
5325 Local<FunctionTemplate> importScripts_fun_template =
5326 FunctionTemplate::New(isolate_, Worker::ImportScripts,
5327 this_value);
5328 Local<Function> importScripts_fun;
5329 if (importScripts_fun_template->GetFunction(context).ToLocal(
5330 &importScripts_fun)) {
5331 global
5332 ->Set(context,
5333 v8::String::NewFromUtf8Literal(
5334 isolate_, "importScripts",
5335 NewStringType::kInternalized),
5336 importScripts_fun)
5337 .FromJust();
5338 }
5339
5340 // First run the script
5341 Local<String> file_name =
5342 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate_, "unnamed");
5343 Local<String> source =
5344 String::NewFromUtf8(isolate_, script_).ToLocalChecked();
5345 success = Shell::ExecuteString(isolate_, source, file_name,
5346 Shell::kReportExceptions);
5347 }
5348 if (!Shell::FinishExecuting(isolate_, context_)) success = false;
5349 if (success) {
5350 bool handler_present;
5351 {
5352 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
5353 Local<Context> context = context_.Get(isolate_);
5354 Context::Scope context_scope(context);
5355 Local<Object> global = context->Global();
5356 // Check that there's a message handler
5357 MaybeLocal<Value> maybe_onmessage = global->Get(
5358 context,
5359 String::NewFromUtf8Literal(isolate_, "onmessage",
5360 NewStringType::kInternalized));
5361 Local<Value> onmessage;
5362 handler_present =
5363 maybe_onmessage.ToLocal(&onmessage) && onmessage->IsFunction();
5364 }
5365 if (handler_present) {
5366 // Now wait for messages.
5367 ProcessMessages();
5368 }
5369 }
5370 }
5371 Shell::CollectGarbage(isolate_);
5372 }
5373
5374 EnterTerminatedState();
5375
5376 Shell::ResetOnProfileEndListener(isolate_);
5377 context_.Reset();
5378 platform::NotifyIsolateShutdown(g_default_platform, isolate_);
5379 }
5380
5381 isolate_->Dispose();
5382 isolate_ = nullptr;
5383
5384 // Post nullptr to wake the thread waiting on GetMessage() if there is one.
5385 out_queue_.Enqueue(nullptr);
5386 out_semaphore_.Signal();
5387 // Also post an cleanup task to the parent isolate, so that it sees that this
5388 // worker is terminated and can clean it up in a thread-safe way.
5389 g_platform->GetForegroundTaskRunner(parent_isolate_)
5390 ->PostTask(std::make_unique<CleanUpWorkerTask>(parent_isolate_,
5391 this->shared_from_this()));
5392}
5393
5394void Worker::PostMessageOut(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
5395 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
5396 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
5397 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
5398
5399 if (info.Length() < 1) {
5400 ThrowError(isolate, "Invalid argument");
5401 return;
5402 }
5403
5404 Local<Value> message = info[0];
5405 Local<Value> transfer = Undefined(isolate);
5406 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data =
5407 Shell::SerializeValue(isolate, message, transfer);
5408 if (data) {
5409 DCHECK(info.Data()->IsExternal());
5410 Local<External> this_value = info.Data().As<External>();
5411 Worker* worker = static_cast<Worker*>(this_value->Value());
5412
5413 worker->out_queue_.Enqueue(std::move(data));
5414 worker->out_semaphore_.Signal();
5415 g_platform->GetForegroundTaskRunner(worker->parent_isolate_)
5416 ->PostTask(std::make_unique<CheckMessageFromWorkerTask>(
5417 worker->parent_isolate_, worker->shared_from_this()));
5418 }
5419}
5420
5421void Worker::ImportScripts(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
5422 Shell::ExecuteFile(info);
5423}
5424
5425void Worker::Close(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
5426 DCHECK(i::ValidateCallbackInfo(info));
5427 Isolate* isolate = info.GetIsolate();
5428 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
5429 DCHECK(info.Data()->IsExternal());
5430 Local<External> this_value = info.Data().As<External>();
5431 Worker* worker = static_cast<Worker*>(this_value->Value());
5432 worker->Terminate();
5433}
5434
5435#ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_WIN
5436// Enable support for unicode filename path on windows.
5437// We first convert ansi encoded argv[i] to utf16 encoded, and then
5438// convert utf16 encoded to utf8 encoded with setting the argv[i]
5439// to the utf8 encoded arg. We allocate memory for the utf8 encoded
5440// arg, and we will free it and reset it to nullptr after using
5441// the filename path arg. And because Execute may be called multiple
5442// times, we need to free the allocated unicode filename when exit.
5443
5444// Save the allocated utf8 filenames, and we will free them when exit.
5445std::vector<char*> utf8_filenames;
5446#include <shellapi.h>
5447// Convert utf-16 encoded string to utf-8 encoded.
5448char* ConvertUtf16StringToUtf8(const wchar_t* str) {
5449 // On Windows wchar_t must be a 16-bit value.
5450 static_assert(sizeof(wchar_t) == 2, "wrong wchar_t size");
5451 int len =
5452 WideCharToMultiByte(CP_UTF8, 0, str, -1, nullptr, 0, nullptr, FALSE);
5453 DCHECK_LT(0, len);
5454 char* utf8_str = new char[len];
5455 utf8_filenames.push_back(utf8_str);
5456 WideCharToMultiByte(CP_UTF8, 0, str, -1, utf8_str, len, nullptr, FALSE);
5457 return utf8_str;
5458}
5459
5460// Convert ansi encoded argv[i] to utf8 encoded.
5461void PreProcessUnicodeFilenameArg(char* argv[], int i) {
5462 int argc;
5463 wchar_t** wargv = CommandLineToArgvW(GetCommandLineW(), &argc);
5464 argv[i] = ConvertUtf16StringToUtf8(wargv[i]);
5465 LocalFree(wargv);
5466}
5467
5468#endif
5469
5470namespace {
5471
5472bool FlagMatches(const char* flag, char** arg, bool keep_flag = false) {
5473 if (strcmp(*arg, flag) == 0) {
5474 if (!keep_flag) {
5475 *arg = nullptr;
5476 }
5477 return true;
5478 }
5479 return false;
5480}
5481
5482template <size_t N>
5483bool FlagWithArgMatches(const char (&flag)[N], char** flag_value, int argc,
5484 char* argv[], int* i) {
5485 char* current_arg = argv[*i];
5486
5487 // Compare the flag up to the last character of the flag name (not including
5488 // the null terminator).
5489 if (strncmp(current_arg, flag, N - 1) == 0) {
5490 // Match against --flag=value
5491 if (current_arg[N - 1] == '=') {
5492 *flag_value = argv[*i] + N;
5493 argv[*i] = nullptr;
5494 return true;
5495 }
5496 // Match against --flag value
5497 if (current_arg[N - 1] == '\0') {
5498 CHECK_LT(*i, argc - 1);
5499 argv[*i] = nullptr;
5500 (*i)++;
5501 *flag_value = argv[*i];
5502 argv[*i] = nullptr;
5503 return true;
5504 }
5505 }
5506
5507 flag_value = nullptr;
5508 return false;
5509}
5510
5511} // namespace
5512
5513bool Shell::SetOptions(int argc, char* argv[]) {
5514 bool logfile_per_isolate = false;
5515 options.d8_path = argv[0];
5516 for (int i = 0; i < argc; i++) {
5517 char* flag_value = nullptr;
5518 if (FlagMatches("--", &argv[i])) {
5519 i++;
5520 for (; i < argc; i++) {
5521 options.arguments.push_back(argv[i]);
5522 argv[i] = nullptr;
5523 }
5524 break;
5525 } else if (FlagMatches("--no-arguments", &argv[i])) {
5526 options.include_arguments = false;
5527 } else if (FlagMatches("--simulate-errors", &argv[i])) {
5528 options.simulate_errors = true;
5529 } else if (FlagMatches("--fuzzing", &argv[i], /*keep_flag=*/true) ||
5530 FlagMatches("--no-abort-on-contradictory-flags", &argv[i],
5531 /*keep_flag=*/true) ||
5532 FlagMatches("--noabort-on-contradictory-flags", &argv[i],
5533 /*keep_flag=*/true)) {
5534 check_d8_flag_contradictions = false;
5535 } else if (FlagMatches("--abort-on-contradictory-flags", &argv[i],
5536 /*keep_flag=*/true)) {
5537 check_d8_flag_contradictions = true;
5538 } else if (FlagMatches("--logfile-per-isolate", &argv[i])) {
5539 logfile_per_isolate = true;
5540 } else if (FlagMatches("--shell", &argv[i])) {
5541 options.interactive_shell = true;
5542 } else if (FlagMatches("--test", &argv[i])) {
5543 options.test_shell = true;
5544 } else if (FlagMatches("--notest", &argv[i]) ||
5545 FlagMatches("--no-test", &argv[i])) {
5546 options.test_shell = false;
5547 } else if (FlagMatches("--send-idle-notification", &argv[i])) {
5548 options.send_idle_notification = true;
5549 } else if (FlagMatches("--invoke-weak-callbacks", &argv[i])) {
5550 options.invoke_weak_callbacks = true;
5551 // TODO(v8:3351): Invoking weak callbacks does not always collect all
5552 // available garbage.
5553 options.send_idle_notification = true;
5554 } else if (FlagMatches("--omit-quit", &argv[i])) {
5555 options.omit_quit = true;
5556 } else if (FlagMatches("--no-wait-for-background-tasks", &argv[i])) {
5557 // TODO(herhut) Remove this flag once wasm compilation is fully
5558 // isolate-independent.
5559 options.wait_for_background_tasks = false;
5560 } else if (FlagMatches("-f", &argv[i], /*keep_flag=*/true)) {
5561 // Ignore any -f flags for compatibility with other stand-alone
5562 // JavaScript engines.
5563 continue;
5564 } else if (FlagMatches("--ignore-unhandled-promises", &argv[i])) {
5565 options.ignore_unhandled_promises = true;
5566 } else if (FlagMatches("--isolate", &argv[i], /*keep_flag=*/true)) {
5567 options.num_isolates++;
5568 } else if (FlagMatches("--throws", &argv[i])) {
5569 options.expected_to_throw = true;
5570 } else if (FlagMatches("--no-fail", &argv[i])) {
5571 options.no_fail = true;
5572 } else if (FlagMatches("--dump-counters", &argv[i])) {
5573 i::v8_flags.slow_histograms = true;
5574 options.dump_counters = true;
5575 } else if (FlagMatches("--dump-counters-nvp", &argv[i])) {
5576 i::v8_flags.slow_histograms = true;
5577 options.dump_counters_nvp = true;
5578 } else if (FlagMatches("--dump-system-memory-stats", &argv[i])) {
5579 options.dump_system_memory_stats = true;
5580 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--icu-data-file", &flag_value, argc, argv,
5581 &i)) {
5582 options.icu_data_file = flag_value;
5583 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--icu-locale", &flag_value, argc, argv,
5584 &i)) {
5585 options.icu_locale = flag_value;
5586#ifdef V8_USE_EXTERNAL_STARTUP_DATA
5587 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--snapshot_blob", &flag_value, argc, argv,
5588 &i)) {
5589 options.snapshot_blob = flag_value;
5590#endif // V8_USE_EXTERNAL_STARTUP_DATA
5591 } else if (FlagMatches("--cache", &argv[i]) ||
5592 FlagWithArgMatches("--cache", &flag_value, argc, argv, &i)) {
5593 if (!flag_value || strcmp(flag_value, "code") == 0) {
5594 options.compile_options = v8::ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions;
5595 options.code_cache_options =
5596 ShellOptions::CodeCacheOptions::kProduceCache;
5597 } else if (strcmp(flag_value, "none") == 0) {
5598 options.compile_options = v8::ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions;
5599 options.code_cache_options = ShellOptions::kNoProduceCache;
5600 } else if (strcmp(flag_value, "after-execute") == 0) {
5601 options.compile_options = v8::ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions;
5602 options.code_cache_options =
5603 ShellOptions::CodeCacheOptions::kProduceCacheAfterExecute;
5604 } else if (strcmp(flag_value, "full-code-cache") == 0) {
5605 options.compile_options = v8::ScriptCompiler::kEagerCompile;
5606 options.code_cache_options =
5607 ShellOptions::CodeCacheOptions::kProduceCache;
5608 } else {
5609 fprintf(stderr, "Unknown option to --cache.\n");
5610 return false;
5611 }
5612 } else if (FlagMatches("--streaming-compile", &argv[i])) {
5613 options.streaming_compile = true;
5614 } else if ((FlagMatches("--no-streaming-compile", &argv[i])) ||
5615 (FlagMatches("--nostreaming-compile", &argv[i]))) {
5616 options.streaming_compile = false;
5617 } else if (FlagMatches("--enable-tracing", &argv[i])) {
5618 options.trace_enabled = true;
5619 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--trace-path", &flag_value, argc, argv,
5620 &i)) {
5621 options.trace_path = flag_value;
5622 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--trace-config", &flag_value, argc, argv,
5623 &i)) {
5624 options.trace_config = flag_value;
5625 } else if (FlagMatches("--enable-inspector", &argv[i])) {
5626 options.enable_inspector = true;
5627 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--lcov", &flag_value, argc, argv, &i)) {
5628 options.lcov_file = flag_value;
5629#ifdef V8_OS_LINUX
5630 } else if (FlagMatches("--scope-linux-perf-to-mark-measure", &argv[i])) {
5631 options.scope_linux_perf_to_mark_measure = true;
5632 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--perf-ctl-fd", &flag_value, argc, argv,
5633 &i)) {
5634 options.perf_ctl_fd = atoi(flag_value);
5635 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--perf-ack-fd", &flag_value, argc, argv,
5636 &i)) {
5637 options.perf_ack_fd = atoi(flag_value);
5638#endif
5639 } else if (FlagMatches("--disable-in-process-stack-traces", &argv[i])) {
5640 options.disable_in_process_stack_traces = true;
5641#ifdef V8_OS_POSIX
5642 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--read-from-tcp-port", &flag_value, argc,
5643 argv, &i)) {
5644 options.read_from_tcp_port = atoi(flag_value);
5645#endif // V8_OS_POSIX
5646 } else if (FlagMatches("--enable-os-system", &argv[i])) {
5647 options.enable_os_system = true;
5648 } else if (FlagMatches("--no-apply-priority", &argv[i])) {
5649 options.apply_priority = false;
5650 } else if (FlagMatches("--quiet-load", &argv[i])) {
5651 options.quiet_load = true;
5652 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--thread-pool-size", &flag_value, argc, argv,
5653 &i)) {
5654 options.thread_pool_size = atoi(flag_value);
5655 } else if (FlagMatches("--stress-delay-tasks", &argv[i])) {
5656 // Delay execution of tasks by 0-100ms randomly (based on --random-seed).
5657 options.stress_delay_tasks = true;
5658 } else if (FlagMatches("--cpu-profiler", &argv[i])) {
5659 options.cpu_profiler = true;
5660 } else if (FlagMatches("--cpu-profiler-print", &argv[i])) {
5661 options.cpu_profiler = true;
5662 options.cpu_profiler_print = true;
5663 } else if (FlagMatches("--stress-deserialize", &argv[i])) {
5664 options.stress_deserialize = true;
5665 } else if (FlagMatches("--compile-only", &argv[i])) {
5666 options.compile_only = true;
5667 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--repeat-compile", &flag_value, argc, argv,
5668 &i)) {
5669 options.repeat_compile = atoi(flag_value);
5670 } else if (FlagWithArgMatches("--max-serializer-memory", &flag_value, argc,
5671 argv, &i)) {
5672 // Value is expressed in MB.
5673 options.max_serializer_memory = atoi(flag_value) * i::MB;
5674#ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
5675 } else if (FlagMatches("--fuzzilli-enable-builtins-coverage", &argv[i])) {
5676 options.fuzzilli_enable_builtins_coverage = true;
5677 } else if (FlagMatches("--fuzzilli-coverage-statistics", &argv[i])) {
5678 options.fuzzilli_coverage_statistics = true;
5679#endif
5680 } else if (FlagMatches("--no-fuzzy-module-file-extensions", &argv[i])) {
5681 DCHECK(options.fuzzy_module_file_extensions);
5682 options.fuzzy_module_file_extensions = false;
5683#if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5684 } else if (FlagMatches("--enable-etw-stack-walking", &argv[i])) {
5685 options.enable_etw_stack_walking = true;
5686 // This needs to be manually triggered for JIT ETW events to work.
5687 i::v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking = true;
5688#if defined(V8_ENABLE_SYSTEM_INSTRUMENTATION)
5689 } else if (FlagMatches("--enable-system-instrumentation", &argv[i])) {
5690 options.enable_system_instrumentation = true;
5691 options.trace_enabled = true;
5692#endif
5693#if defined(V8_OS_WIN)
5694 // Guard this bc the flag has a lot of overhead and is not currently used
5695 // by macos
5696 i::v8_flags.interpreted_frames_native_stack = true;
5697#endif
5698#endif
5699#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5700 } else if (FlagMatches("--wasm-trap-handler", &argv[i])) {
5701 options.wasm_trap_handler = true;
5702 } else if (FlagMatches("--no-wasm-trap-handler", &argv[i])) {
5703 options.wasm_trap_handler = false;
5704#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5705 } else if (FlagMatches("--expose-fast-api", &argv[i])) {
5706 options.expose_fast_api = true;
5707 } else {
5708#ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_WIN
5709 PreProcessUnicodeFilenameArg(argv, i);
5710#endif
5711 }
5712 }
5713
5714#ifdef V8_OS_LINUX
5715 if (options.scope_linux_perf_to_mark_measure) {
5716 if (options.perf_ctl_fd == -1 || options.perf_ack_fd == -1) {
5717 fprintf(stderr,
5718 "Flag --scope-linux-perf-to-mark-measure requires both "
5719 "--perf-ctl-fd and --perf-ack-fd\n");
5720 return false;
5721 }
5722 SendPerfControlCommand("disable");
5723 }
5724#endif
5725
5726 const char* usage =
5727 "Synopsis:\n"
5728 " shell [options] [--shell] [<file>...]\n"
5729 " d8 [options] [-e <string>] [--shell] [--module|]"
5730 " <file>...]\n\n"
5731 " -e execute a string in V8\n"
5732 " --shell run an interactive JavaScript shell\n"
5733 " --module execute a file as a JavaScript module\n";
5734 using HelpOptions = i::FlagList::HelpOptions;
5735 i::v8_flags.abort_on_contradictory_flags = true;
5736 i::FlagList::SetFlagsFromCommandLine(&argc, argv, true,
5737 HelpOptions(HelpOptions::kExit, usage));
5738 i::FlagList::ResolveContradictionsWhenFuzzing();
5739
5740 options.mock_arraybuffer_allocator = i::v8_flags.mock_arraybuffer_allocator;
5741 options.mock_arraybuffer_allocator_limit =
5742 i::v8_flags.mock_arraybuffer_allocator_limit;
5743#ifdef V8_OS_LINUX
5744 options.multi_mapped_mock_allocator = i::v8_flags.multi_mapped_mock_allocator;
5745#endif // V8_OS_LINUX
5746
5747 if (i::v8_flags.stress_snapshot && options.expose_fast_api &&
5748 check_d8_flag_contradictions) {
5749 FATAL("Flag --expose-fast-api is incompatible with --stress-snapshot.");
5750 }
5751
5752 // Set up isolated source groups.
5753 options.isolate_sources = new SourceGroup[options.num_isolates];
5754 internal::g_num_isolates_for_testing = options.num_isolates;
5755 SourceGroup* current = options.isolate_sources;
5756 current->Begin(argv, 1);
5757 for (int i = 1; i < argc; i++) {
5758 const char* str = argv[i];
5759 if (strcmp(str, "--isolate") == 0) {
5760 current->End(i);
5761 current++;
5762 current->Begin(argv, i + 1);
5763 } else if (strcmp(str, "--module") == 0 || strcmp(str, "--json") == 0) {
5764 // Pass on to SourceGroup, which understands these options.
5765 } else if (strncmp(str, "--", 2) == 0) {
5766 if (!i::v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
5767 printf("Warning: unknown flag %s.\nTry --help for options\n", str);
5768 }
5769 } else if (strcmp(str, "-e") == 0 && i + 1 < argc) {
5770 set_script_executed();
5771 } else if (strncmp(str, "-", 1) != 0) {
5772 // Not a flag, so it must be a script to execute.
5773 set_script_executed();
5774 }
5775 }
5776 current->End(argc);
5777
5778 if (!logfile_per_isolate && options.num_isolates) {
5779 V8::SetFlagsFromString("--no-logfile-per-isolate");
5780 }
5781
5782 return true;
5783}
5784
5785int Shell::RunMain(v8::Isolate* isolate, bool last_run) {
5786 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
5787
5788 for (int i = 1; i < options.num_isolates; ++i) {
5789 options.isolate_sources[i].StartExecuteInThread();
5790 }
5791
5792 // The Context object, created inside RunMainIsolate, is used after the method
5793 // returns in some situations:
5794 const bool keep_context_alive =
5795 last_run && (use_interactive_shell() || i::v8_flags.stress_snapshot);
5796 bool success = RunMainIsolate(isolate, keep_context_alive);
5797 CollectGarbage(isolate);
5798
5799 // Park the main thread here to prevent deadlocks in shared GCs when
5800 // waiting in JoinThread.
5801 i_isolate->main_thread_local_heap()->ExecuteMainThreadWhileParked(
5802 [last_run](const i::ParkedScope& parked) {
5803 for (int i = 1; i < options.num_isolates; ++i) {
5804 if (last_run) {
5805 options.isolate_sources[i].JoinThread(parked);
5806 } else {
5807 options.isolate_sources[i].WaitForThread(parked);
5808 }
5809 }
5810 WaitForRunningWorkers(parked);
5811 });
5812
5813 // Other threads have terminated, we can now run the artifical
5814 // serialize-deserialize pass (which destructively mutates heap state).
5815 if (success && last_run && i::v8_flags.stress_snapshot) {
5816 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
5817 static constexpr bool kClearRecompilableData = true;
5818 auto context = v8::Local<v8::Context>::New(isolate, evaluation_context_);
5819 i::DirectHandle<i::Context> i_context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*context);
5820 // Stop concurrent compiles before mutating the heap.
5821 if (i_isolate->concurrent_recompilation_enabled()) {
5822 i_isolate->optimizing_compile_dispatcher()->Stop();
5823 }
5824#if V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
5825 if (i_isolate->maglev_concurrent_dispatcher()->is_enabled()) {
5826 i_isolate->maglev_concurrent_dispatcher()->AwaitCompileJobs();
5827 }
5828#endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
5829 // TODO(jgruber,v8:10500): Don't deoptimize once we support serialization
5830 // of optimized code.
5831 i::Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeAll(i_isolate);
5832 // Trigger GC to better align with production code. Also needed by
5833 // ClearReconstructableDataForSerialization to not look into dead objects.
5834 i_isolate->heap()->CollectAllAvailableGarbage(
5835 i::GarbageCollectionReason::kSnapshotCreator);
5836 i::Snapshot::ClearReconstructableDataForSerialization(
5837 i_isolate, kClearRecompilableData);
5838 i::Snapshot::SerializeDeserializeAndVerifyForTesting(i_isolate, i_context);
5839 }
5840
5841 if (Shell::unhandled_promise_rejections_.load() > 0) {
5842 printf("%i pending unhandled Promise rejection(s) detected.\n",
5843 Shell::unhandled_promise_rejections_.load());
5844 success = false;
5845 // RunMain may be executed multiple times, e.g. in REPRL mode, so we have to
5846 // reset this counter.
5847 Shell::unhandled_promise_rejections_.store(0);
5848 }
5849 // In order to finish successfully, success must be != expected_to_throw.
5850 if (Shell::options.no_fail) return 0;
5851 // Fuzzers aren't expected to use --throws, but may pick it up from testcases.
5852 // In that case, just ignore the flag.
5853 if (i::v8_flags.fuzzing && Shell::options.expected_to_throw) return 0;
5854 return (success == Shell::options.expected_to_throw ? 1 : 0);
5855}
5856
5857bool Shell::RunMainIsolate(v8::Isolate* isolate, bool keep_context_alive) {
5858 if (options.lcov_file) {
5859 debug::Coverage::SelectMode(isolate, debug::CoverageMode::kBlockCount);
5860 }
5861 HandleScope scope(isolate);
5862 Global<Context> global_context;
5863 {
5864 Local<Context> context;
5865 if (!CreateEvaluationContext(isolate).ToLocal(&context)) {
5866 DCHECK(isolate->IsExecutionTerminating());
5867 // We must not exit early here in REPRL mode as that would cause the next
5868 // testcase sent by Fuzzilli to be skipped, which will desynchronize the
5869 // communication between d8 and Fuzzilli, leading to a crash.
5870 DCHECK(!fuzzilli_reprl);
5871 return true;
5872 }
5873 global_context.Reset(isolate, context);
5874 if (keep_context_alive) {
5875 evaluation_context_.Reset(isolate, context);
5876 }
5877 }
5878 PerIsolateData::RealmScope realm_scope(isolate, global_context);
5879 InspectorClient inspector_client(isolate, global_context,
5880 options.enable_inspector);
5881 bool success = true;
5882 {
5883 // We cannot use a Context::Scope here, as it keeps a local handle to the
5884 // context and SourceGroup::Execute may execute a non-nestable task, e.g. a
5885 // stackless GC.
5886 global_context.Get(isolate)->Enter();
5887 if (!options.isolate_sources[0].Execute(isolate)) success = false;
5888 global_context.Get(isolate)->Exit();
5889 }
5890 if (!FinishExecuting(isolate, global_context)) success = false;
5891 WriteLcovData(isolate, options.lcov_file);
5892 return success;
5893}
5894
5895void Shell::CollectGarbage(Isolate* isolate) {
5896 if (options.send_idle_notification) {
5897 isolate->ContextDisposedNotification();
5898 }
5899 if (options.invoke_weak_callbacks) {
5900 // By sending a low memory notifications, we will try hard to collect all
5901 // garbage and will therefore also invoke all weak callbacks of actually
5902 // unreachable persistent handles.
5903 isolate->LowMemoryNotification();
5904 }
5905}
5906
5907namespace {
5908bool ProcessMessages(
5909 Isolate* isolate,
5910 const std::function<platform::MessageLoopBehavior()>& behavior) {
5911 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
5912 i::SaveAndSwitchContext saved_context(i_isolate, i::Context());
5913 SealHandleScope shs(isolate);
5914
5915 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) return true;
5916 TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
5917 try_catch.SetVerbose(true);
5918
5919 while (true) {
5920 bool ran_a_task;
5921 ran_a_task =
5922 v8::platform::PumpMessageLoop(g_default_platform, isolate, behavior());
5923 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) return true;
5924 if (try_catch.HasCaught()) return false;
5925 if (ran_a_task) MicrotasksScope::PerformCheckpoint(isolate);
5926 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) return true;
5927
5928 // In predictable mode we push all background tasks into the foreground
5929 // task queue of the {kProcessGlobalPredictablePlatformWorkerTaskQueue}
5930 // isolate. We execute all background tasks after running one foreground
5931 // task.
5932 if (i::v8_flags.verify_predictable) {
5933 TryCatch try_catch(isolate);
5934 try_catch.SetVerbose(true);
5935 while (v8::platform::PumpMessageLoop(
5936 g_default_platform, kProcessGlobalPredictablePlatformWorkerTaskQueue,
5937 platform::MessageLoopBehavior::kDoNotWait)) {
5938 ran_a_task = true;
5939 if (try_catch.HasCaught()) return false;
5940 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) return true;
5941 }
5942 }
5943
5944 if (!ran_a_task) break;
5945 }
5946 if (g_default_platform->IdleTasksEnabled(isolate)) {
5947 v8::platform::RunIdleTasks(g_default_platform, isolate,
5948 50.0 / base::Time::kMillisecondsPerSecond);
5949 if (try_catch.HasCaught()) return false;
5950 if (isolate->IsExecutionTerminating()) return true;
5951 }
5952 return true;
5953}
5954} // anonymous namespace
5955
5956bool Shell::CompleteMessageLoop(Isolate* isolate) {
5957 auto get_waiting_behaviour = [isolate]() {
5958 if (options.wait_for_background_tasks &&
5959 isolate->HasPendingBackgroundTasks()) {
5960 return platform::MessageLoopBehavior::kWaitForWork;
5961 }
5962 if (PerIsolateData::Get(isolate)->HasRunningSubscribedWorkers()) {
5963 return platform::MessageLoopBehavior::kWaitForWork;
5964 }
5965 return platform::MessageLoopBehavior::kDoNotWait;
5966 };
5967 if (i::v8_flags.verify_predictable) {
5968 bool ran_tasks = ProcessMessages(
5969 isolate, [] { return platform::MessageLoopBehavior::kDoNotWait; });
5970 if (get_waiting_behaviour() ==
5971 platform::MessageLoopBehavior::kWaitForWork) {
5972 FATAL(
5973 "There is outstanding work after executing all tasks in predictable "
5974 "mode -- this would deadlock.");
5975 }
5976 return ran_tasks;
5977 }
5978 return ProcessMessages(isolate, get_waiting_behaviour);
5979}
5980
5981bool Shell::FinishExecuting(Isolate* isolate, const Global<Context>& context) {
5982 if (!CompleteMessageLoop(isolate)) return false;
5983 HandleScope scope(isolate);
5984 // We cannot use a Context::Scope here, as it keeps a local handle to the
5985 // context and HandleUnhandledPromiseRejections may execute a non-nestable
5986 // task, e.g. a stackless GC.
5987 context.Get(isolate)->Enter();
5988 bool result = HandleUnhandledPromiseRejections(isolate);
5989 context.Get(isolate)->Exit();
5990 return result;
5991}
5992
5993bool Shell::EmptyMessageQueues(Isolate* isolate) {
5994 return ProcessMessages(
5995 isolate, []() { return platform::MessageLoopBehavior::kDoNotWait; });
5996}
5997
5998bool Shell::HandleUnhandledPromiseRejections(Isolate* isolate) {
5999 if (options.ignore_unhandled_promises) return true;
6000 PerIsolateData* data = PerIsolateData::Get(isolate);
6001 int count = data->HandleUnhandledPromiseRejections();
6002 Shell::unhandled_promise_rejections_.store(
6003 Shell::unhandled_promise_rejections_.load() + count);
6004 return count == 0;
6005}
6006
6007class Serializer : public ValueSerializer::Delegate {
6008 public:
6009 explicit Serializer(Isolate* isolate)
6010 : isolate_(isolate),
6011 serializer_(isolate, this),
6012 current_memory_usage_(0) {}
6013
6014 Serializer(const Serializer&) = delete;
6015 Serializer& operator=(const Serializer&) = delete;
6016
6017 Maybe<bool> WriteValue(Local<Context> context, Local<Value> value,
6018 Local<Value> transfer) {
6019 bool ok;
6020 DCHECK(!data_);
6021 data_.reset(new SerializationData);
6022 if (!PrepareTransfer(context, transfer).To(&ok)) {
6023 return Nothing<bool>();
6024 }
6025 serializer_.WriteHeader();
6026
6027 if (!serializer_.WriteValue(context, value).To(&ok)) {
6028 data_.reset();
6029 return Nothing<bool>();
6030 }
6031
6032 if (!FinalizeTransfer().To(&ok)) {
6033 return Nothing<bool>();
6034 }
6035
6036 std::pair<uint8_t*, size_t> pair = serializer_.Release();
6037 data_->data_.reset(pair.first);
6038 data_->size_ = pair.second;
6039 return Just(true);
6040 }
6041
6042 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> Release() { return std::move(data_); }
6043
6044 void AppendBackingStoresTo(std::vector<std::shared_ptr<BackingStore>>* to) {
6045 to->insert(to->end(), std::make_move_iterator(backing_stores_.begin()),
6046 std::make_move_iterator(backing_stores_.end()));
6047 backing_stores_.clear();
6048 }
6049
6050 protected:
6051 // Implements ValueSerializer::Delegate.
6052 void ThrowDataCloneError(Local<String> message) override {
6053 isolate_->ThrowException(Exception::Error(message));
6054 }
6055
6056 Maybe<uint32_t> GetSharedArrayBufferId(
6057 Isolate* isolate, Local<SharedArrayBuffer> shared_array_buffer) override {
6058 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(data_);
6059 for (size_t index = 0; index < shared_array_buffers_.size(); ++index) {
6060 if (shared_array_buffers_[index] == shared_array_buffer) {
6061 return Just<uint32_t>(static_cast<uint32_t>(index));
6062 }
6063 }
6064
6065 size_t index = shared_array_buffers_.size();
6066 shared_array_buffers_.emplace_back(isolate_, shared_array_buffer);
6067 data_->sab_backing_stores_.push_back(
6068 shared_array_buffer->GetBackingStore());
6069 return Just<uint32_t>(static_cast<uint32_t>(index));
6070 }
6071
6072 Maybe<uint32_t> GetWasmModuleTransferId(
6073 Isolate* isolate, Local<WasmModuleObject> module) override {
6074 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(data_);
6075 for (size_t index = 0; index < wasm_modules_.size(); ++index) {
6076 if (wasm_modules_[index] == module) {
6077 return Just<uint32_t>(static_cast<uint32_t>(index));
6078 }
6079 }
6080
6081 size_t index = wasm_modules_.size();
6082 wasm_modules_.emplace_back(isolate_, module);
6083 data_->compiled_wasm_modules_.push_back(module->GetCompiledModule());
6084 return Just<uint32_t>(static_cast<uint32_t>(index));
6085 }
6086
6087 void* ReallocateBufferMemory(void* old_buffer, size_t size,
6088 size_t* actual_size) override {
6089 // Not accurate, because we don't take into account reallocated buffers,
6090 // but this is fine for testing.
6091 current_memory_usage_ += size;
6092 if (current_memory_usage_ > Shell::options.max_serializer_memory) {
6093 return nullptr;
6094 }
6095
6096 void* result = base::Realloc(old_buffer, size);
6097 *actual_size = result ? size : 0;
6098 return result;
6099 }
6100
6101 void FreeBufferMemory(void* buffer) override { base::Free(buffer); }
6102
6103 bool AdoptSharedValueConveyor(Isolate* isolate,
6104 SharedValueConveyor&& conveyor) override {
6105 data_->shared_value_conveyor_.emplace(std::move(conveyor));
6106 return true;
6107 }
6108
6109 private:
6110 Maybe<bool> PrepareTransfer(Local<Context> context, Local<Value> transfer) {
6111 if (transfer->IsArray()) {
6112 Local<Array> transfer_array = transfer.As<Array>();
6113 uint32_t length = transfer_array->Length();
6114 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
6115 Local<Value> element;
6116 if (transfer_array->Get(context, i).ToLocal(&element)) {
6117 if (!element->IsArrayBuffer()) {
6118 isolate_->ThrowError(
6119 "Transfer array elements must be an ArrayBuffer");
6120 return Nothing<bool>();
6121 }
6122
6123 Local<ArrayBuffer> array_buffer = element.As<ArrayBuffer>();
6124
6125 if (std::find(array_buffers_.begin(), array_buffers_.end(),
6126 array_buffer) != array_buffers_.end()) {
6127 isolate_->ThrowError(
6128 "ArrayBuffer occurs in the transfer array more than once");
6129 return Nothing<bool>();
6130 }
6131
6132 serializer_.TransferArrayBuffer(
6133 static_cast<uint32_t>(array_buffers_.size()), array_buffer);
6134 array_buffers_.emplace_back(isolate_, array_buffer);
6135 } else {
6136 return Nothing<bool>();
6137 }
6138 }
6139 return Just(true);
6140 } else if (transfer->IsUndefined()) {
6141 return Just(true);
6142 } else {
6143 isolate_->ThrowError("Transfer list must be an Array or undefined");
6144 return Nothing<bool>();
6145 }
6146 }
6147
6148 Maybe<bool> FinalizeTransfer() {
6149 for (const auto& global_array_buffer : array_buffers_) {
6150 Local<ArrayBuffer> array_buffer =
6151 Local<ArrayBuffer>::New(isolate_, global_array_buffer);
6152 if (!array_buffer->IsDetachable()) {
6153 isolate_->ThrowError(
6154 "ArrayBuffer is not detachable and could not be transferred");
6155 return Nothing<bool>();
6156 }
6157
6158 auto backing_store = array_buffer->GetBackingStore();
6159 data_->backing_stores_.push_back(std::move(backing_store));
6160 if (array_buffer->Detach(v8::Local<v8::Value>()).IsNothing()) {
6161 return Nothing<bool>();
6162 }
6163 }
6164
6165 return Just(true);
6166 }
6167
6168 // This must come before ValueSerializer as it caches this value.
6169 Isolate* isolate_;
6170 ValueSerializer serializer_;
6171 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data_;
6172 std::vector<Global<ArrayBuffer>> array_buffers_;
6173 std::vector<Global<SharedArrayBuffer>> shared_array_buffers_;
6174 std::vector<Global<WasmModuleObject>> wasm_modules_;
6175 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<v8::BackingStore>> backing_stores_;
6176 size_t current_memory_usage_;
6177};
6178
6179class Deserializer : public ValueDeserializer::Delegate {
6180 public:
6181 Deserializer(Isolate* isolate, std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data)
6182 : isolate_(isolate),
6183 deserializer_(isolate, data->data(), data->size(), this),
6184 data_(std::move(data)) {
6185 deserializer_.SetSupportsLegacyWireFormat(true);
6186 }
6187
6188 Deserializer(const Deserializer&) = delete;
6189 Deserializer& operator=(const Deserializer&) = delete;
6190
6191 MaybeLocal<Value> ReadValue(Local<Context> context) {
6192 bool read_header;
6193 if (!deserializer_.ReadHeader(context).To(&read_header)) {
6194 return MaybeLocal<Value>();
6195 }
6196
6197 uint32_t index = 0;
6198 for (const auto& backing_store : data_->backing_stores()) {
6199 Local<ArrayBuffer> array_buffer =
6200 ArrayBuffer::New(isolate_, std::move(backing_store));
6201 deserializer_.TransferArrayBuffer(index++, array_buffer);
6202 }
6203
6204 return deserializer_.ReadValue(context);
6205 }
6206
6207 MaybeLocal<SharedArrayBuffer> GetSharedArrayBufferFromId(
6208 Isolate* isolate, uint32_t clone_id) override {
6209 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(data_);
6210 if (clone_id < data_->sab_backing_stores().size()) {
6211 return SharedArrayBuffer::New(
6212 isolate_, std::move(data_->sab_backing_stores().at(clone_id)));
6213 }
6214 return MaybeLocal<SharedArrayBuffer>();
6215 }
6216
6217 MaybeLocal<WasmModuleObject> GetWasmModuleFromId(
6218 Isolate* isolate, uint32_t transfer_id) override {
6219 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(data_);
6220 if (transfer_id >= data_->compiled_wasm_modules().size()) return {};
6221 return WasmModuleObject::FromCompiledModule(
6222 isolate_, data_->compiled_wasm_modules().at(transfer_id));
6223 }
6224
6225 const SharedValueConveyor* GetSharedValueConveyor(Isolate* isolate) override {
6226 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(data_);
6227 if (data_->shared_value_conveyor()) {
6228 return &data_->shared_value_conveyor().value();
6229 }
6230 return nullptr;
6231 }
6232
6233 private:
6234 Isolate* isolate_;
6235 ValueDeserializer deserializer_;
6236 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data_;
6237};
6238
6239class D8Testing {
6240 public:
6245 static int GetStressRuns() {
6246 if (i::v8_flags.stress_runs != 0) return i::v8_flags.stress_runs;
6247#ifdef DEBUG
6248 // In debug mode the code runs much slower so stressing will only make two
6249 // runs.
6250 return 2;
6251#else
6252 return 5;
6253#endif
6254 }
6255
6259 static void DeoptimizeAll(Isolate* isolate) {
6260 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
6261 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
6262 i::Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeAll(i_isolate);
6263 }
6264};
6265
6266std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> Shell::SerializeValue(
6267 Isolate* isolate, Local<Value> value, Local<Value> transfer) {
6268 bool ok;
6269 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
6270 Serializer serializer(isolate);
6271 std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data;
6272 if (serializer.WriteValue(context, value, transfer).To(&ok)) {
6273 data = serializer.Release();
6274 }
6275 return data;
6276}
6277
6278MaybeLocal<Value> Shell::DeserializeValue(
6279 Isolate* isolate, std::unique_ptr<SerializationData> data) {
6280 Local<Context> context = isolate->GetCurrentContext();
6281 Deserializer deserializer(isolate, std::move(data));
6282 return deserializer.ReadValue(context);
6283}
6284
6285void Shell::AddRunningWorker(std::shared_ptr<Worker> worker) {
6286 workers_mutex_.Pointer()->AssertHeld(); // caller should hold the mutex.
6287 running_workers_.insert(worker);
6288}
6289
6290void Shell::RemoveRunningWorker(const std::shared_ptr<Worker>& worker) {
6291 base::MutexGuard lock_guard(workers_mutex_.Pointer());
6292 auto it = running_workers_.find(worker);
6293 if (it != running_workers_.end()) running_workers_.erase(it);
6294}
6295
6296void Shell::WaitForRunningWorkers(const i::ParkedScope& parked) {
6297 // Make a copy of running_workers_, because we don't want to call
6298 // Worker::Terminate while holding the workers_mutex_ lock. Otherwise, if a
6299 // worker is about to create a new Worker, it would deadlock.
6300 std::unordered_set<std::shared_ptr<Worker>> workers_copy;
6301 {
6302 base::MutexGuard lock_guard(workers_mutex_.Pointer());
6303 allow_new_workers_ = false;
6304 workers_copy.swap(running_workers_);
6305 }
6306
6307 for (auto& worker : workers_copy) {
6308 worker->TerminateAndWaitForThread(parked);
6309 }
6310
6311 // Now that all workers are terminated, we can re-enable Worker creation.
6312 base::MutexGuard lock_guard(workers_mutex_.Pointer());
6313 DCHECK(running_workers_.empty());
6314 allow_new_workers_ = true;
6315}
6316
6317namespace {
6318
6319#ifdef V8_OS_POSIX
6320void d8_sigterm_handler(int signal, siginfo_t* info, void* context) {
6321 // Dump stacktraces when terminating d8 instances with SIGTERM.
6322 // SIGKILL is not intercepted.
6323 if (signal == SIGTERM) {
6324 FATAL("d8: Received SIGTERM signal (likely due to a TIMEOUT)\n");
6325 } else {
6326 UNREACHABLE();
6327 }
6328}
6329#endif // V8_OS_POSIX
6330
6331void d8_install_sigterm_handler() {
6332#ifdef V8_OS_POSIX
6333 CHECK(!i::v8_flags.fuzzing);
6334 struct sigaction sa;
6335 sa.sa_sigaction = d8_sigterm_handler;
6336 sigemptyset(&sa.sa_mask);
6337 sa.sa_flags = 0;
6338 if (sigaction(SIGTERM, &sa, NULL) == -1) {
6339 FATAL("Could not install SIGTERM handler");
6340 }
6341#endif // V8_OS_POSIX
6342}
6343
6344} // namespace
6345
6346int Shell::Main(int argc, char* argv[]) {
6347 v8::base::EnsureConsoleOutput();
6348 if (!SetOptions(argc, argv)) return 1;
6349 if (!i::v8_flags.fuzzing) d8_install_sigterm_handler();
6350
6351 v8::V8::InitializeICUDefaultLocation(argv[0], options.icu_data_file);
6352
6353#ifdef V8_OS_DARWIN
6354 if (options.apply_priority) {
6355 struct task_category_policy category = {.role =
6356 TASK_FOREGROUND_APPLICATION};
6357 task_policy_set(mach_task_self(), TASK_CATEGORY_POLICY,
6358 (task_policy_t)&category, TASK_CATEGORY_POLICY_COUNT);
6359 pthread_set_qos_class_self_np(QOS_CLASS_USER_INTERACTIVE, 0);
6360 }
6361#endif
6362
6363#ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
6364 if (options.icu_locale != nullptr) {
6365 icu::Locale locale(options.icu_locale);
6366 UErrorCode error_code = U_ZERO_ERROR;
6367 icu::Locale::setDefault(locale, error_code);
6368 }
6369#endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
6370
6371 v8::platform::InProcessStackDumping in_process_stack_dumping =
6372 options.disable_in_process_stack_traces
6373 ? v8::platform::InProcessStackDumping::kDisabled
6374 : v8::platform::InProcessStackDumping::kEnabled;
6375
6376 std::ofstream trace_file;
6377 std::unique_ptr<platform::tracing::TracingController> tracing;
6378 if (options.trace_enabled && !i::v8_flags.verify_predictable) {
6379 tracing = std::make_unique<platform::tracing::TracingController>();
6380
6381 if (!options.enable_etw_stack_walking) {
6382 const char* trace_path =
6383 options.trace_path ? options.trace_path : "v8_trace.json";
6384 trace_file.open(trace_path);
6385 if (!trace_file.good()) {
6386 printf("Cannot open trace file '%s' for writing: %s.\n", trace_path,
6387 strerror(errno));
6388 return 1;
6389 }
6390 }
6391
6392#ifdef V8_USE_PERFETTO
6393 // Set up the in-process backend that the tracing controller will connect
6394 // to.
6395 perfetto::TracingInitArgs init_args;
6396 init_args.backends = perfetto::BackendType::kInProcessBackend;
6397 perfetto::Tracing::Initialize(init_args);
6398
6399 tracing->InitializeForPerfetto(&trace_file);
6400#else
6401 platform::tracing::TraceBuffer* trace_buffer = nullptr;
6402#if defined(V8_ENABLE_SYSTEM_INSTRUMENTATION)
6403 if (options.enable_system_instrumentation) {
6404 trace_buffer =
6405 platform::tracing::TraceBuffer::CreateTraceBufferRingBuffer(
6406 platform::tracing::TraceBuffer::kRingBufferChunks,
6407 platform::tracing::TraceWriter::
6408 CreateSystemInstrumentationTraceWriter());
6409 }
6410#endif // V8_ENABLE_SYSTEM_INSTRUMENTATION
6411 if (!trace_buffer) {
6412 trace_buffer =
6413 platform::tracing::TraceBuffer::CreateTraceBufferRingBuffer(
6414 platform::tracing::TraceBuffer::kRingBufferChunks,
6415 platform::tracing::TraceWriter::CreateJSONTraceWriter(
6416 trace_file));
6417 }
6418 tracing->Initialize(trace_buffer);
6419#endif // V8_USE_PERFETTO
6420 }
6421
6422 v8::SandboxHardwareSupport::InitializeBeforeThreadCreation();
6423
6424 platform::tracing::TracingController* tracing_controller = tracing.get();
6425 if (i::v8_flags.single_threaded) {
6426 g_platform = v8::platform::NewSingleThreadedDefaultPlatform(
6427 v8::platform::IdleTaskSupport::kEnabled, in_process_stack_dumping,
6428 std::move(tracing));
6429 } else {
6430 g_platform = v8::platform::NewDefaultPlatform(
6431 options.thread_pool_size, v8::platform::IdleTaskSupport::kEnabled,
6432 in_process_stack_dumping, std::move(tracing),
6433 options.apply_priority ? v8::platform::PriorityMode::kApply
6434 : v8::platform::PriorityMode::kDontApply);
6435 }
6436 g_default_platform = g_platform.get();
6437 if (i::v8_flags.predictable) {
6438 g_platform = MakePredictablePlatform(std::move(g_platform));
6439 }
6440 if (options.stress_delay_tasks) {
6441 int64_t random_seed = i::v8_flags.fuzzer_random_seed;
6442 if (!random_seed) random_seed = i::v8_flags.random_seed;
6443 // If random_seed is still 0 here, the {DelayedTasksPlatform} will choose a
6444 // random seed.
6445 g_platform = MakeDelayedTasksPlatform(std::move(g_platform), random_seed);
6446 }
6447
6448 if (i::v8_flags.trace_turbo_cfg_file == nullptr) {
6449 V8::SetFlagsFromString("--trace-turbo-cfg-file=turbo.cfg");
6450 }
6451 if (i::v8_flags.redirect_code_traces_to == nullptr) {
6452 V8::SetFlagsFromString("--redirect-code-traces-to=code.asm");
6453 }
6454 v8::V8::InitializePlatform(g_platform.get());
6455
6456 // Disable flag freezing if we are producing a code cache, because for that we
6457 // modify v8_flags.hash_seed (below).
6458 if (options.code_cache_options != ShellOptions::kNoProduceCache) {
6459 i::v8_flags.freeze_flags_after_init = false;
6460 }
6461
6462 v8::V8::Initialize();
6463 if (options.snapshot_blob) {
6464 v8::V8::InitializeExternalStartupDataFromFile(options.snapshot_blob);
6465 } else {
6466 v8::V8::InitializeExternalStartupData(argv[0]);
6467 }
6468 int result = 0;
6469 Isolate::CreateParams create_params;
6470 ShellArrayBufferAllocator shell_array_buffer_allocator;
6471 MockArrayBufferAllocator mock_arraybuffer_allocator;
6472 const size_t memory_limit =
6473 options.mock_arraybuffer_allocator_limit * options.num_isolates;
6474 MockArrayBufferAllocatiorWithLimit mock_arraybuffer_allocator_with_limit(
6475 memory_limit >= options.mock_arraybuffer_allocator_limit
6476 ? memory_limit
6477 : std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max());
6478#ifdef V8_OS_LINUX
6479 MultiMappedAllocator multi_mapped_mock_allocator;
6480#endif // V8_OS_LINUX
6481 if (options.mock_arraybuffer_allocator) {
6482 if (memory_limit) {
6483 Shell::array_buffer_allocator = &mock_arraybuffer_allocator_with_limit;
6484 } else {
6485 Shell::array_buffer_allocator = &mock_arraybuffer_allocator;
6486 }
6487#ifdef V8_OS_LINUX
6488 } else if (options.multi_mapped_mock_allocator) {
6489 Shell::array_buffer_allocator = &multi_mapped_mock_allocator;
6490#endif // V8_OS_LINUX
6491 } else {
6492 Shell::array_buffer_allocator = &shell_array_buffer_allocator;
6493 }
6494 create_params.array_buffer_allocator = Shell::array_buffer_allocator;
6495#ifdef ENABLE_VTUNE_JIT_INTERFACE
6496 if (i::v8_flags.enable_vtunejit) {
6497 create_params.code_event_handler = vTune::GetVtuneCodeEventHandler();
6498 }
6499#endif // ENABLE_VTUNE_JIT_INTERFACE
6500 create_params.constraints.ConfigureDefaults(
6501 base::SysInfo::AmountOfPhysicalMemory(),
6502 base::SysInfo::AmountOfVirtualMemory());
6503
6504 Shell::counter_map_ = new CounterMap();
6505 if (options.dump_counters || options.dump_counters_nvp ||
6506 i::TracingFlags::is_gc_stats_enabled()) {
6507 create_params.counter_lookup_callback = LookupCounter;
6508 create_params.create_histogram_callback = CreateHistogram;
6509 create_params.add_histogram_sample_callback = AddHistogramSample;
6510 }
6511
6512#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6513 if (V8_TRAP_HANDLER_SUPPORTED && options.wasm_trap_handler) {
6514 constexpr bool kUseDefaultTrapHandler = true;
6515 if (!v8::V8::EnableWebAssemblyTrapHandler(kUseDefaultTrapHandler)) {
6516 FATAL("Could not register trap handler");
6517 }
6518 }
6519#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6520
6521 if (i::v8_flags.experimental) {
6522 // This message is printed to stderr so that it is also visible in
6523 // Clusterfuzz reports.
6524 fprintf(stderr,
6525 "V8 is running with experimental features enabled. Stability and "
6526 "security will suffer.\n");
6527 }
6528
6529 Isolate* isolate = Isolate::New(create_params);
6530
6531#ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
6532 // Let the parent process (Fuzzilli) know we are ready.
6533 if (options.fuzzilli_enable_builtins_coverage) {
6534 cov_init_builtins_edges(static_cast<uint32_t>(
6535 i::BasicBlockProfiler::Get()
6536 ->GetCoverageBitmap(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate))
6537 .size()));
6538 }
6539 char helo[] = "HELO";
6540 if (write(REPRL_CWFD, helo, 4) != 4 || read(REPRL_CRFD, helo, 4) != 4) {
6541 fuzzilli_reprl = false;
6542 }
6543
6544 if (memcmp(helo, "HELO", 4) != 0) {
6545 FATAL("REPRL: Invalid response from parent");
6546 }
6547#endif // V8_FUZZILLI
6548
6549 {
6550 Isolate::Scope scope(isolate);
6551 D8Console console(isolate);
6552 Initialize(isolate, &console);
6553 PerIsolateData data(isolate);
6554
6555 // Fuzzilli REPRL = read-eval-print-loop
6556 do {
6557#ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
6558 if (fuzzilli_reprl) {
6559 unsigned action = 0;
6560 ssize_t nread = read(REPRL_CRFD, &action, 4);
6561 if (nread != 4 || action != 'cexe') {
6562 FATAL("REPRL: Unknown action: %u", action);
6563 }
6564 }
6565#endif // V8_FUZZILLI
6566
6567 result = 0;
6568
6569 if (options.trace_enabled) {
6570 platform::tracing::TraceConfig* trace_config;
6571 if (options.trace_config) {
6572 int size = 0;
6573 char* trace_config_json_str = ReadChars(options.trace_config, &size);
6574 trace_config = tracing::CreateTraceConfigFromJSON(
6575 isolate, trace_config_json_str);
6576 delete[] trace_config_json_str;
6577 } else {
6578 trace_config =
6579 platform::tracing::TraceConfig::CreateDefaultTraceConfig();
6580 if (options.enable_system_instrumentation) {
6581 trace_config->AddIncludedCategory("disabled-by-default-v8.compile");
6582 }
6583 }
6584 tracing_controller->StartTracing(trace_config);
6585 }
6586
6587 CpuProfiler* cpu_profiler;
6588 if (options.cpu_profiler) {
6589 cpu_profiler = CpuProfiler::New(isolate);
6590 cpu_profiler->StartProfiling(String::Empty(isolate),
6591 CpuProfilingOptions{});
6592 }
6593
6594 if (i::v8_flags.stress_runs > 0) {
6595 options.stress_runs = i::v8_flags.stress_runs;
6596 for (int i = 0; i < options.stress_runs && result == 0; i++) {
6597 printf("============ Run %d/%d ============\n", i + 1,
6598 options.stress_runs.get());
6599 bool last_run = i == options.stress_runs - 1;
6600 result = RunMain(isolate, last_run);
6601 }
6602 } else if (options.code_cache_options != ShellOptions::kNoProduceCache) {
6603 // Park the main thread here in case the new isolate wants to perform
6604 // a shared GC to prevent a deadlock.
6605 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate)
6606 ->main_thread_local_isolate()
6607 ->ExecuteMainThreadWhileParked([&result]() {
6608 printf("============ Run: Produce code cache ============\n");
6609 // First run to produce the cache
6610 Isolate::CreateParams create_params2;
6611 create_params2.array_buffer_allocator =
6612 Shell::array_buffer_allocator;
6613 // Use a different hash seed.
6614 i::v8_flags.hash_seed = i::v8_flags.hash_seed ^ 1337;
6615 Isolate* isolate2 = Isolate::New(create_params2);
6616 // Restore old hash seed.
6617 i::v8_flags.hash_seed = i::v8_flags.hash_seed ^ 1337;
6618 {
6619 Isolate::Scope isolate_scope(isolate2);
6620 D8Console console2(isolate2);
6621 Initialize(isolate2, &console2);
6622 PerIsolateData data2(isolate2);
6623
6624 result = RunMain(isolate2, false);
6625 ResetOnProfileEndListener(isolate2);
6626 }
6627 // D8WasmAsyncResolvePromiseTask may be still in the runner at
6628 // this point. We need to terminate the task runners before the
6629 // Isolate to avoid retaining stray tasks with v8::Global pointing
6630 // into a reclaimed Isolate.
6631 platform::NotifyIsolateShutdown(g_default_platform, isolate2);
6632 isolate2->Dispose();
6633 });
6634
6635 // Change the options to consume cache
6636 DCHECK(options.compile_options == v8::ScriptCompiler::kEagerCompile ||
6637 options.compile_options ==
6638 v8::ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions);
6639 options.compile_options.Overwrite(
6640 v8::ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache);
6641 options.code_cache_options.Overwrite(ShellOptions::kNoProduceCache);
6642
6643 printf("============ Run: Consume code cache ============\n");
6644 // Second run to consume the cache in current isolate
6645 result = RunMain(isolate, true);
6646 options.compile_options.Overwrite(
6647 v8::ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions);
6648 } else {
6649 bool last_run = true;
6650 result = RunMain(isolate, last_run);
6651 }
6652
6653 // Run interactive shell if explicitly requested or if no script has been
6654 // executed, but never on --test
6655 if (use_interactive_shell()) {
6656 RunShell(isolate);
6657 }
6658
6659 if (i::v8_flags.trace_ignition_dispatches_output_file != nullptr) {
6660 WriteIgnitionDispatchCountersFile(isolate);
6661 }
6662
6663 if (options.cpu_profiler) {
6664 CpuProfile* profile =
6665 cpu_profiler->StopProfiling(String::Empty(isolate));
6666 if (options.cpu_profiler_print) {
6667 const internal::ProfileNode* root =
6668 reinterpret_cast<const internal::ProfileNode*>(
6669 profile->GetTopDownRoot());
6670 root->Print(0);
6671 }
6672 profile->Delete();
6673 cpu_profiler->Dispose();
6674 }
6675
6676#ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
6677 // Send result to parent (fuzzilli) and reset edge guards.
6678 if (fuzzilli_reprl) {
6679 int status = result << 8;
6680 std::vector<bool> bitmap;
6681 if (options.fuzzilli_enable_builtins_coverage) {
6682 bitmap = i::BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->GetCoverageBitmap(
6683 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate));
6684 cov_update_builtins_basic_block_coverage(bitmap);
6685 }
6686 if (options.fuzzilli_coverage_statistics) {
6687 int tot = 0;
6688 for (bool b : bitmap) {
6689 if (b) tot++;
6690 }
6691 static int iteration_counter = 0;
6692 std::ofstream covlog("covlog.txt", std::ios::app);
6693 covlog << iteration_counter << "\t" << tot << "\t"
6694 << sanitizer_cov_count_discovered_edges() << "\t"
6695 << bitmap.size() << std::endl;
6696 iteration_counter++;
6697 }
6698 // In REPRL mode, stdout and stderr can be regular files, so they need
6699 // to be flushed after every execution
6700 fflush(stdout);
6701 fflush(stderr);
6702 CHECK_EQ(write(REPRL_CWFD, &status, 4), 4);
6703 sanitizer_cov_reset_edgeguards();
6704 if (options.fuzzilli_enable_builtins_coverage) {
6705 i::BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->ResetCounts(
6706 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate));
6707 }
6708 }
6709#endif // V8_FUZZILLI
6710 } while (fuzzilli_reprl);
6711
6712 // Shut down contexts and collect garbage.
6713 cached_code_map_.clear();
6714 evaluation_context_.Reset();
6715 stringify_function_.Reset();
6716 ResetOnProfileEndListener(isolate);
6717 CollectGarbage(isolate);
6718 }
6719 OnExit(isolate, true);
6720
6721 // Delete the platform explicitly here to write the tracing output to the
6722 // tracing file.
6723 if (options.trace_enabled) {
6724 tracing_controller->StopTracing();
6725 }
6726 g_platform.reset();
6727
6728#ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_WIN
6729 // We need to free the allocated utf8 filenames in
6730 // PreProcessUnicodeFilenameArg.
6731 for (char* utf8_str : utf8_filenames) {
6732 delete[] utf8_str;
6733 }
6734 utf8_filenames.clear();
6735#endif
6736
6737 return result;
6738}
6739
6740} // namespace v8
6741
6742int main(int argc, char* argv[]) { return v8::Shell::Main(argc, argv); }
6743
6744#undef CHECK
6745#undef DCHECK
